37// Helper for coercing an aggregate argument or return value into an integer
38// array of the same size (including padding) and alignment. This alternate
39// coercion happens only for the RenderScript ABI and can be removed after
40// runtimes that rely on it are no longer supported.
41//
42// RenderScript assumes that the size of the argument / return value in the IR
43// is the same as the size of the corresponding qualified type. This helper
44// coerces the aggregate type into an array of the same size (including
45// padding). This coercion is used in lieu of expansion of struct members or
46// other canonical coercions that return a coerced-type of larger size.
47//
48// Ty - The argument / return value type
49// Context - The associated ASTContext
50// LLVMContext - The associated LLVMContext
51static ABIArgInfo coerceToIntArray(QualType Ty,
52 ASTContext &Context,
53 llvm::LLVMContext &LLVMContext) {
54 // Alignment and Size are measured in bits.
55 const uint64_t Size = Context.getTypeSize(Ty);
56 const uint64_t Alignment = Context.getTypeAlign(Ty);
57 llvm::Type *IntType = llvm::Type::getIntNTy(LLVMContext, Alignment);
58 const uint64_t NumElements = (Size + Alignment - 1) / Alignment;
59 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(llvm::ArrayType::get(IntType, NumElements));
60}
61
62static void AssignToArrayRange(CodeGen::CGBuilderTy &Builder,
63 llvm::Value *Array,
64 llvm::Value *Value,
65 unsigned FirstIndex,
66 unsigned LastIndex) {
67 // Alternatively, we could emit this as a loop in the source.
68 for (unsigned I = FirstIndex; I <= LastIndex; ++I) {
69 llvm::Value *Cell =
70 Builder.CreateConstInBoundsGEP1_32(Builder.getInt8Ty(), Array, I);
71 Builder.CreateAlignedStore(Value, Cell, CharUnits::One());
72 }
73}

75static bool isAggregateTypeForABI(QualType T) {
76 return !CodeGenFunction::hasScalarEvaluationKind(T) ||
77 T->isMemberFunctionPointerType();
78}

83 return ABIArgInfo::getIndirect(getContext().getTypeAlignInChars(Ty),
84 ByRef, Realign, Padding);

100/// Does the given lowering require more than the given number of
101/// registers when expanded?
102///
103/// This is intended to be the basis of a reasonable basic implementation
104/// of should{Pass,Return}IndirectlyForSwift.
105///
106/// For most targets, a limit of four total registers is reasonable; this
107/// limits the amount of code required in order to move around the value
108/// in case it wasn't produced immediately prior to the call by the caller
109/// (or wasn't produced in exactly the right registers) or isn't used
110/// immediately within the callee. But some targets may need to further
111/// limit the register count due to an inability to support that many
112/// return registers.
113static bool occupiesMoreThan(CodeGenTypes &cgt,
114 ArrayRef<llvm::Type*> scalarTypes,
115 unsigned maxAllRegisters) {
116 unsigned intCount = 0, fpCount = 0;
117 for (llvm::Type *type : scalarTypes) {
118 if (type->isPointerTy()) {
119 intCount++;
120 } else if (auto intTy = dyn_cast<llvm::IntegerType>(type)) {
121 auto ptrWidth = cgt.getTarget().getPointerWidth(0);
122 intCount += (intTy->getBitWidth() + ptrWidth - 1) / ptrWidth;
123 } else {
124 assert(type->isVectorTy() || type->isFloatingPointTy());
125 fpCount++;
126 }
127 }
128
129 return (intCount + fpCount > maxAllRegisters);
130}
131
132bool SwiftABIInfo::isLegalVectorTypeForSwift(CharUnits vectorSize,
133 llvm::Type *eltTy,
134 unsigned numElts) const {
135 // The default implementation of this assumes that the target guarantees
136 // 128-bit SIMD support but nothing more.
137 return (vectorSize.getQuantity() > 8 && vectorSize.getQuantity() <= 16);
138}
139
140static CGCXXABI::RecordArgABI getRecordArgABI(const RecordType *RT,
141 CGCXXABI &CXXABI) {
142 const CXXRecordDecl *RD = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RT->getDecl());
143 if (!RD) {
144 if (!RT->getDecl()->canPassInRegisters())
145 return CGCXXABI::RAA_Indirect;
146 return CGCXXABI::RAA_Default;
147 }
148 return CXXABI.getRecordArgABI(RD);
149}
150
151static CGCXXABI::RecordArgABI getRecordArgABI(QualType T,
152 CGCXXABI &CXXABI) {
153 const RecordType *RT = T->getAs<RecordType>();
154 if (!RT)
155 return CGCXXABI::RAA_Default;
156 return getRecordArgABI(RT, CXXABI);
157}
158
159static bool classifyReturnType(const CGCXXABI &CXXABI, CGFunctionInfo &FI,
160 const ABIInfo &Info) {
161 QualType Ty = FI.getReturnType();
162
163 if (const auto *RT = Ty->getAs<RecordType>())
164 if (!isa<CXXRecordDecl>(RT->getDecl()) &&
165 !RT->getDecl()->canPassInRegisters()) {
166 FI.getReturnInfo() = Info.getNaturalAlignIndirect(Ty);
167 return true;
168 }
169
170 return CXXABI.classifyReturnType(FI);
171}
172
173/// Pass transparent unions as if they were the type of the first element. Sema
174/// should ensure that all elements of the union have the same "machine type".
175static QualType useFirstFieldIfTransparentUnion(QualType Ty) {
176 if (const RecordType *UT = Ty->getAsUnionType()) {
177 const RecordDecl *UD = UT->getDecl();
178 if (UD->hasAttr<TransparentUnionAttr>()) {
179 assert(!UD->field_empty() && "sema created an empty transparent union");
180 return UD->field_begin()->getType();
181 }
182 }
183 return Ty;
184}

221LLVM_DUMP_METHOD void ABIArgInfo::dump() const {
222 raw_ostream &OS = llvm::errs();
223 OS << "(ABIArgInfo Kind=";
224 switch (TheKind) {
225 case Direct:
226 OS << "Direct Type=";
227 if (llvm::Type *Ty = getCoerceToType())
228 Ty->print(OS);
229 else
230 OS << "null";
231 break;
232 case Extend:
233 OS << "Extend";
234 break;
235 case Ignore:
236 OS << "Ignore";
237 break;
238 case InAlloca:
239 OS << "InAlloca Offset=" << getInAllocaFieldIndex();
240 break;
241 case Indirect:
242 OS << "Indirect Align=" << getIndirectAlign().getQuantity()
243 << " ByVal=" << getIndirectByVal()
244 << " Realign=" << getIndirectRealign();
245 break;
246 case Expand:
247 OS << "Expand";
248 break;
249 case CoerceAndExpand:
250 OS << "CoerceAndExpand Type=";
251 getCoerceAndExpandType()->print(OS);
252 break;
253 }
254 OS << ")\n";
255}
256
257// Dynamically round a pointer up to a multiple of the given alignment.
258static llvm::Value *emitRoundPointerUpToAlignment(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
259 llvm::Value *Ptr,
260 CharUnits Align) {
261 llvm::Value *PtrAsInt = Ptr;
262 // OverflowArgArea = (OverflowArgArea + Align - 1) & -Align;
263 PtrAsInt = CGF.Builder.CreatePtrToInt(PtrAsInt, CGF.IntPtrTy);
264 PtrAsInt = CGF.Builder.CreateAdd(PtrAsInt,
265 llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.IntPtrTy, Align.getQuantity() - 1));
266 PtrAsInt = CGF.Builder.CreateAnd(PtrAsInt,
267 llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.IntPtrTy, -Align.getQuantity()));
268 PtrAsInt = CGF.Builder.CreateIntToPtr(PtrAsInt,
269 Ptr->getType(),
270 Ptr->getName() + ".aligned");
271 return PtrAsInt;
272}
273
274/// Emit va_arg for a platform using the common void* representation,
275/// where arguments are simply emitted in an array of slots on the stack.
276///
277/// This version implements the core direct-value passing rules.
278///
279/// \param SlotSize - The size and alignment of a stack slot.
280/// Each argument will be allocated to a multiple of this number of
281/// slots, and all the slots will be aligned to this value.
282/// \param AllowHigherAlign - The slot alignment is not a cap;
283/// an argument type with an alignment greater than the slot size
284/// will be emitted on a higher-alignment address, potentially
285/// leaving one or more empty slots behind as padding. If this
286/// is false, the returned address might be less-aligned than
287/// DirectAlign.
288static Address emitVoidPtrDirectVAArg(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
289 Address VAListAddr,
290 llvm::Type *DirectTy,
291 CharUnits DirectSize,
292 CharUnits DirectAlign,
293 CharUnits SlotSize,
294 bool AllowHigherAlign) {
295 // Cast the element type to i8* if necessary. Some platforms define
296 // va_list as a struct containing an i8* instead of just an i8*.
297 if (VAListAddr.getElementType() != CGF.Int8PtrTy)
298 VAListAddr = CGF.Builder.CreateElementBitCast(VAListAddr, CGF.Int8PtrTy);
299
300 llvm::Value *Ptr = CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(VAListAddr, "argp.cur");
301
302 // If the CC aligns values higher than the slot size, do so if needed.
303 Address Addr = Address::invalid();
304 if (AllowHigherAlign && DirectAlign > SlotSize) {
305 llvm::Value *PtrAsInt = Ptr;
306 if (CGF.getTarget().SupportsCapabilities() &&
307 CGF.CGM.getDataLayout().isFatPointer(Ptr->getType())) {
308 PtrAsInt = CGF.getPointerAddress(PtrAsInt);
309 PtrAsInt = CGF.Builder.CreateAdd(PtrAsInt,
310 llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.IntPtrTy, DirectAlign.getQuantity() - 1));
311 PtrAsInt = CGF.Builder.CreateAnd(PtrAsInt,
312 llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.IntPtrTy, -DirectAlign.getQuantity()));
313 Addr = Address(CGF.setPointerAddress(Ptr, PtrAsInt), DirectAlign);
314 } else
315 Addr = Address(emitRoundPointerUpToAlignment(CGF, Ptr, DirectAlign),
316 DirectAlign);
317 } else {
318 Addr = Address(Ptr, SlotSize);
319 }
320
321 // Advance the pointer past the argument, then store that back.
322 CharUnits FullDirectSize = DirectSize.alignTo(SlotSize);
323 Address NextPtr =
324 CGF.Builder.CreateConstInBoundsByteGEP(Addr, FullDirectSize, "argp.next");
325 CGF.Builder.CreateStore(NextPtr.getPointer(), VAListAddr);
326
327 // If the argument is smaller than a slot, and this is a big-endian
328 // target, the argument will be right-adjusted in its slot.
329 if (DirectSize < SlotSize && CGF.CGM.getDataLayout().isBigEndian() &&
330 !DirectTy->isStructTy()) {
331 Addr = CGF.Builder.CreateConstInBoundsByteGEP(Addr, SlotSize - DirectSize);
332 }
333
334 Addr = CGF.Builder.CreateElementBitCast(Addr, DirectTy);
335 return Addr;
336}
337
338/// Emit va_arg for a platform using the common void* representation,
339/// where arguments are simply emitted in an array of slots on the stack.
340///
341/// \param IsIndirect - Values of this type are passed indirectly.
342/// \param ValueInfo - The size and alignment of this type, generally
343/// computed with getContext().getTypeInfoInChars(ValueTy).
344/// \param SlotSizeAndAlign - The size and alignment of a stack slot.
345/// Each argument will be allocated to a multiple of this number of
346/// slots, and all the slots will be aligned to this value.
347/// \param AllowHigherAlign - The slot alignment is not a cap;
348/// an argument type with an alignment greater than the slot size
349/// will be emitted on a higher-alignment address, potentially
350/// leaving one or more empty slots behind as padding.
351static Address emitVoidPtrVAArg(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Address VAListAddr,
352 QualType ValueTy, bool IsIndirect,
353 std::pair<CharUnits, CharUnits> ValueInfo,
354 CharUnits SlotSizeAndAlign,
355 bool AllowHigherAlign) {
356 // The size and alignment of the value that was passed directly.
357 CharUnits DirectSize, DirectAlign;
358 if (IsIndirect) {
359 DirectSize = CGF.getPointerSize();
360 DirectAlign = CGF.getPointerAlign();
361 } else {
362 DirectSize = ValueInfo.first;
363 DirectAlign = ValueInfo.second;
364 }
365
366 // Cast the address we've calculated to the right type.
367 llvm::Type *DirectTy = CGF.ConvertTypeForMem(ValueTy);
368 if (IsIndirect)
369 DirectTy = DirectTy->getPointerTo(0);
370
371 Address Addr = emitVoidPtrDirectVAArg(CGF, VAListAddr, DirectTy,
372 DirectSize, DirectAlign,
373 SlotSizeAndAlign,
374 AllowHigherAlign);
375
376 if (IsIndirect) {
377 Addr = Address(CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(Addr), ValueInfo.second);
378 }
379
380 return Addr;
381
382}
383
384static Address emitMergePHI(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
385 Address Addr1, llvm::BasicBlock *Block1,
386 Address Addr2, llvm::BasicBlock *Block2,
387 const llvm::Twine &Name = "") {
388 assert(Addr1.getType() == Addr2.getType());
389 llvm::PHINode *PHI = CGF.Builder.CreatePHI(Addr1.getType(), 2, Name);
390 PHI->addIncoming(Addr1.getPointer(), Block1);
391 PHI->addIncoming(Addr2.getPointer(), Block2);
392 CharUnits Align = std::min(Addr1.getAlignment(), Addr2.getAlignment());
393 return Address(PHI, Align);
394}

396TargetCodeGenInfo::~TargetCodeGenInfo() { delete Info; }

398// If someone can figure out a general rule for this, that would be great.
399// It's probably just doomed to be platform-dependent, though.
400unsigned TargetCodeGenInfo::getSizeOfUnwindException() const {
401 // Verified for:
402 // x86-64 FreeBSD, Linux, Darwin
403 // x86-32 FreeBSD, Linux, Darwin
404 // PowerPC Linux, Darwin
405 // ARM Darwin (*not* EABI)
406 // AArch64 Linux
407 return 32;
408}

410bool TargetCodeGenInfo::isNoProtoCallVariadic(const CallArgList &args,
411 const FunctionNoProtoType *fnType) const {
412 // The following conventions are known to require this to be false:
413 // x86_stdcall
414 // MIPS
415 // For everything else, we just prefer false unless we opt out.
416 return false;
417}

419void
420TargetCodeGenInfo::getDependentLibraryOption(llvm::StringRef Lib,
421 llvm::SmallString<24> &Opt) const {
422 // This assumes the user is passing a library name like "rt" instead of a
423 // filename like "librt.a/so", and that they don't care whether it's static or
424 // dynamic.
425 Opt = "-l";
426 Opt += Lib;
427}
428
429unsigned TargetCodeGenInfo::getOpenCLKernelCallingConv() const {
430 // OpenCL kernels are called via an explicit runtime API with arguments
431 // set with clSetKernelArg(), not as normal sub-functions.
432 // Return SPIR_KERNEL by default as the kernel calling convention to
433 // ensure the fingerprint is fixed such way that each OpenCL argument
434 // gets one matching argument in the produced kernel function argument
435 // list to enable feasible implementation of clSetKernelArg() with
436 // aggregates etc. In case we would use the default C calling conv here,
437 // clSetKernelArg() might break depending on the target-specific
438 // conventions; different targets might split structs passed as values
439 // to multiple function arguments etc.
440 return llvm::CallingConv::SPIR_KERNEL;
441}

443llvm::Constant *TargetCodeGenInfo::getNullPointer(const CodeGen::CodeGenModule &CGM,
444 llvm::PointerType *T, QualType QT) const {
445 return llvm::ConstantPointerNull::get(T);

448LangAS TargetCodeGenInfo::getGlobalVarAddressSpace(CodeGenModule &CGM,
449 const VarDecl *D) const {
450 assert(!CGM.getLangOpts().OpenCL &&
451 !(CGM.getLangOpts().CUDA && CGM.getLangOpts().CUDAIsDevice) &&
452 "Address space agnostic languages only");
453 return D ? D->getType().getAddressSpace() : LangAS::Default;
454}
455
456llvm::Value *TargetCodeGenInfo::performAddrSpaceCast(
457 CodeGen::CodeGenFunction &CGF, llvm::Value *Src, LangAS SrcAddr,
458 LangAS DestAddr, llvm::Type *DestTy, bool isNonNull) const {
459 // Since target may map different address spaces in AST to the same address
460 // space, an address space conversion may end up as a bitcast.
461 if (auto *C = dyn_cast<llvm::Constant>(Src))
462 return performAddrSpaceCast(CGF.CGM, C, SrcAddr, DestAddr, DestTy);
463 return CGF.Builder.CreatePointerBitCastOrAddrSpaceCast(Src, DestTy);
464}
465
466unsigned TargetCodeGenInfo::getAddressSpaceForType(QualType DestTy,
467 ASTContext& Context) const {
468 if (DestTy->isCHERICapabilityType(Context)) {
469 return getCHERICapabilityAS();
470 }
471 return Context.getTargetAddressSpace(DestTy.getQualifiers());
472}
473
474llvm::Value *TargetCodeGenInfo::getPointerAddress(CodeGen::CodeGenFunction &CGF,
475 llvm::Value *V,
476 const Twine &Name) const {
477 assert(isa<llvm::PointerType>(V->getType()));
478 return CGF.Builder.CreatePtrToInt(V, CGF.PtrDiffTy);
479}
480
481bool TargetCodeGenInfo::canMarkAsNonNull(QualType DestTy, ASTContext& Context) const {
482 unsigned AS = getAddressSpaceForType(DestTy, Context);
483 if (AS == 0 || (Context.getTargetInfo().SupportsCapabilities() &&
484 AS == getCHERICapabilityAS()))
485 return true;
486 return false;
487}
488
489llvm::Constant *
490TargetCodeGenInfo::performAddrSpaceCast(CodeGenModule &CGM, llvm::Constant *Src,
491 LangAS SrcAddr, LangAS DestAddr,
492 llvm::Type *DestTy) const {
493 // Since target may map different address spaces in AST to the same address
494 // space, an address space conversion may end up as a bitcast.
495 return llvm::ConstantExpr::getPointerCast(Src, DestTy);
496}

505
506static bool isEmptyRecord(ASTContext &Context, QualType T, bool AllowArrays);
507
508/// isEmptyField - Return true iff a the field is "empty", that is it
509/// is an unnamed bit-field or an (array of) empty record(s).
510static bool isEmptyField(ASTContext &Context, const FieldDecl *FD,
511 bool AllowArrays) {
512 if (FD->isUnnamedBitfield())
513 return true;
514
515 QualType FT = FD->getType();
516
517 // Constant arrays of empty records count as empty, strip them off.
518 // Constant arrays of zero length always count as empty.
519 if (AllowArrays)
520 while (const ConstantArrayType *AT = Context.getAsConstantArrayType(FT)) {
521 if (AT->getSize() == 0)
522 return true;
523 FT = AT->getElementType();
524 }
525
526 const RecordType *RT = FT->getAs<RecordType>();
527 if (!RT)
528 return false;
529
530 // C++ record fields are never empty, at least in the Itanium ABI.
531 //
532 // FIXME: We should use a predicate for whether this behavior is true in the
533 // current ABI.
534 if (isa<CXXRecordDecl>(RT->getDecl()))
535 return false;
536
537 return isEmptyRecord(Context, FT, AllowArrays);
538}
539
540/// isEmptyRecord - Return true iff a structure contains only empty
541/// fields. Note that a structure with a flexible array member is not
542/// considered empty.
543static bool isEmptyRecord(ASTContext &Context, QualType T, bool AllowArrays) {
544 const RecordType *RT = T->getAs<RecordType>();
545 if (!RT)
546 return false;
547 const RecordDecl *RD = RT->getDecl();
548 if (RD->hasFlexibleArrayMember())
549 return false;
550
551 // If this is a C++ record, check the bases first.
552 if (const CXXRecordDecl *CXXRD = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RD))
553 for (const auto &I : CXXRD->bases())
554 if (!isEmptyRecord(Context, I.getType(), true))
555 return false;
556
557 for (const auto *I : RD->fields())
558 if (!isEmptyField(Context, I, AllowArrays))
559 return false;
560 return true;
561}
562
563/// isSingleElementStruct - Determine if a structure is a "single
564/// element struct", i.e. it has exactly one non-empty field or
565/// exactly one field which is itself a single element
566/// struct. Structures with flexible array members are never
567/// considered single element structs.
568///
569/// \return The field declaration for the single non-empty field, if
570/// it exists.
571static const Type *isSingleElementStruct(QualType T, ASTContext &Context) {
572 const RecordType *RT = T->getAs<RecordType>();
573 if (!RT)
574 return nullptr;
575
576 const RecordDecl *RD = RT->getDecl();
577 if (RD->hasFlexibleArrayMember())
578 return nullptr;
579
580 const Type *Found = nullptr;
581
582 // If this is a C++ record, check the bases first.
583 if (const CXXRecordDecl *CXXRD = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RD)) {
584 for (const auto &I : CXXRD->bases()) {
585 // Ignore empty records.
586 if (isEmptyRecord(Context, I.getType(), true))
587 continue;
588
589 // If we already found an element then this isn't a single-element struct.
590 if (Found)
591 return nullptr;
592
593 // If this is non-empty and not a single element struct, the composite
594 // cannot be a single element struct.
595 Found = isSingleElementStruct(I.getType(), Context);
596 if (!Found)
597 return nullptr;
598 }
599 }
600
601 // Check for single element.
602 for (const auto *FD : RD->fields()) {
603 QualType FT = FD->getType();
604
605 // Ignore empty fields.
606 if (isEmptyField(Context, FD, true))
607 continue;
608
609 // If we already found an element then this isn't a single-element
610 // struct.
611 if (Found)
612 return nullptr;
613
614 // Treat single element arrays as the element.
615 while (const ConstantArrayType *AT = Context.getAsConstantArrayType(FT)) {
616 if (AT->getSize().getZExtValue() != 1)
617 break;
618 FT = AT->getElementType();
619 }
620
621 if (!isAggregateTypeForABI(FT)) {
622 Found = FT.getTypePtr();
623 } else {
624 Found = isSingleElementStruct(FT, Context);
625 if (!Found)
626 return nullptr;
627 }
628 }
629
630 // We don't consider a struct a single-element struct if it has
631 // padding beyond the element type.
632 if (Found && Context.getTypeSize(Found) != Context.getTypeSize(T))
633 return nullptr;
634
635 return Found;
636}
637
638namespace {
639Address EmitVAArgInstr(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Address VAListAddr, QualType Ty,
640 const ABIArgInfo &AI) {
641 // This default implementation defers to the llvm backend's va_arg
642 // instruction. It can handle only passing arguments directly
643 // (typically only handled in the backend for primitive types), or
644 // aggregates passed indirectly by pointer (NOTE: if the "byval"
645 // flag has ABI impact in the callee, this implementation cannot
646 // work.)
647
648 // Only a few cases are covered here at the moment -- those needed
649 // by the default abi.
650 llvm::Value *Val;
651
652 if (AI.isIndirect()) {
653 assert(!AI.getPaddingType() &&
654 "Unexpected PaddingType seen in arginfo in generic VAArg emitter!");
655 assert(
656 !AI.getIndirectRealign() &&
657 "Unexpected IndirectRealign seen in arginfo in generic VAArg emitter!");
658
659 auto TyInfo = CGF.getContext().getTypeInfoInChars(Ty);
660 CharUnits TyAlignForABI = TyInfo.second;
661
662 llvm::Type *BaseTy =
663 CGF.CGM.getPointerInDefaultAS(CGF.ConvertTypeForMem(Ty));
664 llvm::Value *Addr =
665 CGF.Builder.CreateVAArg(VAListAddr.getPointer(), BaseTy);
666 return Address(Addr, TyAlignForABI);
667 } else {
668 assert((AI.isDirect() || AI.isExtend()) &&
669 "Unexpected ArgInfo Kind in generic VAArg emitter!");
670
671 assert(!AI.getInReg() &&
672 "Unexpected InReg seen in arginfo in generic VAArg emitter!");
673 assert(!AI.getPaddingType() &&
674 "Unexpected PaddingType seen in arginfo in generic VAArg emitter!");
675 assert(!AI.getDirectOffset() &&
676 "Unexpected DirectOffset seen in arginfo in generic VAArg emitter!");
677 assert(!AI.getCoerceToType() &&
678 "Unexpected CoerceToType seen in arginfo in generic VAArg emitter!");
679
680 Address Temp = CGF.CreateMemTemp(Ty, "varet");
681 Val = CGF.Builder.CreateVAArg(VAListAddr.getPointer(), CGF.ConvertType(Ty));
682 CGF.Builder.CreateStore(Val, Temp);
683 return Temp;
684 }
685}
686
687/// DefaultABIInfo - The default implementation for ABI specific
688/// details. This implementation provides information which results in
689/// self-consistent and sensible LLVM IR generation, but does not
690/// conform to any particular ABI.
691class DefaultABIInfo : public ABIInfo {
692public:
693 DefaultABIInfo(CodeGen::CodeGenTypes &CGT) : ABIInfo(CGT) {}
694
695 ABIArgInfo classifyReturnType(QualType RetTy) const;
696 ABIArgInfo classifyArgumentType(QualType RetTy) const;
697
698 void computeInfo(CGFunctionInfo &FI) const override {
699 if (!getCXXABI().classifyReturnType(FI))
700 FI.getReturnInfo() = classifyReturnType(FI.getReturnType());
701 for (auto &I : FI.arguments())
702 I.info = classifyArgumentType(I.type);
703 }
704
705 Address EmitVAArg(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Address VAListAddr,
706 QualType Ty) const override {
707 return EmitVAArgInstr(CGF, VAListAddr, Ty, classifyArgumentType(Ty));
708 }
709};
710
711class DefaultTargetCodeGenInfo : public TargetCodeGenInfo {
712public:
713 DefaultTargetCodeGenInfo(CodeGen::CodeGenTypes &CGT)
714 : TargetCodeGenInfo(new DefaultABIInfo(CGT)) {}
715};
716
717ABIArgInfo DefaultABIInfo::classifyArgumentType(QualType Ty) const {
718 Ty = useFirstFieldIfTransparentUnion(Ty);
719
720 if (isAggregateTypeForABI(Ty)) {
721 // Records with non-trivial destructors/copy-constructors should not be
722 // passed by value.
723 if (CGCXXABI::RecordArgABI RAA = getRecordArgABI(Ty, getCXXABI()))
724 return getNaturalAlignIndirect(Ty, RAA == CGCXXABI::RAA_DirectInMemory);
725
726 return getNaturalAlignIndirect(Ty);
727 }
728
729 // Treat an enum type as its underlying type.
730 if (const EnumType *EnumTy = Ty->getAs<EnumType>())
731 Ty = EnumTy->getDecl()->getIntegerType();
732
733 return (Ty->isPromotableIntegerType() ? ABIArgInfo::getExtend(Ty)
734 : ABIArgInfo::getDirect());
735}
736
737ABIArgInfo DefaultABIInfo::classifyReturnType(QualType RetTy) const {
738 if (RetTy->isVoidType())
739 return ABIArgInfo::getIgnore();
740
741 if (isAggregateTypeForABI(RetTy))
742 return getNaturalAlignIndirect(RetTy);
743
744 // Treat an enum type as its underlying type.
745 if (const EnumType *EnumTy = RetTy->getAs<EnumType>())
746 RetTy = EnumTy->getDecl()->getIntegerType();
747
748 return (RetTy->isPromotableIntegerType() ? ABIArgInfo::getExtend(RetTy)
749 : ABIArgInfo::getDirect());
750}
751
752//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
753// WebAssembly ABI Implementation
754//
755// This is a very simple ABI that relies a lot on DefaultABIInfo.
756//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
757
758class WebAssemblyABIInfo final : public SwiftABIInfo {
759 DefaultABIInfo defaultInfo;
760
761public:
762 explicit WebAssemblyABIInfo(CodeGen::CodeGenTypes &CGT)
763 : SwiftABIInfo(CGT), defaultInfo(CGT) {}
764
765private:
766 ABIArgInfo classifyReturnType(QualType RetTy) const;
767 ABIArgInfo classifyArgumentType(QualType Ty) const;
768
769 // DefaultABIInfo's classifyReturnType and classifyArgumentType are
770 // non-virtual, but computeInfo and EmitVAArg are virtual, so we
771 // overload them.
772 void computeInfo(CGFunctionInfo &FI) const override {
773 if (!getCXXABI().classifyReturnType(FI))
774 FI.getReturnInfo() = classifyReturnType(FI.getReturnType());
775 for (auto &Arg : FI.arguments())
776 Arg.info = classifyArgumentType(Arg.type);
777 }
778
779 Address EmitVAArg(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Address VAListAddr,
780 QualType Ty) const override;
781
782 bool shouldPassIndirectlyForSwift(ArrayRef<llvm::Type*> scalars,
783 bool asReturnValue) const override {
784 return occupiesMoreThan(CGT, scalars, /*total*/ 4);
785 }
786
787 bool isSwiftErrorInRegister() const override {
788 return false;
789 }
790};
791
792class WebAssemblyTargetCodeGenInfo final : public TargetCodeGenInfo {
793public:
794 explicit WebAssemblyTargetCodeGenInfo(CodeGen::CodeGenTypes &CGT)
795 : TargetCodeGenInfo(new WebAssemblyABIInfo(CGT)) {}
796
797 void setTargetAttributes(const Decl *D, llvm::GlobalValue *GV,
798 CodeGen::CodeGenModule &CGM) const override {
799 TargetCodeGenInfo::setTargetAttributes(D, GV, CGM);
800 if (const auto *FD = dyn_cast_or_null<FunctionDecl>(D)) {
801 if (const auto *Attr = FD->getAttr<WebAssemblyImportModuleAttr>()) {
802 llvm::Function *Fn = cast<llvm::Function>(GV);
803 llvm::AttrBuilder B;
804 B.addAttribute("wasm-import-module", Attr->getImportModule());
805 Fn->addAttributes(llvm::AttributeList::FunctionIndex, B);
806 }
807 if (const auto *Attr = FD->getAttr<WebAssemblyImportNameAttr>()) {
808 llvm::Function *Fn = cast<llvm::Function>(GV);
809 llvm::AttrBuilder B;
810 B.addAttribute("wasm-import-name", Attr->getImportName());
811 Fn->addAttributes(llvm::AttributeList::FunctionIndex, B);
812 }
813 }
814
815 if (auto *FD = dyn_cast_or_null<FunctionDecl>(D)) {
816 llvm::Function *Fn = cast<llvm::Function>(GV);
817 if (!FD->doesThisDeclarationHaveABody() && !FD->hasPrototype())
818 Fn->addFnAttr("no-prototype");
819 }
820 }
821};
822
823/// Classify argument of given type \p Ty.
824ABIArgInfo WebAssemblyABIInfo::classifyArgumentType(QualType Ty) const {
825 Ty = useFirstFieldIfTransparentUnion(Ty);
826
827 if (isAggregateTypeForABI(Ty)) {
828 // Records with non-trivial destructors/copy-constructors should not be
829 // passed by value.
830 if (auto RAA = getRecordArgABI(Ty, getCXXABI()))
831 return getNaturalAlignIndirect(Ty, RAA == CGCXXABI::RAA_DirectInMemory);
832 // Ignore empty structs/unions.
833 if (isEmptyRecord(getContext(), Ty, true))
834 return ABIArgInfo::getIgnore();
835 // Lower single-element structs to just pass a regular value. TODO: We
836 // could do reasonable-size multiple-element structs too, using getExpand(),
837 // though watch out for things like bitfields.
838 if (const Type *SeltTy = isSingleElementStruct(Ty, getContext()))
839 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(CGT.ConvertType(QualType(SeltTy, 0)));
840 }
841
842 // Otherwise just do the default thing.
843 return defaultInfo.classifyArgumentType(Ty);
844}
845
846ABIArgInfo WebAssemblyABIInfo::classifyReturnType(QualType RetTy) const {
847 if (isAggregateTypeForABI(RetTy)) {
848 // Records with non-trivial destructors/copy-constructors should not be
849 // returned by value.
850 if (!getRecordArgABI(RetTy, getCXXABI())) {
851 // Ignore empty structs/unions.
852 if (isEmptyRecord(getContext(), RetTy, true))
853 return ABIArgInfo::getIgnore();
854 // Lower single-element structs to just return a regular value. TODO: We
855 // could do reasonable-size multiple-element structs too, using
856 // ABIArgInfo::getDirect().
857 if (const Type *SeltTy = isSingleElementStruct(RetTy, getContext()))
858 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(CGT.ConvertType(QualType(SeltTy, 0)));
859 }
860 }
861
862 // Otherwise just do the default thing.
863 return defaultInfo.classifyReturnType(RetTy);
864}
865
866Address WebAssemblyABIInfo::EmitVAArg(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Address VAListAddr,
867 QualType Ty) const {
868 return emitVoidPtrVAArg(CGF, VAListAddr, Ty, /*Indirect=*/ false,
869 getContext().getTypeInfoInChars(Ty),
870 CharUnits::fromQuantity(4),
871 /*AllowHigherAlign=*/ true);
872}
873
874//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
875// le32/PNaCl bitcode ABI Implementation
876//
877// This is a simplified version of the x86_32 ABI. Arguments and return values
878// are always passed on the stack.
879//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
880
881class PNaClABIInfo : public ABIInfo {
882 public:
883 PNaClABIInfo(CodeGen::CodeGenTypes &CGT) : ABIInfo(CGT) {}
884
885 ABIArgInfo classifyReturnType(QualType RetTy) const;
886 ABIArgInfo classifyArgumentType(QualType RetTy) const;
887
888 void computeInfo(CGFunctionInfo &FI) const override;
889 Address EmitVAArg(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
890 Address VAListAddr, QualType Ty) const override;
891};
892
893class PNaClTargetCodeGenInfo : public TargetCodeGenInfo {
894 public:
895 PNaClTargetCodeGenInfo(CodeGen::CodeGenTypes &CGT)
896 : TargetCodeGenInfo(new PNaClABIInfo(CGT)) {}
897};
898
899void PNaClABIInfo::computeInfo(CGFunctionInfo &FI) const {
900 if (!getCXXABI().classifyReturnType(FI))
901 FI.getReturnInfo() = classifyReturnType(FI.getReturnType());
902
903 for (auto &I : FI.arguments())
904 I.info = classifyArgumentType(I.type);
905}
906
907Address PNaClABIInfo::EmitVAArg(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Address VAListAddr,
908 QualType Ty) const {
909 // The PNaCL ABI is a bit odd, in that varargs don't use normal
910 // function classification. Structs get passed directly for varargs
911 // functions, through a rewriting transform in
912 // pnacl-llvm/lib/Transforms/NaCl/ExpandVarArgs.cpp, which allows
913 // this target to actually support a va_arg instructions with an
914 // aggregate type, unlike other targets.
915 return EmitVAArgInstr(CGF, VAListAddr, Ty, ABIArgInfo::getDirect());
916}
917
918/// Classify argument of given type \p Ty.
919ABIArgInfo PNaClABIInfo::classifyArgumentType(QualType Ty) const {
920 if (isAggregateTypeForABI(Ty)) {
921 if (CGCXXABI::RecordArgABI RAA = getRecordArgABI(Ty, getCXXABI()))
922 return getNaturalAlignIndirect(Ty, RAA == CGCXXABI::RAA_DirectInMemory);
923 return getNaturalAlignIndirect(Ty);
924 } else if (const EnumType *EnumTy = Ty->getAs<EnumType>()) {
925 // Treat an enum type as its underlying type.
926 Ty = EnumTy->getDecl()->getIntegerType();
927 } else if (Ty->isFloatingType()) {
928 // Floating-point types don't go inreg.
929 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect();
930 }
931
932 return (Ty->isPromotableIntegerType() ? ABIArgInfo::getExtend(Ty)
933 : ABIArgInfo::getDirect());
934}
935
936ABIArgInfo PNaClABIInfo::classifyReturnType(QualType RetTy) const {
937 if (RetTy->isVoidType())
938 return ABIArgInfo::getIgnore();
939
940 // In the PNaCl ABI we always return records/structures on the stack.
941 if (isAggregateTypeForABI(RetTy))
942 return getNaturalAlignIndirect(RetTy);
943
944 // Treat an enum type as its underlying type.
945 if (const EnumType *EnumTy = RetTy->getAs<EnumType>())
946 RetTy = EnumTy->getDecl()->getIntegerType();
947
948 return (RetTy->isPromotableIntegerType() ? ABIArgInfo::getExtend(RetTy)
949 : ABIArgInfo::getDirect());
950}
951
952static llvm::Type* X86AdjustInlineAsmType(CodeGen::CodeGenFunction &CGF,
953 StringRef Constraint,
954 llvm::Type* Ty) {
955 bool IsMMXCons = llvm::StringSwitch<bool>(Constraint)
956 .Cases("y", "&y", "^Ym", true)
957 .Default(false);
958 if (IsMMXCons && Ty->isVectorTy()) {
959 if (cast<llvm::VectorType>(Ty)->getBitWidth() != 64) {
960 // Invalid MMX constraint
961 return nullptr;
962 }
963
964 return llvm::Type::getX86_MMXTy(CGF.getLLVMContext());
965 }
966
967 // No operation needed
968 return Ty;
969}
970
971/// Returns true if this type can be passed in SSE registers with the
972/// X86_VectorCall calling convention. Shared between x86_32 and x86_64.
973static bool isX86VectorTypeForVectorCall(ASTContext &Context, QualType Ty) {
974 if (const BuiltinType *BT = Ty->getAs<BuiltinType>()) {
975 if (BT->isFloatingPoint() && BT->getKind() != BuiltinType::Half) {
976 if (BT->getKind() == BuiltinType::LongDouble) {
977 if (&Context.getTargetInfo().getLongDoubleFormat() ==
978 &llvm::APFloat::x87DoubleExtended())
979 return false;
980 }
981 return true;
982 }
983 } else if (const VectorType *VT = Ty->getAs<VectorType>()) {
984 // vectorcall can pass XMM, YMM, and ZMM vectors. We don't pass SSE1 MMX
985 // registers specially.
986 unsigned VecSize = Context.getTypeSize(VT);
987 if (VecSize == 128 || VecSize == 256 || VecSize == 512)
988 return true;
989 }
990 return false;
991}
992
993/// Returns true if this aggregate is small enough to be passed in SSE registers
994/// in the X86_VectorCall calling convention. Shared between x86_32 and x86_64.
995static bool isX86VectorCallAggregateSmallEnough(uint64_t NumMembers) {
996 return NumMembers <= 4;
997}
998
999/// Returns a Homogeneous Vector Aggregate ABIArgInfo, used in X86.
1000static ABIArgInfo getDirectX86Hva(llvm::Type* T = nullptr) {
1001 auto AI = ABIArgInfo::getDirect(T);
1002 AI.setInReg(true);
1003 AI.setCanBeFlattened(false);
1004 return AI;
1005}

1007//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
1008// X86-32 ABI Implementation
1009//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
1010
1011/// Similar to llvm::CCState, but for Clang.
1012struct CCState {
1013 CCState(unsigned CC) : CC(CC), FreeRegs(0), FreeSSERegs(0) {}
1014
1015 unsigned CC;
1016 unsigned FreeRegs;
1017 unsigned FreeSSERegs;
1018};
1019
1020enum {
1021 // Vectorcall only allows the first 6 parameters to be passed in registers.
1022 VectorcallMaxParamNumAsReg = 6
1023};
1024
1025/// X86_32ABIInfo - The X86-32 ABI information.
1026class X86_32ABIInfo : public SwiftABIInfo {
1027 enum Class {
1028 Integer,
1029 Float
1030 };
1031
1032 static const unsigned MinABIStackAlignInBytes = 4;
1033
1034 bool IsDarwinVectorABI;
1035 bool IsRetSmallStructInRegABI;
1036 bool IsWin32StructABI;
1037 bool IsSoftFloatABI;
1038 bool IsMCUABI;
1039 unsigned DefaultNumRegisterParameters;
1040 bool IsMMXEnabled;
1041
1042 static bool isRegisterSize(unsigned Size) {
1043 return (Size == 8 || Size == 16 || Size == 32 || Size == 64);
1044 }
1045
1046 bool isHomogeneousAggregateBaseType(QualType Ty) const override {
1047 // FIXME: Assumes vectorcall is in use.
1048 return isX86VectorTypeForVectorCall(getContext(), Ty);
1049 }
1050
1051 bool isHomogeneousAggregateSmallEnough(const Type *Ty,
1052 uint64_t NumMembers) const override {
1053 // FIXME: Assumes vectorcall is in use.
1054 return isX86VectorCallAggregateSmallEnough(NumMembers);
1055 }
1056
1057 bool shouldReturnTypeInRegister(QualType Ty, ASTContext &Context) const;
1058
1059 /// getIndirectResult - Give a source type \arg Ty, return a suitable result
1060 /// such that the argument will be passed in memory.
1061 ABIArgInfo getIndirectResult(QualType Ty, bool ByVal, CCState &State) const;
1062
1063 ABIArgInfo getIndirectReturnResult(QualType Ty, CCState &State) const;
1064
1065 /// Return the alignment to use for the given type on the stack.
1066 unsigned getTypeStackAlignInBytes(QualType Ty, unsigned Align) const;
1067
1068 Class classify(QualType Ty) const;
1069 ABIArgInfo classifyReturnType(QualType RetTy, CCState &State) const;
1070 ABIArgInfo classifyArgumentType(QualType RetTy, CCState &State) const;
1071
1072 /// Updates the number of available free registers, returns
1073 /// true if any registers were allocated.
1074 bool updateFreeRegs(QualType Ty, CCState &State) const;
1075
1076 bool shouldAggregateUseDirect(QualType Ty, CCState &State, bool &InReg,
1077 bool &NeedsPadding) const;
1078 bool shouldPrimitiveUseInReg(QualType Ty, CCState &State) const;
1079
1080 bool canExpandIndirectArgument(QualType Ty) const;
1081
1082 /// Rewrite the function info so that all memory arguments use
1083 /// inalloca.
1084 void rewriteWithInAlloca(CGFunctionInfo &FI) const;
1085
1086 void addFieldToArgStruct(SmallVector<llvm::Type *, 6> &FrameFields,
1087 CharUnits &StackOffset, ABIArgInfo &Info,
1088 QualType Type) const;
1089 void computeVectorCallArgs(CGFunctionInfo &FI, CCState &State,
1090 bool &UsedInAlloca) const;
1091
1092public:
1093
1094 void computeInfo(CGFunctionInfo &FI) const override;
1095 Address EmitVAArg(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Address VAListAddr,
1096 QualType Ty) const override;
1097
1098 X86_32ABIInfo(CodeGen::CodeGenTypes &CGT, bool DarwinVectorABI,
1099 bool RetSmallStructInRegABI, bool Win32StructABI,
1100 unsigned NumRegisterParameters, bool SoftFloatABI,
1101 bool MMXEnabled)
1102 : SwiftABIInfo(CGT), IsDarwinVectorABI(DarwinVectorABI),
1103 IsRetSmallStructInRegABI(RetSmallStructInRegABI),
1104 IsWin32StructABI(Win32StructABI),
1105 IsSoftFloatABI(SoftFloatABI),
1106 IsMCUABI(CGT.getTarget().getTriple().isOSIAMCU()),
1107 DefaultNumRegisterParameters(NumRegisterParameters),
1108 IsMMXEnabled(MMXEnabled) {}
1109
1110 bool shouldPassIndirectlyForSwift(ArrayRef<llvm::Type*> scalars,
1111 bool asReturnValue) const override {
1112 // LLVM's x86-32 lowering currently only assigns up to three
1113 // integer registers and three fp registers. Oddly, it'll use up to
1114 // four vector registers for vectors, but those can overlap with the
1115 // scalar registers.
1116 return occupiesMoreThan(CGT, scalars, /*total*/ 3);
1117 }
1118
1119 bool isSwiftErrorInRegister() const override {
1120 // x86-32 lowering does not support passing swifterror in a register.
1121 return false;
1122 }
1123
1124 bool isPassInMMXRegABI() const {
1125 // The System V i386 psABI requires __m64 to be passed in MMX registers.
1126 // Clang historically had a bug where it failed to apply this rule, and
1127 // some platforms (e.g. Darwin, PS4, and FreeBSD) have opted to maintain
1128 // compatibility with the old Clang behavior, so we only apply it on
1129 // platforms that have specifically requested it (currently just Linux and
1130 // NetBSD).
1131 const llvm::Triple &T = getTarget().getTriple();
1132 if (IsMMXEnabled && (T.isOSLinux() || T.isOSNetBSD()))
1133 return true;
1134 return false;
1135 }
1136};
1137
1138class X86_32TargetCodeGenInfo : public TargetCodeGenInfo {
1139public:

1141 bool RetSmallStructInRegABI, bool Win32StructABI,
1142 unsigned NumRegisterParameters, bool SoftFloatABI,
1143 bool MMXEnabled = false)
1144 : TargetCodeGenInfo(new X86_32ABIInfo(
1145 CGT, DarwinVectorABI, RetSmallStructInRegABI, Win32StructABI,
1146 NumRegisterParameters, SoftFloatABI, MMXEnabled)) {}
1147
1148 static bool isStructReturnInRegABI(
1149 const llvm::Triple &Triple, const CodeGenOptions &Opts);
1150
1151 void setTargetAttributes(const Decl *D, llvm::GlobalValue *GV,
1152 CodeGen::CodeGenModule &CGM) const override;
1153
1154 int getDwarfEHStackPointer(CodeGen::CodeGenModule &CGM) const override {
1155 // Darwin uses different dwarf register numbers for EH.
1156 if (CGM.getTarget().getTriple().isOSDarwin()) return 5;
1157 return 4;
1158 }
1159
1160 bool initDwarfEHRegSizeTable(CodeGen::CodeGenFunction &CGF,
1161 llvm::Value *Address) const override;
1162
1163 llvm::Type* adjustInlineAsmType(CodeGen::CodeGenFunction &CGF,
1164 StringRef Constraint,
1165 llvm::Type* Ty) const override {
1166 return X86AdjustInlineAsmType(CGF, Constraint, Ty);
1167 }
1168
1169 void addReturnRegisterOutputs(CodeGenFunction &CGF, LValue ReturnValue,
1170 std::string &Constraints,
1171 std::vector<llvm::Type *> &ResultRegTypes,
1172 std::vector<llvm::Type *> &ResultTruncRegTypes,
1173 std::vector<LValue> &ResultRegDests,
1174 std::string &AsmString,
1175 unsigned NumOutputs) const override;
1176
1177 llvm::Constant *
1178 getUBSanFunctionSignature(CodeGen::CodeGenModule &CGM) const override {
1179 unsigned Sig = (0xeb << 0) | // jmp rel8
1180 (0x06 << 8) | // .+0x08
1181 ('v' << 16) |
1182 ('2' << 24);
1183 return llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.Int32Ty, Sig);
1184 }
1185
1186 StringRef getARCRetainAutoreleasedReturnValueMarker() const override {
1187 return "movl\t%ebp, %ebp"
1188 "\t\t// marker for objc_retainAutoreleaseReturnValue";
1189 }
1190};

1192}
1193
1194/// Rewrite input constraint references after adding some output constraints.
1195/// In the case where there is one output and one input and we add one output,
1196/// we need to replace all operand references greater than or equal to 1:
1197/// mov $0, $1
1198/// mov eax, $1
1199/// The result will be:
1200/// mov $0, $2
1201/// mov eax, $2
1202static void rewriteInputConstraintReferences(unsigned FirstIn,
1203 unsigned NumNewOuts,
1204 std::string &AsmString) {
1205 std::string Buf;
1206 llvm::raw_string_ostream OS(Buf);
1207 size_t Pos = 0;
1208 while (Pos < AsmString.size()) {
1209 size_t DollarStart = AsmString.find('$', Pos);
1210 if (DollarStart == std::string::npos)
1211 DollarStart = AsmString.size();
1212 size_t DollarEnd = AsmString.find_first_not_of('$', DollarStart);
1213 if (DollarEnd == std::string::npos)
1214 DollarEnd = AsmString.size();
1215 OS << StringRef(&AsmString[Pos], DollarEnd - Pos);
1216 Pos = DollarEnd;
1217 size_t NumDollars = DollarEnd - DollarStart;
1218 if (NumDollars % 2 != 0 && Pos < AsmString.size()) {
1219 // We have an operand reference.
1220 size_t DigitStart = Pos;
1221 size_t DigitEnd = AsmString.find_first_not_of("0123456789", DigitStart);
1222 if (DigitEnd == std::string::npos)
1223 DigitEnd = AsmString.size();
1224 StringRef OperandStr(&AsmString[DigitStart], DigitEnd - DigitStart);
1225 unsigned OperandIndex;
1226 if (!OperandStr.getAsInteger(10, OperandIndex)) {
1227 if (OperandIndex >= FirstIn)
1228 OperandIndex += NumNewOuts;
1229 OS << OperandIndex;
1230 } else {
1231 OS << OperandStr;
1232 }
1233 Pos = DigitEnd;
1234 }
1235 }
1236 AsmString = std::move(OS.str());
1237}
1238
1239/// Add output constraints for EAX:EDX because they are return registers.
1240void X86_32TargetCodeGenInfo::addReturnRegisterOutputs(
1241 CodeGenFunction &CGF, LValue ReturnSlot, std::string &Constraints,
1242 std::vector<llvm::Type *> &ResultRegTypes,
1243 std::vector<llvm::Type *> &ResultTruncRegTypes,
1244 std::vector<LValue> &ResultRegDests, std::string &AsmString,
1245 unsigned NumOutputs) const {
1246 uint64_t RetWidth = CGF.getContext().getTypeSize(ReturnSlot.getType());
1247
1248 // Use the EAX constraint if the width is 32 or smaller and EAX:EDX if it is
1249 // larger.
1250 if (!Constraints.empty())
1251 Constraints += ',';
1252 if (RetWidth <= 32) {
1253 Constraints += "={eax}";
1254 ResultRegTypes.push_back(CGF.Int32Ty);
1255 } else {
1256 // Use the 'A' constraint for EAX:EDX.
1257 Constraints += "=A";
1258 ResultRegTypes.push_back(CGF.Int64Ty);
1259 }
1260
1261 // Truncate EAX or EAX:EDX to an integer of the appropriate size.
1262 llvm::Type *CoerceTy = llvm::IntegerType::get(CGF.getLLVMContext(), RetWidth);
1263 ResultTruncRegTypes.push_back(CoerceTy);
1264
1265 // Coerce the integer by bitcasting the return slot pointer.
1266 ReturnSlot.setAddress(CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(ReturnSlot.getAddress(),
1267 CoerceTy->getPointerTo(getDefaultAS())));
1268 ResultRegDests.push_back(ReturnSlot);
1269
1270 rewriteInputConstraintReferences(NumOutputs, 1, AsmString);
1271}
1272
1273/// shouldReturnTypeInRegister - Determine if the given type should be
1274/// returned in a register (for the Darwin and MCU ABI).
1275bool X86_32ABIInfo::shouldReturnTypeInRegister(QualType Ty,
1276 ASTContext &Context) const {
1277 uint64_t Size = Context.getTypeSize(Ty);
1278
1279 // For i386, type must be register sized.
1280 // For the MCU ABI, it only needs to be <= 8-byte
1281 if ((IsMCUABI && Size > 64) || (!IsMCUABI && !isRegisterSize(Size)))
1282 return false;
1283
1284 if (Ty->isVectorType()) {
1285 // 64- and 128- bit vectors inside structures are not returned in
1286 // registers.
1287 if (Size == 64 || Size == 128)
1288 return false;
1289
1290 return true;
1291 }
1292
1293 // If this is a builtin, pointer, enum, complex type, member pointer, or
1294 // member function pointer it is ok.
1295 if (Ty->getAs<BuiltinType>() || Ty->hasPointerRepresentation() ||
1296 Ty->isAnyComplexType() || Ty->isEnumeralType() ||
1297 Ty->isBlockPointerType() || Ty->isMemberPointerType())
1298 return true;
1299
1300 // Arrays are treated like records.
1301 if (const ConstantArrayType *AT = Context.getAsConstantArrayType(Ty))
1302 return shouldReturnTypeInRegister(AT->getElementType(), Context);
1303
1304 // Otherwise, it must be a record type.
1305 const RecordType *RT = Ty->getAs<RecordType>();
1306 if (!RT) return false;
1307
1308 // FIXME: Traverse bases here too.
1309
1310 // Structure types are passed in register if all fields would be
1311 // passed in a register.
1312 for (const auto *FD : RT->getDecl()->fields()) {
1313 // Empty fields are ignored.
1314 if (isEmptyField(Context, FD, true))
1315 continue;
1316
1317 // Check fields recursively.
1318 if (!shouldReturnTypeInRegister(FD->getType(), Context))
1319 return false;
1320 }
1321 return true;
1322}
1323
1324static bool is32Or64BitBasicType(QualType Ty, ASTContext &Context) {
1325 // Treat complex types as the element type.
1326 if (const ComplexType *CTy = Ty->getAs<ComplexType>())
1327 Ty = CTy->getElementType();
1328
1329 // Check for a type which we know has a simple scalar argument-passing
1330 // convention without any padding. (We're specifically looking for 32
1331 // and 64-bit integer and integer-equivalents, float, and double.)
1332 if (!Ty->getAs<BuiltinType>() && !Ty->hasPointerRepresentation() &&
1333 !Ty->isEnumeralType() && !Ty->isBlockPointerType())
1334 return false;
1335
1336 uint64_t Size = Context.getTypeSize(Ty);
1337 return Size == 32 || Size == 64;
1338}
1339
1340static bool addFieldSizes(ASTContext &Context, const RecordDecl *RD,
1341 uint64_t &Size) {
1342 for (const auto *FD : RD->fields()) {
1343 // Scalar arguments on the stack get 4 byte alignment on x86. If the
1344 // argument is smaller than 32-bits, expanding the struct will create
1345 // alignment padding.
1346 if (!is32Or64BitBasicType(FD->getType(), Context))
1347 return false;
1348
1349 // FIXME: Reject bit-fields wholesale; there are two problems, we don't know
1350 // how to expand them yet, and the predicate for telling if a bitfield still
1351 // counts as "basic" is more complicated than what we were doing previously.
1352 if (FD->isBitField())
1353 return false;
1354
1355 Size += Context.getTypeSize(FD->getType());
1356 }
1357 return true;
1358}
1359
1360static bool addBaseAndFieldSizes(ASTContext &Context, const CXXRecordDecl *RD,
1361 uint64_t &Size) {
1362 // Don't do this if there are any non-empty bases.
1363 for (const CXXBaseSpecifier &Base : RD->bases()) {
1364 if (!addBaseAndFieldSizes(Context, Base.getType()->getAsCXXRecordDecl(),
1365 Size))
1366 return false;
1367 }
1368 if (!addFieldSizes(Context, RD, Size))
1369 return false;
1370 return true;
1371}
1372
1373/// Test whether an argument type which is to be passed indirectly (on the
1374/// stack) would have the equivalent layout if it was expanded into separate
1375/// arguments. If so, we prefer to do the latter to avoid inhibiting
1376/// optimizations.
1377bool X86_32ABIInfo::canExpandIndirectArgument(QualType Ty) const {
1378 // We can only expand structure types.
1379 const RecordType *RT = Ty->getAs<RecordType>();
1380 if (!RT)
1381 return false;
1382 const RecordDecl *RD = RT->getDecl();
1383 uint64_t Size = 0;
1384 if (const CXXRecordDecl *CXXRD = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RD)) {
1385 if (!IsWin32StructABI) {
1386 // On non-Windows, we have to conservatively match our old bitcode
1387 // prototypes in order to be ABI-compatible at the bitcode level.
1388 if (!CXXRD->isCLike())
1389 return false;
1390 } else {
1391 // Don't do this for dynamic classes.
1392 if (CXXRD->isDynamicClass())
1393 return false;
1394 }
1395 if (!addBaseAndFieldSizes(getContext(), CXXRD, Size))
1396 return false;
1397 } else {
1398 if (!addFieldSizes(getContext(), RD, Size))
1399 return false;
1400 }
1401
1402 // We can do this if there was no alignment padding.
1403 return Size == getContext().getTypeSize(Ty);
1404}
1405
1406ABIArgInfo X86_32ABIInfo::getIndirectReturnResult(QualType RetTy, CCState &State) const {
1407 // If the return value is indirect, then the hidden argument is consuming one
1408 // integer register.
1409 if (State.FreeRegs) {
1410 --State.FreeRegs;
1411 if (!IsMCUABI)
1412 return getNaturalAlignIndirectInReg(RetTy);
1413 }
1414 return getNaturalAlignIndirect(RetTy, /*ByVal=*/false);
1415}
1416
1417ABIArgInfo X86_32ABIInfo::classifyReturnType(QualType RetTy,
1418 CCState &State) const {
1419 if (RetTy->isVoidType())
1420 return ABIArgInfo::getIgnore();
1421
1422 const Type *Base = nullptr;
1423 uint64_t NumElts = 0;
1424 if ((State.CC == llvm::CallingConv::X86_VectorCall ||
1425 State.CC == llvm::CallingConv::X86_RegCall) &&
1426 isHomogeneousAggregate(RetTy, Base, NumElts)) {
1427 // The LLVM struct type for such an aggregate should lower properly.
1428 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect();
1429 }
1430
1431 if (const VectorType *VT = RetTy->getAs<VectorType>()) {
1432 uint64_t Size = getContext().getTypeSize(RetTy);
1433 // On Darwin, some vectors are returned in registers.
1434 if (IsDarwinVectorABI) {
1435 // 128-bit vectors are a special case; they are returned in
1436 // registers and we need to make sure to pick a type the LLVM
1437 // backend will like.
1438 if (Size == 128)
1439 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(llvm::VectorType::get(
1440 llvm::Type::getInt64Ty(getVMContext()), 2));
1441
1442 // Always return in register if it fits in a general purpose
1443 // register, or if it is 64 bits and has a single element.
1444 if ((Size == 8 || Size == 16 || Size == 32) ||
1445 (Size == 64 && VT->getNumElements() == 1))
1446 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(llvm::IntegerType::get(getVMContext(),
1447 Size));
1448
1449 return getIndirectReturnResult(RetTy, State);
1450 }
1451
1452 if (VT->getElementType()->isIntegerType() && Size == 64 &&
1453 isPassInMMXRegABI())
1454 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(llvm::Type::getX86_MMXTy(getVMContext()));
1455
1456 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect();
1457 }
1458
1459 if (isAggregateTypeForABI(RetTy)) {
1460 if (const RecordType *RT = RetTy->getAs<RecordType>()) {
1461 // Structures with flexible arrays are always indirect.
1462 if (RT->getDecl()->hasFlexibleArrayMember())
1463 return getIndirectReturnResult(RetTy, State);
1464 }
1465
1466 // If specified, structs and unions are always indirect.
1467 if (!IsRetSmallStructInRegABI && !RetTy->isAnyComplexType())
1468 return getIndirectReturnResult(RetTy, State);
1469
1470 // Ignore empty structs/unions.
1471 if (isEmptyRecord(getContext(), RetTy, true))
1472 return ABIArgInfo::getIgnore();
1473
1474 // Small structures which are register sized are generally returned
1475 // in a register.
1476 if (shouldReturnTypeInRegister(RetTy, getContext())) {
1477 uint64_t Size = getContext().getTypeSize(RetTy);
1478
1479 // As a special-case, if the struct is a "single-element" struct, and
1480 // the field is of type "float" or "double", return it in a
1481 // floating-point register. (MSVC does not apply this special case.)
1482 // We apply a similar transformation for pointer types to improve the
1483 // quality of the generated IR.
1484 if (const Type *SeltTy = isSingleElementStruct(RetTy, getContext()))
1485 if ((!IsWin32StructABI && SeltTy->isRealFloatingType())
1486 || SeltTy->hasPointerRepresentation())
1487 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(CGT.ConvertType(QualType(SeltTy, 0)));
1488
1489 // FIXME: We should be able to narrow this integer in cases with dead
1490 // padding.
1491 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(llvm::IntegerType::get(getVMContext(),Size));
1492 }
1493
1494 return getIndirectReturnResult(RetTy, State);
1495 }
1496
1497 // Treat an enum type as its underlying type.
1498 if (const EnumType *EnumTy = RetTy->getAs<EnumType>())
1499 RetTy = EnumTy->getDecl()->getIntegerType();
1500
1501 return (RetTy->isPromotableIntegerType() ? ABIArgInfo::getExtend(RetTy)
1502 : ABIArgInfo::getDirect());
1503}
1504
1505static bool isSSEVectorType(ASTContext &Context, QualType Ty) {
1506 return Ty->getAs<VectorType>() && Context.getTypeSize(Ty) == 128;
1507}
1508
1509static bool isRecordWithSSEVectorType(ASTContext &Context, QualType Ty) {
1510 const RecordType *RT = Ty->getAs<RecordType>();
1511 if (!RT)
1512 return 0;
1513 const RecordDecl *RD = RT->getDecl();
1514
1515 // If this is a C++ record, check the bases first.
1516 if (const CXXRecordDecl *CXXRD = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RD))
1517 for (const auto &I : CXXRD->bases())
1518 if (!isRecordWithSSEVectorType(Context, I.getType()))
1519 return false;
1520
1521 for (const auto *i : RD->fields()) {
1522 QualType FT = i->getType();
1523
1524 if (isSSEVectorType(Context, FT))
1525 return true;
1526
1527 if (isRecordWithSSEVectorType(Context, FT))
1528 return true;
1529 }
1530
1531 return false;
1532}
1533
1534unsigned X86_32ABIInfo::getTypeStackAlignInBytes(QualType Ty,
1535 unsigned Align) const {
1536 // Otherwise, if the alignment is less than or equal to the minimum ABI
1537 // alignment, just use the default; the backend will handle this.
1538 if (Align <= MinABIStackAlignInBytes)
1539 return 0; // Use default alignment.
1540
1541 // On non-Darwin, the stack type alignment is always 4.
1542 if (!IsDarwinVectorABI) {
1543 // Set explicit alignment, since we may need to realign the top.
1544 return MinABIStackAlignInBytes;
1545 }
1546
1547 // Otherwise, if the type contains an SSE vector type, the alignment is 16.
1548 if (Align >= 16 && (isSSEVectorType(getContext(), Ty) ||
1549 isRecordWithSSEVectorType(getContext(), Ty)))
1550 return 16;
1551
1552 return MinABIStackAlignInBytes;
1553}
1554
1555ABIArgInfo X86_32ABIInfo::getIndirectResult(QualType Ty, bool ByVal,
1556 CCState &State) const {
1557 if (!ByVal) {
1558 if (State.FreeRegs) {
1559 --State.FreeRegs; // Non-byval indirects just use one pointer.
1560 if (!IsMCUABI)
1561 return getNaturalAlignIndirectInReg(Ty);
1562 }
1563 return getNaturalAlignIndirect(Ty, false);
1564 }
1565
1566 // Compute the byval alignment.
1567 unsigned TypeAlign = getContext().getTypeAlign(Ty) / 8;
1568 unsigned StackAlign = getTypeStackAlignInBytes(Ty, TypeAlign);
1569 if (StackAlign == 0)
1570 return ABIArgInfo::getIndirect(CharUnits::fromQuantity(4), /*ByVal=*/true);
1571
1572 // If the stack alignment is less than the type alignment, realign the
1573 // argument.
1574 bool Realign = TypeAlign > StackAlign;
1575 return ABIArgInfo::getIndirect(CharUnits::fromQuantity(StackAlign),
1576 /*ByVal=*/true, Realign);
1577}
1578
1579X86_32ABIInfo::Class X86_32ABIInfo::classify(QualType Ty) const {
1580 const Type *T = isSingleElementStruct(Ty, getContext());
1581 if (!T)
1582 T = Ty.getTypePtr();
1583
1584 if (const BuiltinType *BT = T->getAs<BuiltinType>()) {
1585 BuiltinType::Kind K = BT->getKind();
1586 if (K == BuiltinType::Float || K == BuiltinType::Double)
1587 return Float;
1588 }
1589 return Integer;
1590}
1591
1592bool X86_32ABIInfo::updateFreeRegs(QualType Ty, CCState &State) const {
1593 if (!IsSoftFloatABI) {
1594 Class C = classify(Ty);
1595 if (C == Float)
1596 return false;
1597 }
1598
1599 unsigned Size = getContext().getTypeSize(Ty);
1600 unsigned SizeInRegs = (Size + 31) / 32;
1601
1602 if (SizeInRegs == 0)
1603 return false;
1604
1605 if (!IsMCUABI) {
1606 if (SizeInRegs > State.FreeRegs) {
1607 State.FreeRegs = 0;
1608 return false;
1609 }
1610 } else {
1611 // The MCU psABI allows passing parameters in-reg even if there are
1612 // earlier parameters that are passed on the stack. Also,
1613 // it does not allow passing >8-byte structs in-register,
1614 // even if there are 3 free registers available.
1615 if (SizeInRegs > State.FreeRegs || SizeInRegs > 2)
1616 return false;
1617 }
1618
1619 State.FreeRegs -= SizeInRegs;
1620 return true;
1621}
1622
1623bool X86_32ABIInfo::shouldAggregateUseDirect(QualType Ty, CCState &State,
1624 bool &InReg,
1625 bool &NeedsPadding) const {
1626 // On Windows, aggregates other than HFAs are never passed in registers, and
1627 // they do not consume register slots. Homogenous floating-point aggregates
1628 // (HFAs) have already been dealt with at this point.
1629 if (IsWin32StructABI && isAggregateTypeForABI(Ty))
1630 return false;
1631
1632 NeedsPadding = false;
1633 InReg = !IsMCUABI;
1634
1635 if (!updateFreeRegs(Ty, State))
1636 return false;
1637
1638 if (IsMCUABI)
1639 return true;
1640
1641 if (State.CC == llvm::CallingConv::X86_FastCall ||
1642 State.CC == llvm::CallingConv::X86_VectorCall ||
1643 State.CC == llvm::CallingConv::X86_RegCall) {
1644 if (getContext().getTypeSize(Ty) <= 32 && State.FreeRegs)
1645 NeedsPadding = true;
1646
1647 return false;
1648 }
1649
1650 return true;
1651}
1652
1653bool X86_32ABIInfo::shouldPrimitiveUseInReg(QualType Ty, CCState &State) const {
1654 if (!updateFreeRegs(Ty, State))
1655 return false;
1656
1657 if (IsMCUABI)
1658 return false;
1659
1660 if (State.CC == llvm::CallingConv::X86_FastCall ||
1661 State.CC == llvm::CallingConv::X86_VectorCall ||
1662 State.CC == llvm::CallingConv::X86_RegCall) {
1663 if (getContext().getTypeSize(Ty) > 32)
1664 return false;
1665
1666 return (Ty->isIntegralOrEnumerationType() || Ty->isPointerType() ||
1667 Ty->isReferenceType());
1668 }
1669
1670 return true;
1671}
1672
1673ABIArgInfo X86_32ABIInfo::classifyArgumentType(QualType Ty,
1674 CCState &State) const {
1675 // FIXME: Set alignment on indirect arguments.
1676
1677 Ty = useFirstFieldIfTransparentUnion(Ty);
1678
1679 // Check with the C++ ABI first.
1680 const RecordType *RT = Ty->getAs<RecordType>();
1681 if (RT) {
1682 CGCXXABI::RecordArgABI RAA = getRecordArgABI(RT, getCXXABI());
1683 if (RAA == CGCXXABI::RAA_Indirect) {
1684 return getIndirectResult(Ty, false, State);
1685 } else if (RAA == CGCXXABI::RAA_DirectInMemory) {
1686 // The field index doesn't matter, we'll fix it up later.
1687 return ABIArgInfo::getInAlloca(/*FieldIndex=*/0);
1688 }
1689 }
1690
1691 // Regcall uses the concept of a homogenous vector aggregate, similar
1692 // to other targets.
1693 const Type *Base = nullptr;
1694 uint64_t NumElts = 0;
1695 if (State.CC == llvm::CallingConv::X86_RegCall &&
1696 isHomogeneousAggregate(Ty, Base, NumElts)) {
1697
1698 if (State.FreeSSERegs >= NumElts) {
1699 State.FreeSSERegs -= NumElts;
1700 if (Ty->isBuiltinType() || Ty->isVectorType())
1701 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect();
1702 return ABIArgInfo::getExpand();
1703 }
1704 return getIndirectResult(Ty, /*ByVal=*/false, State);
1705 }
1706
1707 if (isAggregateTypeForABI(Ty)) {
1708 // Structures with flexible arrays are always indirect.
1709 // FIXME: This should not be byval!
1710 if (RT && RT->getDecl()->hasFlexibleArrayMember())
1711 return getIndirectResult(Ty, true, State);
1712
1713 // Ignore empty structs/unions on non-Windows.
1714 if (!IsWin32StructABI && isEmptyRecord(getContext(), Ty, true))
1715 return ABIArgInfo::getIgnore();
1716
1717 llvm::LLVMContext &LLVMContext = getVMContext();
1718 llvm::IntegerType *Int32 = llvm::Type::getInt32Ty(LLVMContext);
1719 bool NeedsPadding = false;
1720 bool InReg;
1721 if (shouldAggregateUseDirect(Ty, State, InReg, NeedsPadding)) {
1722 unsigned SizeInRegs = (getContext().getTypeSize(Ty) + 31) / 32;
1723 SmallVector<llvm::Type*, 3> Elements(SizeInRegs, Int32);
1724 llvm::Type *Result = llvm::StructType::get(LLVMContext, Elements);
1725 if (InReg)
1726 return ABIArgInfo::getDirectInReg(Result);
1727 else
1728 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(Result);
1729 }
1730 llvm::IntegerType *PaddingType = NeedsPadding ? Int32 : nullptr;
1731
1732 // Expand small (<= 128-bit) record types when we know that the stack layout
1733 // of those arguments will match the struct. This is important because the
1734 // LLVM backend isn't smart enough to remove byval, which inhibits many
1735 // optimizations.
1736 // Don't do this for the MCU if there are still free integer registers
1737 // (see X86_64 ABI for full explanation).
1738 if (getContext().getTypeSize(Ty) <= 4 * 32 &&
1739 (!IsMCUABI || State.FreeRegs == 0) && canExpandIndirectArgument(Ty))
1740 return ABIArgInfo::getExpandWithPadding(
1741 State.CC == llvm::CallingConv::X86_FastCall ||
1742 State.CC == llvm::CallingConv::X86_VectorCall ||
1743 State.CC == llvm::CallingConv::X86_RegCall,
1744 PaddingType);
1745
1746 return getIndirectResult(Ty, true, State);
1747 }
1748
1749 if (const VectorType *VT = Ty->getAs<VectorType>()) {
1750 uint64_t Size = getContext().getTypeSize(Ty);
1751 // On Darwin, some vectors are passed in memory, we handle this by passing
1752 // it as an i8/i16/i32/i64.
1753 if (IsDarwinVectorABI) {
1754 if ((Size == 8 || Size == 16 || Size == 32) ||
1755 (Size == 64 && VT->getNumElements() == 1))
1756 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(llvm::IntegerType::get(getVMContext(),
1757 Size));
1758 }
1759
1760 if (VT->getElementType()->isIntegerType() && Size == 64) {
1761 if (isPassInMMXRegABI())
1762 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(llvm::Type::getX86_MMXTy(getVMContext()));
1763 else
1764 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(
1765 llvm::IntegerType::get(getVMContext(), 64));
1766 }
1767 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect();
1768 }
1769
1770 if (const EnumType *EnumTy = Ty->getAs<EnumType>())
1771 Ty = EnumTy->getDecl()->getIntegerType();
1772
1773 bool InReg = shouldPrimitiveUseInReg(Ty, State);
1774
1775 if (Ty->isPromotableIntegerType()) {
1776 if (InReg)
1777 return ABIArgInfo::getExtendInReg(Ty);
1778 return ABIArgInfo::getExtend(Ty);
1779 }
1780
1781 if (InReg)
1782 return ABIArgInfo::getDirectInReg();
1783 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect();
1784}
1785
1786void X86_32ABIInfo::computeVectorCallArgs(CGFunctionInfo &FI, CCState &State,
1787 bool &UsedInAlloca) const {
1788 // Vectorcall x86 works subtly different than in x64, so the format is
1789 // a bit different than the x64 version. First, all vector types (not HVAs)
1790 // are assigned, with the first 6 ending up in the YMM0-5 or XMM0-5 registers.
1791 // This differs from the x64 implementation, where the first 6 by INDEX get
1792 // registers.
1793 // After that, integers AND HVAs are assigned Left to Right in the same pass.
1794 // Integers are passed as ECX/EDX if one is available (in order). HVAs will
1795 // first take up the remaining YMM/XMM registers. If insufficient registers
1796 // remain but an integer register (ECX/EDX) is available, it will be passed
1797 // in that, else, on the stack.
1798 for (auto &I : FI.arguments()) {
1799 // First pass do all the vector types.
1800 const Type *Base = nullptr;
1801 uint64_t NumElts = 0;
1802 const QualType& Ty = I.type;
1803 if ((Ty->isVectorType() || Ty->isBuiltinType()) &&
1804 isHomogeneousAggregate(Ty, Base, NumElts)) {
1805 if (State.FreeSSERegs >= NumElts) {
1806 State.FreeSSERegs -= NumElts;
1807 I.info = ABIArgInfo::getDirect();
1808 } else {
1809 I.info = classifyArgumentType(Ty, State);
1810 }
1811 UsedInAlloca |= (I.info.getKind() == ABIArgInfo::InAlloca);
1812 }
1813 }
1814
1815 for (auto &I : FI.arguments()) {
1816 // Second pass, do the rest!
1817 const Type *Base = nullptr;
1818 uint64_t NumElts = 0;
1819 const QualType& Ty = I.type;
1820 bool IsHva = isHomogeneousAggregate(Ty, Base, NumElts);
1821
1822 if (IsHva && !Ty->isVectorType() && !Ty->isBuiltinType()) {
1823 // Assign true HVAs (non vector/native FP types).
1824 if (State.FreeSSERegs >= NumElts) {
1825 State.FreeSSERegs -= NumElts;
1826 I.info = getDirectX86Hva();
1827 } else {
1828 I.info = getIndirectResult(Ty, /*ByVal=*/false, State);
1829 }
1830 } else if (!IsHva) {
1831 // Assign all Non-HVAs, so this will exclude Vector/FP args.
1832 I.info = classifyArgumentType(Ty, State);
1833 UsedInAlloca |= (I.info.getKind() == ABIArgInfo::InAlloca);
1834 }
1835 }
1836}
1837
1838void X86_32ABIInfo::computeInfo(CGFunctionInfo &FI) const {
1839 CCState State(FI.getCallingConvention());
1840 if (IsMCUABI)
1841 State.FreeRegs = 3;
1842 else if (State.CC == llvm::CallingConv::X86_FastCall)
1843 State.FreeRegs = 2;
1844 else if (State.CC == llvm::CallingConv::X86_VectorCall) {
1845 State.FreeRegs = 2;
1846 State.FreeSSERegs = 6;
1847 } else if (FI.getHasRegParm())
1848 State.FreeRegs = FI.getRegParm();
1849 else if (State.CC == llvm::CallingConv::X86_RegCall) {
1850 State.FreeRegs = 5;
1851 State.FreeSSERegs = 8;
1852 } else
1853 State.FreeRegs = DefaultNumRegisterParameters;
1854
1855 if (!::classifyReturnType(getCXXABI(), FI, *this)) {
1856 FI.getReturnInfo() = classifyReturnType(FI.getReturnType(), State);
1857 } else if (FI.getReturnInfo().isIndirect()) {
1858 // The C++ ABI is not aware of register usage, so we have to check if the
1859 // return value was sret and put it in a register ourselves if appropriate.
1860 if (State.FreeRegs) {
1861 --State.FreeRegs; // The sret parameter consumes a register.
1862 if (!IsMCUABI)
1863 FI.getReturnInfo().setInReg(true);
1864 }
1865 }
1866
1867 // The chain argument effectively gives us another free register.
1868 if (FI.isChainCall())
1869 ++State.FreeRegs;
1870
1871 bool UsedInAlloca = false;
1872 if (State.CC == llvm::CallingConv::X86_VectorCall) {
1873 computeVectorCallArgs(FI, State, UsedInAlloca);
1874 } else {
1875 // If not vectorcall, revert to normal behavior.
1876 for (auto &I : FI.arguments()) {
1877 I.info = classifyArgumentType(I.type, State);
1878 UsedInAlloca |= (I.info.getKind() == ABIArgInfo::InAlloca);
1879 }
1880 }
1881
1882 // If we needed to use inalloca for any argument, do a second pass and rewrite
1883 // all the memory arguments to use inalloca.
1884 if (UsedInAlloca)
1885 rewriteWithInAlloca(FI);
1886}
1887
1888void
1889X86_32ABIInfo::addFieldToArgStruct(SmallVector<llvm::Type *, 6> &FrameFields,
1890 CharUnits &StackOffset, ABIArgInfo &Info,
1891 QualType Type) const {
1892 // Arguments are always 4-byte-aligned.
1893 CharUnits FieldAlign = CharUnits::fromQuantity(4);
1894
1895 assert(StackOffset.isMultipleOf(FieldAlign) && "unaligned inalloca struct");
1896 Info = ABIArgInfo::getInAlloca(FrameFields.size());
1897 FrameFields.push_back(CGT.ConvertTypeForMem(Type));
1898 StackOffset += getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(Type);
1899
1900 // Insert padding bytes to respect alignment.
1901 CharUnits FieldEnd = StackOffset;
1902 StackOffset = FieldEnd.alignTo(FieldAlign);
1903 if (StackOffset != FieldEnd) {
1904 CharUnits NumBytes = StackOffset - FieldEnd;
1905 llvm::Type *Ty = llvm::Type::getInt8Ty(getVMContext());
1906 Ty = llvm::ArrayType::get(Ty, NumBytes.getQuantity());
1907 FrameFields.push_back(Ty);
1908 }
1909}
1910
1911static bool isArgInAlloca(const ABIArgInfo &Info) {
1912 // Leave ignored and inreg arguments alone.
1913 switch (Info.getKind()) {
1914 case ABIArgInfo::InAlloca:
1915 return true;
1916 case ABIArgInfo::Indirect:
1917 assert(Info.getIndirectByVal());
1918 return true;
1919 case ABIArgInfo::Ignore:
1920 return false;
1921 case ABIArgInfo::Direct:
1922 case ABIArgInfo::Extend:
1923 if (Info.getInReg())
1924 return false;
1925 return true;
1926 case ABIArgInfo::Expand:
1927 case ABIArgInfo::CoerceAndExpand:
1928 // These are aggregate types which are never passed in registers when
1929 // inalloca is involved.
1930 return true;
1931 }
1932 llvm_unreachable("invalid enum");
1933}
1934
1935void X86_32ABIInfo::rewriteWithInAlloca(CGFunctionInfo &FI) const {
1936 assert(IsWin32StructABI && "inalloca only supported on win32");
1937
1938 // Build a packed struct type for all of the arguments in memory.
1939 SmallVector<llvm::Type *, 6> FrameFields;
1940
1941 // The stack alignment is always 4.
1942 CharUnits StackAlign = CharUnits::fromQuantity(4);
1943
1944 CharUnits StackOffset;
1945 CGFunctionInfo::arg_iterator I = FI.arg_begin(), E = FI.arg_end();
1946
1947 // Put 'this' into the struct before 'sret', if necessary.
1948 bool IsThisCall =
1949 FI.getCallingConvention() == llvm::CallingConv::X86_ThisCall;
1950 ABIArgInfo &Ret = FI.getReturnInfo();
1951 if (Ret.isIndirect() && Ret.isSRetAfterThis() && !IsThisCall &&
1952 isArgInAlloca(I->info)) {
1953 addFieldToArgStruct(FrameFields, StackOffset, I->info, I->type);
1954 ++I;
1955 }
1956
1957 // Put the sret parameter into the inalloca struct if it's in memory.
1958 if (Ret.isIndirect() && !Ret.getInReg()) {
1959 CanQualType PtrTy = getContext().getPointerType(FI.getReturnType());
1960 addFieldToArgStruct(FrameFields, StackOffset, Ret, PtrTy);
1961 // On Windows, the hidden sret parameter is always returned in eax.
1962 Ret.setInAllocaSRet(IsWin32StructABI);
1963 }
1964
1965 // Skip the 'this' parameter in ecx.
1966 if (IsThisCall)
1967 ++I;
1968
1969 // Put arguments passed in memory into the struct.
1970 for (; I != E; ++I) {
1971 if (isArgInAlloca(I->info))
1972 addFieldToArgStruct(FrameFields, StackOffset, I->info, I->type);
1973 }
1974
1975 FI.setArgStruct(llvm::StructType::get(getVMContext(), FrameFields,
1976 /*isPacked=*/true),
1977 StackAlign);
1978}
1979
1980Address X86_32ABIInfo::EmitVAArg(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
1981 Address VAListAddr, QualType Ty) const {
1982
1983 auto TypeInfo = getContext().getTypeInfoInChars(Ty);
1984
1985 // x86-32 changes the alignment of certain arguments on the stack.
1986 //
1987 // Just messing with TypeInfo like this works because we never pass
1988 // anything indirectly.
1989 TypeInfo.second = CharUnits::fromQuantity(
1990 getTypeStackAlignInBytes(Ty, TypeInfo.second.getQuantity()));
1991
1992 return emitVoidPtrVAArg(CGF, VAListAddr, Ty, /*Indirect*/ false,
1993 TypeInfo, CharUnits::fromQuantity(4),
1994 /*AllowHigherAlign*/ true);
1995}
1996
1997bool X86_32TargetCodeGenInfo::isStructReturnInRegABI(
1998 const llvm::Triple &Triple, const CodeGenOptions &Opts) {
1999 assert(Triple.getArch() == llvm::Triple::x86);
2000
2001 switch (Opts.getStructReturnConvention()) {
2002 case CodeGenOptions::SRCK_Default:
2003 break;
2004 case CodeGenOptions::SRCK_OnStack: // -fpcc-struct-return
2005 return false;
2006 case CodeGenOptions::SRCK_InRegs: // -freg-struct-return
2007 return true;
2008 }
2009
2010 if (Triple.isOSDarwin() || Triple.isOSIAMCU())
2011 return true;
2012
2013 switch (Triple.getOS()) {
2014 case llvm::Triple::DragonFly:
2015 case llvm::Triple::FreeBSD:
2016 case llvm::Triple::OpenBSD:
2017 case llvm::Triple::Win32:
2018 return true;
2019 default:
2020 return false;
2021 }
2022}
2023
2024void X86_32TargetCodeGenInfo::setTargetAttributes(
2025 const Decl *D, llvm::GlobalValue *GV, CodeGen::CodeGenModule &CGM) const {
2026 if (GV->isDeclaration())
2027 return;
2028 if (const FunctionDecl *FD = dyn_cast_or_null<FunctionDecl>(D)) {
2029 if (FD->hasAttr<X86ForceAlignArgPointerAttr>()) {
2030 llvm::Function *Fn = cast<llvm::Function>(GV);
2031 Fn->addFnAttr("stackrealign");
2032 }
2033 if (FD->hasAttr<AnyX86InterruptAttr>()) {
2034 llvm::Function *Fn = cast<llvm::Function>(GV);
2035 Fn->setCallingConv(llvm::CallingConv::X86_INTR);
2036 }
2037 }
2038}
2039
2040bool X86_32TargetCodeGenInfo::initDwarfEHRegSizeTable(
2041 CodeGen::CodeGenFunction &CGF,
2042 llvm::Value *Address) const {
2043 CodeGen::CGBuilderTy &Builder = CGF.Builder;
2044
2045 llvm::Value *Four8 = llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.Int8Ty, 4);
2046
2047 // 0-7 are the eight integer registers; the order is different
2048 // on Darwin (for EH), but the range is the same.
2049 // 8 is %eip.
2050 AssignToArrayRange(Builder, Address, Four8, 0, 8);
2051
2052 if (CGF.CGM.getTarget().getTriple().isOSDarwin()) {
2053 // 12-16 are st(0..4). Not sure why we stop at 4.
2054 // These have size 16, which is sizeof(long double) on
2055 // platforms with 8-byte alignment for that type.
2056 llvm::Value *Sixteen8 = llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.Int8Ty, 16);
2057 AssignToArrayRange(Builder, Address, Sixteen8, 12, 16);
2058
2059 } else {
2060 // 9 is %eflags, which doesn't get a size on Darwin for some
2061 // reason.
2062 Builder.CreateAlignedStore(
2063 Four8, Builder.CreateConstInBoundsGEP1_32(CGF.Int8Ty, Address, 9),
2064 CharUnits::One());
2065
2066 // 11-16 are st(0..5). Not sure why we stop at 5.
2067 // These have size 12, which is sizeof(long double) on
2068 // platforms with 4-byte alignment for that type.
2069 llvm::Value *Twelve8 = llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.Int8Ty, 12);
2070 AssignToArrayRange(Builder, Address, Twelve8, 11, 16);
2071 }
2072
2073 return false;
2074}

2081namespace {
2082/// The AVX ABI level for X86 targets.
2083enum class X86AVXABILevel {
2084 None,
2085 AVX,
2086 AVX512
2087};
2088
2089/// \p returns the size in bits of the largest (native) vector for \p AVXLevel.
2090static unsigned getNativeVectorSizeForAVXABI(X86AVXABILevel AVXLevel) {
2091 switch (AVXLevel) {
2092 case X86AVXABILevel::AVX512:
2093 return 512;
2094 case X86AVXABILevel::AVX:
2095 return 256;
2096 case X86AVXABILevel::None:
2097 return 128;
2098 }
2099 llvm_unreachable("Unknown AVXLevel");
2100}
