4120// PowerPC-32
4121namespace {
4122/// PPC32_SVR4_ABIInfo - The 32-bit PowerPC ELF (SVR4) ABI information.
4123class PPC32_SVR4_ABIInfo : public DefaultABIInfo {
4124 bool IsSoftFloatABI;
4125
4126 CharUnits getParamTypeAlignment(QualType Ty) const;
4127
4128public:
4129 PPC32_SVR4_ABIInfo(CodeGen::CodeGenTypes &CGT, bool SoftFloatABI)
4130 : DefaultABIInfo(CGT), IsSoftFloatABI(SoftFloatABI) {}
4131
4132 Address EmitVAArg(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Address VAListAddr,
4133 QualType Ty) const override;
4134};
4135
4136class PPC32TargetCodeGenInfo : public TargetCodeGenInfo {
4137public:
4138 PPC32TargetCodeGenInfo(CodeGenTypes &CGT, bool SoftFloatABI)
4139 : TargetCodeGenInfo(new PPC32_SVR4_ABIInfo(CGT, SoftFloatABI)) {}
4140
4141 int getDwarfEHStackPointer(CodeGen::CodeGenModule &M) const override {
4142 // This is recovered from gcc output.
4143 return 1; // r1 is the dedicated stack pointer
4144 }
4145
4146 bool initDwarfEHRegSizeTable(CodeGen::CodeGenFunction &CGF,
4147 llvm::Value *Address) const override;
4148};
4149}
4150
4151CharUnits PPC32_SVR4_ABIInfo::getParamTypeAlignment(QualType Ty) const {
4152 // Complex types are passed just like their elements
4153 if (const ComplexType *CTy = Ty->getAs<ComplexType>())
4154 Ty = CTy->getElementType();
4155
4156 if (Ty->isVectorType())
4157 return CharUnits::fromQuantity(getContext().getTypeSize(Ty) == 128 ? 16
4158 : 4);
4159
4160 // For single-element float/vector structs, we consider the whole type
4161 // to have the same alignment requirements as its single element.
4162 const Type *AlignTy = nullptr;
4163 if (const Type *EltType = isSingleElementStruct(Ty, getContext())) {
4164 const BuiltinType *BT = EltType->getAs<BuiltinType>();
4165 if ((EltType->isVectorType() && getContext().getTypeSize(EltType) == 128) ||
4166 (BT && BT->isFloatingPoint()))
4167 AlignTy = EltType;
4168 }
4169
4170 if (AlignTy)
4171 return CharUnits::fromQuantity(AlignTy->isVectorType() ? 16 : 4);
4172 return CharUnits::fromQuantity(4);
4173}
4174
4175// TODO: this implementation is now likely redundant with
4176// DefaultABIInfo::EmitVAArg.
4177Address PPC32_SVR4_ABIInfo::EmitVAArg(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Address VAList,
4178 QualType Ty) const {
4179 if (getTarget().getTriple().isOSDarwin()) {
4180 auto TI = getContext().getTypeInfoInChars(Ty);
4181 TI.second = getParamTypeAlignment(Ty);
4182
4183 CharUnits SlotSize = CharUnits::fromQuantity(4);
4184 return emitVoidPtrVAArg(CGF, VAList, Ty,
4185 classifyArgumentType(Ty).isIndirect(), TI, SlotSize,
4186 /*AllowHigherAlign=*/true);
4187 }
4188
4189 const unsigned OverflowLimit = 8;
4190 if (const ComplexType *CTy = Ty->getAs<ComplexType>()) {
4191 // TODO: Implement this. For now ignore.
4192 (void)CTy;
4193 return Address::invalid(); // FIXME?
4194 }
4195
4196 // struct __va_list_tag {
4197 // unsigned char gpr;
4198 // unsigned char fpr;
4199 // unsigned short reserved;
4200 // void *overflow_arg_area;
4201 // void *reg_save_area;
4202 // };
4203
4204 bool isI64 = Ty->isIntegerType() && getContext().getTypeSize(Ty) == 64;
4205 bool isInt =
4206 Ty->isIntegerType() || Ty->isPointerType() || Ty->isAggregateType();
4207 bool isF64 = Ty->isFloatingType() && getContext().getTypeSize(Ty) == 64;
4208
4209 // All aggregates are passed indirectly? That doesn't seem consistent
4210 // with the argument-lowering code.
4211 bool isIndirect = Ty->isAggregateType();
4212
4213 CGBuilderTy &Builder = CGF.Builder;
4214
4215 // The calling convention either uses 1-2 GPRs or 1 FPR.
4216 Address NumRegsAddr = Address::invalid();
4217 if (isInt || IsSoftFloatABI) {
4218 NumRegsAddr = Builder.CreateStructGEP(VAList, 0, "gpr");
4219 } else {
4220 NumRegsAddr = Builder.CreateStructGEP(VAList, 1, "fpr");
4221 }
4222
4223 llvm::Value *NumRegs = Builder.CreateLoad(NumRegsAddr, "numUsedRegs");
4224
4225 // "Align" the register count when TY is i64.
4226 if (isI64 || (isF64 && IsSoftFloatABI)) {
4227 NumRegs = Builder.CreateAdd(NumRegs, Builder.getInt8(1));
4228 NumRegs = Builder.CreateAnd(NumRegs, Builder.getInt8((uint8_t) ~1U));
4229 }
4230
4231 llvm::Value *CC =
4232 Builder.CreateICmpULT(NumRegs, Builder.getInt8(OverflowLimit), "cond");
4233
4234 llvm::BasicBlock *UsingRegs = CGF.createBasicBlock("using_regs");
4235 llvm::BasicBlock *UsingOverflow = CGF.createBasicBlock("using_overflow");
4236 llvm::BasicBlock *Cont = CGF.createBasicBlock("cont");
4237
4238 Builder.CreateCondBr(CC, UsingRegs, UsingOverflow);
4239
4240 llvm::Type *DirectTy = CGF.ConvertType(Ty);
4241 if (isIndirect) DirectTy = DirectTy->getPointerTo(0);
4242
4243 // Case 1: consume registers.
4244 Address RegAddr = Address::invalid();
4245 {
4246 CGF.EmitBlock(UsingRegs);
4247
4248 Address RegSaveAreaPtr = Builder.CreateStructGEP(VAList, 4);
4249 RegAddr = Address(Builder.CreateLoad(RegSaveAreaPtr),
4250 CharUnits::fromQuantity(8));
4251 assert(RegAddr.getElementType() == CGF.Int8Ty);
4252
4253 // Floating-point registers start after the general-purpose registers.
4254 if (!(isInt || IsSoftFloatABI)) {
4255 RegAddr = Builder.CreateConstInBoundsByteGEP(RegAddr,
4256 CharUnits::fromQuantity(32));
4257 }
4258
4259 // Get the address of the saved value by scaling the number of
4260 // registers we've used by the number of
4261 CharUnits RegSize = CharUnits::fromQuantity((isInt || IsSoftFloatABI) ? 4 : 8);
4262 llvm::Value *RegOffset =
4263 Builder.CreateMul(NumRegs, Builder.getInt8(RegSize.getQuantity()));
4264 RegAddr = Address(Builder.CreateInBoundsGEP(CGF.Int8Ty,
4265 RegAddr.getPointer(), RegOffset),
4266 RegAddr.getAlignment().alignmentOfArrayElement(RegSize));
4267 RegAddr = Builder.CreateElementBitCast(RegAddr, DirectTy);
4268
4269 // Increase the used-register count.
4270 NumRegs =
4271 Builder.CreateAdd(NumRegs,
4272 Builder.getInt8((isI64 || (isF64 && IsSoftFloatABI)) ? 2 : 1));
4273 Builder.CreateStore(NumRegs, NumRegsAddr);
4274
4275 CGF.EmitBranch(Cont);
4276 }
4277
4278 // Case 2: consume space in the overflow area.
4279 Address MemAddr = Address::invalid();
4280 {
4281 CGF.EmitBlock(UsingOverflow);
4282
4283 Builder.CreateStore(Builder.getInt8(OverflowLimit), NumRegsAddr);
4284
4285 // Everything in the overflow area is rounded up to a size of at least 4.
4286 CharUnits OverflowAreaAlign = CharUnits::fromQuantity(4);
4287
4288 CharUnits Size;
4289 if (!isIndirect) {
4290 auto TypeInfo = CGF.getContext().getTypeInfoInChars(Ty);
4291 Size = TypeInfo.first.alignTo(OverflowAreaAlign);
4292 } else {
4293 Size = CGF.getPointerSize();
4294 }
4295
4296 Address OverflowAreaAddr = Builder.CreateStructGEP(VAList, 3);
4297 Address OverflowArea(Builder.CreateLoad(OverflowAreaAddr, "argp.cur"),
4298 OverflowAreaAlign);
4299 // Round up address of argument to alignment
4300 CharUnits Align = CGF.getContext().getTypeAlignInChars(Ty);
4301 if (Align > OverflowAreaAlign) {
4302 llvm::Value *Ptr = OverflowArea.getPointer();
4303 OverflowArea = Address(emitRoundPointerUpToAlignment(CGF, Ptr, Align),
4304 Align);
4305 }
4306
4307 MemAddr = Builder.CreateElementBitCast(OverflowArea, DirectTy);
4308
4309 // Increase the overflow area.
4310 OverflowArea = Builder.CreateConstInBoundsByteGEP(OverflowArea, Size);
4311 Builder.CreateStore(OverflowArea.getPointer(), OverflowAreaAddr);
4312 CGF.EmitBranch(Cont);
4313 }
4314
4315 CGF.EmitBlock(Cont);
4316
4317 // Merge the cases with a phi.
4318 Address Result = emitMergePHI(CGF, RegAddr, UsingRegs, MemAddr, UsingOverflow,
4319 "vaarg.addr");
4320
4321 // Load the pointer if the argument was passed indirectly.
4322 if (isIndirect) {
4323 Result = Address(Builder.CreateLoad(Result, "aggr"),
4324 getContext().getTypeAlignInChars(Ty));
4325 }
4326
4327 return Result;
4328}
4329
4330bool
4331PPC32TargetCodeGenInfo::initDwarfEHRegSizeTable(CodeGen::CodeGenFunction &CGF,
4332 llvm::Value *Address) const {
4333 // This is calculated from the LLVM and GCC tables and verified
4334 // against gcc output. AFAIK all ABIs use the same encoding.
4335
4336 CodeGen::CGBuilderTy &Builder = CGF.Builder;
4337
4338 llvm::IntegerType *i8 = CGF.Int8Ty;
4339 llvm::Value *Four8 = llvm::ConstantInt::get(i8, 4);
4340 llvm::Value *Eight8 = llvm::ConstantInt::get(i8, 8);
4341 llvm::Value *Sixteen8 = llvm::ConstantInt::get(i8, 16);
4342
4343 // 0-31: r0-31, the 4-byte general-purpose registers
4344 AssignToArrayRange(Builder, Address, Four8, 0, 31);
4345
4346 // 32-63: fp0-31, the 8-byte floating-point registers
4347 AssignToArrayRange(Builder, Address, Eight8, 32, 63);
4348
4349 // 64-76 are various 4-byte special-purpose registers:
4350 // 64: mq
4351 // 65: lr
4352 // 66: ctr
4353 // 67: ap
4354 // 68-75 cr0-7
4355 // 76: xer
4356 AssignToArrayRange(Builder, Address, Four8, 64, 76);
4357
4358 // 77-108: v0-31, the 16-byte vector registers
4359 AssignToArrayRange(Builder, Address, Sixteen8, 77, 108);
4360
4361 // 109: vrsave
4362 // 110: vscr
4363 // 111: spe_acc
4364 // 112: spefscr
4365 // 113: sfp
4366 AssignToArrayRange(Builder, Address, Four8, 109, 113);
4367
4368 return false;
4369}
4370
4371// PowerPC-64
4372
4373namespace {
4374/// PPC64_SVR4_ABIInfo - The 64-bit PowerPC ELF (SVR4) ABI information.
4375class PPC64_SVR4_ABIInfo : public SwiftABIInfo {
4376public:
4377 enum ABIKind {
4378 ELFv1 = 0,
4379 ELFv2
4380 };
4381
4382private:
4383 static const unsigned GPRBits = 64;
4384 ABIKind Kind;
4385 bool HasQPX;
4386 bool IsSoftFloatABI;
4387
4388 // A vector of float or double will be promoted to <4 x f32> or <4 x f64> and
4389 // will be passed in a QPX register.
4390 bool IsQPXVectorTy(const Type *Ty) const {
4391 if (!HasQPX)
4392 return false;
4393
4394 if (const VectorType *VT = Ty->getAs<VectorType>()) {
4395 unsigned NumElements = VT->getNumElements();
4396 if (NumElements == 1)
4397 return false;
4398
4399 if (VT->getElementType()->isSpecificBuiltinType(BuiltinType::Double)) {
4400 if (getContext().getTypeSize(Ty) <= 256)
4401 return true;
4402 } else if (VT->getElementType()->
4403 isSpecificBuiltinType(BuiltinType::Float)) {
4404 if (getContext().getTypeSize(Ty) <= 128)
4405 return true;
4406 }
4407 }
4408
4409 return false;
4410 }
4411
4412 bool IsQPXVectorTy(QualType Ty) const {
4413 return IsQPXVectorTy(Ty.getTypePtr());
4414 }
4415
4416public:
4417 PPC64_SVR4_ABIInfo(CodeGen::CodeGenTypes &CGT, ABIKind Kind, bool HasQPX,
4418 bool SoftFloatABI)
4419 : SwiftABIInfo(CGT), Kind(Kind), HasQPX(HasQPX),
4420 IsSoftFloatABI(SoftFloatABI) {}
4421
4422 bool isPromotableTypeForABI(QualType Ty) const;
4423 CharUnits getParamTypeAlignment(QualType Ty) const;
4424
4425 ABIArgInfo classifyReturnType(QualType RetTy) const;
4426 ABIArgInfo classifyArgumentType(QualType Ty) const;
4427
4428 bool isHomogeneousAggregateBaseType(QualType Ty) const override;
4429 bool isHomogeneousAggregateSmallEnough(const Type *Ty,
4430 uint64_t Members) const override;
4431
4432 // TODO: We can add more logic to computeInfo to improve performance.
4433 // Example: For aggregate arguments that fit in a register, we could
4434 // use getDirectInReg (as is done below for structs containing a single
4435 // floating-point value) to avoid pushing them to memory on function
4436 // entry. This would require changing the logic in PPCISelLowering
4437 // when lowering the parameters in the caller and args in the callee.
4438 void computeInfo(CGFunctionInfo &FI) const override {
4439 if (!getCXXABI().classifyReturnType(FI))
4440 FI.getReturnInfo() = classifyReturnType(FI.getReturnType());
4441 for (auto &I : FI.arguments()) {
4442 // We rely on the default argument classification for the most part.
4443 // One exception: An aggregate containing a single floating-point
4444 // or vector item must be passed in a register if one is available.
4445 const Type *T = isSingleElementStruct(I.type, getContext());
4446 if (T) {
4447 const BuiltinType *BT = T->getAs<BuiltinType>();
4448 if (IsQPXVectorTy(T) ||
4449 (T->isVectorType() && getContext().getTypeSize(T) == 128) ||
4450 (BT && BT->isFloatingPoint())) {
4451 QualType QT(T, 0);
4452 I.info = ABIArgInfo::getDirectInReg(CGT.ConvertType(QT));
4453 continue;
4454 }
4455 }
4456 I.info = classifyArgumentType(I.type);
4457 }
4458 }
4459
4460 Address EmitVAArg(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Address VAListAddr,
4461 QualType Ty) const override;
4462
4463 bool shouldPassIndirectlyForSwift(ArrayRef<llvm::Type*> scalars,
4464 bool asReturnValue) const override {
4465 return occupiesMoreThan(CGT, scalars, /*total*/ 4);
4466 }
4467
4468 bool isSwiftErrorInRegister() const override {
4469 return false;
4470 }
4471};
4472
4473class PPC64_SVR4_TargetCodeGenInfo : public TargetCodeGenInfo {
4474
4475public:
4476 PPC64_SVR4_TargetCodeGenInfo(CodeGenTypes &CGT,
4477 PPC64_SVR4_ABIInfo::ABIKind Kind, bool HasQPX,
4478 bool SoftFloatABI)
4479 : TargetCodeGenInfo(new PPC64_SVR4_ABIInfo(CGT, Kind, HasQPX,
4480 SoftFloatABI)) {}
4481
4482 int getDwarfEHStackPointer(CodeGen::CodeGenModule &M) const override {
4483 // This is recovered from gcc output.
4484 return 1; // r1 is the dedicated stack pointer
4485 }
4486
4487 bool initDwarfEHRegSizeTable(CodeGen::CodeGenFunction &CGF,
4488 llvm::Value *Address) const override;
4489};
4490
4491class PPC64TargetCodeGenInfo : public DefaultTargetCodeGenInfo {
4492public:
4493 PPC64TargetCodeGenInfo(CodeGenTypes &CGT) : DefaultTargetCodeGenInfo(CGT) {}
4494
4495 int getDwarfEHStackPointer(CodeGen::CodeGenModule &M) const override {
4496 // This is recovered from gcc output.
4497 return 1; // r1 is the dedicated stack pointer
4498 }
4499
4500 bool initDwarfEHRegSizeTable(CodeGen::CodeGenFunction &CGF,
4501 llvm::Value *Address) const override;
4502};
4503
4504}
4505
4506// Return true if the ABI requires Ty to be passed sign- or zero-
4507// extended to 64 bits.
4508bool
4509PPC64_SVR4_ABIInfo::isPromotableTypeForABI(QualType Ty) const {
4510 // Treat an enum type as its underlying type.
4511 if (const EnumType *EnumTy = Ty->getAs<EnumType>())
4512 Ty = EnumTy->getDecl()->getIntegerType();
4513
4514 // Promotable integer types are required to be promoted by the ABI.
4515 if (Ty->isPromotableIntegerType())
4516 return true;
4517
4518 // In addition to the usual promotable integer types, we also need to
4519 // extend all 32-bit types, since the ABI requires promotion to 64 bits.
4520 if (const BuiltinType *BT = Ty->getAs<BuiltinType>())
4521 switch (BT->getKind()) {
4522 case BuiltinType::Int:
4523 case BuiltinType::UInt:
4524 return true;
4525 default:
4526 break;
4527 }
4528
4529 return false;
4530}
4531
4532/// isAlignedParamType - Determine whether a type requires 16-byte or
4533/// higher alignment in the parameter area. Always returns at least 8.
4534CharUnits PPC64_SVR4_ABIInfo::getParamTypeAlignment(QualType Ty) const {
4535 // Complex types are passed just like their elements.
4536 if (const ComplexType *CTy = Ty->getAs<ComplexType>())
4537 Ty = CTy->getElementType();
4538
4539 // Only vector types of size 16 bytes need alignment (larger types are
4540 // passed via reference, smaller types are not aligned).
4541 if (IsQPXVectorTy(Ty)) {
4542 if (getContext().getTypeSize(Ty) > 128)
4543 return CharUnits::fromQuantity(32);
4544
4545 return CharUnits::fromQuantity(16);
4546 } else if (Ty->isVectorType()) {
4547 return CharUnits::fromQuantity(getContext().getTypeSize(Ty) == 128 ? 16 : 8);
4548 }
4549
4550 // For single-element float/vector structs, we consider the whole type
4551 // to have the same alignment requirements as its single element.
4552 const Type *AlignAsType = nullptr;
4553 const Type *EltType = isSingleElementStruct(Ty, getContext());
4554 if (EltType) {
4555 const BuiltinType *BT = EltType->getAs<BuiltinType>();
4556 if (IsQPXVectorTy(EltType) || (EltType->isVectorType() &&
4557 getContext().getTypeSize(EltType) == 128) ||
4558 (BT && BT->isFloatingPoint()))
4559 AlignAsType = EltType;
4560 }
4561
4562 // Likewise for ELFv2 homogeneous aggregates.
4563 const Type *Base = nullptr;
4564 uint64_t Members = 0;
4565 if (!AlignAsType && Kind == ELFv2 &&
4566 isAggregateTypeForABI(Ty) && isHomogeneousAggregate(Ty, Base, Members))
4567 AlignAsType = Base;
4568
4569 // With special case aggregates, only vector base types need alignment.
4570 if (AlignAsType && IsQPXVectorTy(AlignAsType)) {
4571 if (getContext().getTypeSize(AlignAsType) > 128)
4572 return CharUnits::fromQuantity(32);
4573
4574 return CharUnits::fromQuantity(16);
4575 } else if (AlignAsType) {
4576 return CharUnits::fromQuantity(AlignAsType->isVectorType() ? 16 : 8);
4577 }
4578
4579 // Otherwise, we only need alignment for any aggregate type that
4580 // has an alignment requirement of >= 16 bytes.
4581 if (isAggregateTypeForABI(Ty) && getContext().getTypeAlign(Ty) >= 128) {
4582 if (HasQPX && getContext().getTypeAlign(Ty) >= 256)
4583 return CharUnits::fromQuantity(32);
4584 return CharUnits::fromQuantity(16);
4585 }
4586
4587 return CharUnits::fromQuantity(8);
4588}
4589
4590/// isHomogeneousAggregate - Return true if a type is an ELFv2 homogeneous
4591/// aggregate. Base is set to the base element type, and Members is set
4592/// to the number of base elements.
4593bool ABIInfo::isHomogeneousAggregate(QualType Ty, const Type *&Base,
4594 uint64_t &Members) const {
4595 if (const ConstantArrayType *AT = getContext().getAsConstantArrayType(Ty)) {
4596 uint64_t NElements = AT->getSize().getZExtValue();
4597 if (NElements == 0)
4598 return false;
4599 if (!isHomogeneousAggregate(AT->getElementType(), Base, Members))
4600 return false;
4601 Members *= NElements;
4602 } else if (const RecordType *RT = Ty->getAs<RecordType>()) {
4603 const RecordDecl *RD = RT->getDecl();
4604 if (RD->hasFlexibleArrayMember())
4605 return false;
4606
4607 Members = 0;
4608
4609 // If this is a C++ record, check the bases first.
4610 if (const CXXRecordDecl *CXXRD = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RD)) {
4611 for (const auto &I : CXXRD->bases()) {
4612 // Ignore empty records.
4613 if (isEmptyRecord(getContext(), I.getType(), true))
4614 continue;
4615
4616 uint64_t FldMembers;
4617 if (!isHomogeneousAggregate(I.getType(), Base, FldMembers))
4618 return false;
4619
4620 Members += FldMembers;
4621 }
4622 }
4623
4624 for (const auto *FD : RD->fields()) {
4625 // Ignore (non-zero arrays of) empty records.
4626 QualType FT = FD->getType();
4627 while (const ConstantArrayType *AT =
4628 getContext().getAsConstantArrayType(FT)) {
4629 if (AT->getSize().getZExtValue() == 0)
4630 return false;
4631 FT = AT->getElementType();
4632 }
4633 if (isEmptyRecord(getContext(), FT, true))
4634 continue;
4635
4636 // For compatibility with GCC, ignore empty bitfields in C++ mode.
4637 if (getContext().getLangOpts().CPlusPlus &&
4638 FD->isZeroLengthBitField(getContext()))
4639 continue;
4640
4641 uint64_t FldMembers;
4642 if (!isHomogeneousAggregate(FD->getType(), Base, FldMembers))
4643 return false;
4644
4645 Members = (RD->isUnion() ?
4646 std::max(Members, FldMembers) : Members + FldMembers);
4647 }
4648
4649 if (!Base)
4650 return false;
4651
4652 // Ensure there is no padding.
4653 if (getContext().getTypeSize(Base) * Members !=
4654 getContext().getTypeSize(Ty))
4655 return false;
4656 } else {
4657 Members = 1;
4658 if (const ComplexType *CT = Ty->getAs<ComplexType>()) {
4659 Members = 2;
4660 Ty = CT->getElementType();
4661 }
4662
4663 // Most ABIs only support float, double, and some vector type widths.
4664 if (!isHomogeneousAggregateBaseType(Ty))
4665 return false;
4666
4667 // The base type must be the same for all members. Types that
4668 // agree in both total size and mode (float vs. vector) are
4669 // treated as being equivalent here.
4670 const Type *TyPtr = Ty.getTypePtr();
4671 if (!Base) {
4672 Base = TyPtr;
4673 // If it's a non-power-of-2 vector, its size is already a power-of-2,
4674 // so make sure to widen it explicitly.
4675 if (const VectorType *VT = Base->getAs<VectorType>()) {
4676 QualType EltTy = VT->getElementType();
4677 unsigned NumElements =
4678 getContext().getTypeSize(VT) / getContext().getTypeSize(EltTy);
4679 Base = getContext()
4680 .getVectorType(EltTy, NumElements, VT->getVectorKind())
4681 .getTypePtr();
4682 }
4683 }
4684
4685 if (Base->isVectorType() != TyPtr->isVectorType() ||
4686 getContext().getTypeSize(Base) != getContext().getTypeSize(TyPtr))
4687 return false;
4688 }
4689 return Members > 0 && isHomogeneousAggregateSmallEnough(Base, Members);
4690}
4691
4692bool PPC64_SVR4_ABIInfo::isHomogeneousAggregateBaseType(QualType Ty) const {
4693 // Homogeneous aggregates for ELFv2 must have base types of float,
4694 // double, long double, or 128-bit vectors.
4695 if (const BuiltinType *BT = Ty->getAs<BuiltinType>()) {
4696 if (BT->getKind() == BuiltinType::Float ||
4697 BT->getKind() == BuiltinType::Double ||
4698 BT->getKind() == BuiltinType::LongDouble ||
4699 (getContext().getTargetInfo().hasFloat128Type() &&
4700 (BT->getKind() == BuiltinType::Float128))) {
4701 if (IsSoftFloatABI)
4702 return false;
4703 return true;
4704 }
4705 }
4706 if (const VectorType *VT = Ty->getAs<VectorType>()) {
4707 if (getContext().getTypeSize(VT) == 128 || IsQPXVectorTy(Ty))
4708 return true;
4709 }
4710 return false;
4711}
4712
4713bool PPC64_SVR4_ABIInfo::isHomogeneousAggregateSmallEnough(
4714 const Type *Base, uint64_t Members) const {
4715 // Vector and fp128 types require one register, other floating point types
4716 // require one or two registers depending on their size.
4717 uint32_t NumRegs =
4718 ((getContext().getTargetInfo().hasFloat128Type() &&
4719 Base->isFloat128Type()) ||
4720 Base->isVectorType()) ? 1
4721 : (getContext().getTypeSize(Base) + 63) / 64;
4722
4723 // Homogeneous Aggregates may occupy at most 8 registers.
4724 return Members * NumRegs <= 8;
4725}
4726
4727ABIArgInfo
4728PPC64_SVR4_ABIInfo::classifyArgumentType(QualType Ty) const {
4729 Ty = useFirstFieldIfTransparentUnion(Ty);
4730
4731 if (Ty->isAnyComplexType())
4732 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect();
4733
4734 // Non-Altivec vector types are passed in GPRs (smaller than 16 bytes)
4735 // or via reference (larger than 16 bytes).
4736 if (Ty->isVectorType() && !IsQPXVectorTy(Ty)) {
4737 uint64_t Size = getContext().getTypeSize(Ty);
4738 if (Size > 128)
4739 return getNaturalAlignIndirect(Ty, /*ByVal=*/false);
4740 else if (Size < 128) {
4741 llvm::Type *CoerceTy = llvm::IntegerType::get(getVMContext(), Size);
4742 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(CoerceTy);
4743 }
4744 }
4745
4746 if (isAggregateTypeForABI(Ty)) {
4747 if (CGCXXABI::RecordArgABI RAA = getRecordArgABI(Ty, getCXXABI()))
4748 return getNaturalAlignIndirect(Ty, RAA == CGCXXABI::RAA_DirectInMemory);
4749
4750 uint64_t ABIAlign = getParamTypeAlignment(Ty).getQuantity();
4751 uint64_t TyAlign = getContext().getTypeAlignInChars(Ty).getQuantity();
4752
4753 // ELFv2 homogeneous aggregates are passed as array types.
4754 const Type *Base = nullptr;
4755 uint64_t Members = 0;
4756 if (Kind == ELFv2 &&
4757 isHomogeneousAggregate(Ty, Base, Members)) {
4758 llvm::Type *BaseTy = CGT.ConvertType(QualType(Base, 0));
4759 llvm::Type *CoerceTy = llvm::ArrayType::get(BaseTy, Members);
4760 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(CoerceTy);
4761 }
4762
4763 // If an aggregate may end up fully in registers, we do not
4764 // use the ByVal method, but pass the aggregate as array.
4765 // This is usually beneficial since we avoid forcing the
4766 // back-end to store the argument to memory.
4767 uint64_t Bits = getContext().getTypeSize(Ty);
4768 if (Bits > 0 && Bits <= 8 * GPRBits) {
4769 llvm::Type *CoerceTy;
4770
4771 // Types up to 8 bytes are passed as integer type (which will be
4772 // properly aligned in the argument save area doubleword).
4773 if (Bits <= GPRBits)
4774 CoerceTy =
4775 llvm::IntegerType::get(getVMContext(), llvm::alignTo(Bits, 8));
4776 // Larger types are passed as arrays, with the base type selected
4777 // according to the required alignment in the save area.
4778 else {
4779 uint64_t RegBits = ABIAlign * 8;
4780 uint64_t NumRegs = llvm::alignTo(Bits, RegBits) / RegBits;
4781 llvm::Type *RegTy = llvm::IntegerType::get(getVMContext(), RegBits);
4782 CoerceTy = llvm::ArrayType::get(RegTy, NumRegs);
4783 }
4784
4785 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(CoerceTy);
4786 }
4787
4788 // All other aggregates are passed ByVal.
4789 return ABIArgInfo::getIndirect(CharUnits::fromQuantity(ABIAlign),
4790 /*ByVal=*/true,
4791 /*Realign=*/TyAlign > ABIAlign);
4792 }
4793
4794 return (isPromotableTypeForABI(Ty) ? ABIArgInfo::getExtend(Ty)
4795 : ABIArgInfo::getDirect());
4796}
4797
4798ABIArgInfo
4799PPC64_SVR4_ABIInfo::classifyReturnType(QualType RetTy) const {
4800 if (RetTy->isVoidType())
4801 return ABIArgInfo::getIgnore();
4802
4803 if (RetTy->isAnyComplexType())
4804 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect();
4805
4806 // Non-Altivec vector types are returned in GPRs (smaller than 16 bytes)
4807 // or via reference (larger than 16 bytes).
4808 if (RetTy->isVectorType() && !IsQPXVectorTy(RetTy)) {
4809 uint64_t Size = getContext().getTypeSize(RetTy);
4810 if (Size > 128)
4811 return getNaturalAlignIndirect(RetTy);
4812 else if (Size < 128) {
4813 llvm::Type *CoerceTy = llvm::IntegerType::get(getVMContext(), Size);
4814 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(CoerceTy);
4815 }
4816 }
4817
4818 if (isAggregateTypeForABI(RetTy)) {
4819 // ELFv2 homogeneous aggregates are returned as array types.
4820 const Type *Base = nullptr;
4821 uint64_t Members = 0;
4822 if (Kind == ELFv2 &&
4823 isHomogeneousAggregate(RetTy, Base, Members)) {
4824 llvm::Type *BaseTy = CGT.ConvertType(QualType(Base, 0));
4825 llvm::Type *CoerceTy = llvm::ArrayType::get(BaseTy, Members);
4826 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(CoerceTy);
4827 }
4828
4829 // ELFv2 small aggregates are returned in up to two registers.
4830 uint64_t Bits = getContext().getTypeSize(RetTy);
4831 if (Kind == ELFv2 && Bits <= 2 * GPRBits) {
4832 if (Bits == 0)
4833 return ABIArgInfo::getIgnore();
4834
4835 llvm::Type *CoerceTy;
4836 if (Bits > GPRBits) {
4837 CoerceTy = llvm::IntegerType::get(getVMContext(), GPRBits);
4838 CoerceTy = llvm::StructType::get(CoerceTy, CoerceTy);
4839 } else
4840 CoerceTy =
4841 llvm::IntegerType::get(getVMContext(), llvm::alignTo(Bits, 8));
4842 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(CoerceTy);
4843 }
4844
4845 // All other aggregates are returned indirectly.
4846 return getNaturalAlignIndirect(RetTy);
4847 }
4848
4849 return (isPromotableTypeForABI(RetTy) ? ABIArgInfo::getExtend(RetTy)
4850 : ABIArgInfo::getDirect());
4851}
4852
4853// Based on ARMABIInfo::EmitVAArg, adjusted for 64-bit machine.
4854Address PPC64_SVR4_ABIInfo::EmitVAArg(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Address VAListAddr,
4855 QualType Ty) const {
4856 auto TypeInfo = getContext().getTypeInfoInChars(Ty);
4857 TypeInfo.second = getParamTypeAlignment(Ty);
4858
4859 CharUnits SlotSize = CharUnits::fromQuantity(8);
4860
4861 // If we have a complex type and the base type is smaller than 8 bytes,
4862 // the ABI calls for the real and imaginary parts to be right-adjusted
4863 // in separate doublewords. However, Clang expects us to produce a
4864 // pointer to a structure with the two parts packed tightly. So generate
4865 // loads of the real and imaginary parts relative to the va_list pointer,
4866 // and store them to a temporary structure.
4867 if (const ComplexType *CTy = Ty->getAs<ComplexType>()) {
4868 CharUnits EltSize = TypeInfo.first / 2;
4869 if (EltSize < SlotSize) {
4870 Address Addr = emitVoidPtrDirectVAArg(CGF, VAListAddr, CGF.Int8Ty,
4871 SlotSize * 2, SlotSize,
4872 SlotSize, /*AllowHigher*/ true);
4873
4874 Address RealAddr = Addr;
4875 Address ImagAddr = RealAddr;
4876 if (CGF.CGM.getDataLayout().isBigEndian()) {
4877 RealAddr = CGF.Builder.CreateConstInBoundsByteGEP(RealAddr,
4878 SlotSize - EltSize);
4879 ImagAddr = CGF.Builder.CreateConstInBoundsByteGEP(ImagAddr,
4880 2 * SlotSize - EltSize);
4881 } else {
4882 ImagAddr = CGF.Builder.CreateConstInBoundsByteGEP(RealAddr, SlotSize);
4883 }
4884
4885 llvm::Type *EltTy = CGF.ConvertTypeForMem(CTy->getElementType());
4886 RealAddr = CGF.Builder.CreateElementBitCast(RealAddr, EltTy);
4887 ImagAddr = CGF.Builder.CreateElementBitCast(ImagAddr, EltTy);
4888 llvm::Value *Real = CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(RealAddr, ".vareal");
4889 llvm::Value *Imag = CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(ImagAddr, ".vaimag");
4890
4891 Address Temp = CGF.CreateMemTemp(Ty, "vacplx");
4892 CGF.EmitStoreOfComplex({Real, Imag}, CGF.MakeAddrLValue(Temp, Ty),
4893 /*init*/ true);
4894 return Temp;
4895 }
4896 }
4897
4898 // Otherwise, just use the general rule.
4899 return emitVoidPtrVAArg(CGF, VAListAddr, Ty, /*Indirect*/ false,
4900 TypeInfo, SlotSize, /*AllowHigher*/ true);
4901}
4902
4903static bool
4904PPC64_initDwarfEHRegSizeTable(CodeGen::CodeGenFunction &CGF,
4905 llvm::Value *Address) {
4906 // This is calculated from the LLVM and GCC tables and verified
4907 // against gcc output. AFAIK all ABIs use the same encoding.
4908
4909 CodeGen::CGBuilderTy &Builder = CGF.Builder;
4910
4911 llvm::IntegerType *i8 = CGF.Int8Ty;
4912 llvm::Value *Four8 = llvm::ConstantInt::get(i8, 4);
4913 llvm::Value *Eight8 = llvm::ConstantInt::get(i8, 8);
4914 llvm::Value *Sixteen8 = llvm::ConstantInt::get(i8, 16);
4915
4916 // 0-31: r0-31, the 8-byte general-purpose registers
4917 AssignToArrayRange(Builder, Address, Eight8, 0, 31);
4918
4919 // 32-63: fp0-31, the 8-byte floating-point registers
4920 AssignToArrayRange(Builder, Address, Eight8, 32, 63);
4921
4922 // 64-67 are various 8-byte special-purpose registers:
4923 // 64: mq
4924 // 65: lr
4925 // 66: ctr
4926 // 67: ap
4927 AssignToArrayRange(Builder, Address, Eight8, 64, 67);
4928
4929 // 68-76 are various 4-byte special-purpose registers:
4930 // 68-75 cr0-7
4931 // 76: xer
4932 AssignToArrayRange(Builder, Address, Four8, 68, 76);
4933
4934 // 77-108: v0-31, the 16-byte vector registers
4935 AssignToArrayRange(Builder, Address, Sixteen8, 77, 108);
4936
4937 // 109: vrsave
4938 // 110: vscr
4939 // 111: spe_acc
4940 // 112: spefscr
4941 // 113: sfp
4942 // 114: tfhar
4943 // 115: tfiar
4944 // 116: texasr
4945 AssignToArrayRange(Builder, Address, Eight8, 109, 116);
4946
4947 return false;
4948}
4949
4950bool
4951PPC64_SVR4_TargetCodeGenInfo::initDwarfEHRegSizeTable(
4952 CodeGen::CodeGenFunction &CGF,
4953 llvm::Value *Address) const {
4954
4955 return PPC64_initDwarfEHRegSizeTable(CGF, Address);
4956}
4957
4958bool
4959PPC64TargetCodeGenInfo::initDwarfEHRegSizeTable(CodeGen::CodeGenFunction &CGF,
4960 llvm::Value *Address) const {
4961
4962 return PPC64_initDwarfEHRegSizeTable(CGF, Address);
4963}

4967//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//

4969namespace {
4970
4971class AArch64ABIInfo : public SwiftABIInfo {
4972public:
4973 enum ABIKind {
4974 AAPCS = 0,
4975 DarwinPCS,
4976 Win64
4977 };
4978
4979private:
4980 ABIKind Kind;
4981
4982public:
4983 AArch64ABIInfo(CodeGenTypes &CGT, ABIKind Kind)
4984 : SwiftABIInfo(CGT), Kind(Kind) {}
4985
4986private:
4987 ABIKind getABIKind() const { return Kind; }
4988 bool isDarwinPCS() const { return Kind == DarwinPCS; }
4989
4990 ABIArgInfo classifyReturnType(QualType RetTy) const;
4991 ABIArgInfo classifyArgumentType(QualType RetTy) const;
4992 bool isHomogeneousAggregateBaseType(QualType Ty) const override;
4993 bool isHomogeneousAggregateSmallEnough(const Type *Ty,
4994 uint64_t Members) const override;
4995
4996 bool isIllegalVectorType(QualType Ty) const;
4997
4998 void computeInfo(CGFunctionInfo &FI) const override {
4999 if (!::classifyReturnType(getCXXABI(), FI, *this))
5000 FI.getReturnInfo() = classifyReturnType(FI.getReturnType());
5001
5002 for (auto &it : FI.arguments())
5003 it.info = classifyArgumentType(it.type);
5004 }
5005
5006 Address EmitDarwinVAArg(Address VAListAddr, QualType Ty,
5007 CodeGenFunction &CGF) const;
5008
5009 Address EmitAAPCSVAArg(Address VAListAddr, QualType Ty,
5010 CodeGenFunction &CGF) const;
5011
5012 Address EmitVAArg(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Address VAListAddr,
5013 QualType Ty) const override {
5014 return Kind == Win64 ? EmitMSVAArg(CGF, VAListAddr, Ty)
5015 : isDarwinPCS() ? EmitDarwinVAArg(VAListAddr, Ty, CGF)
5016 : EmitAAPCSVAArg(VAListAddr, Ty, CGF);
5017 }
5018
5019 Address EmitMSVAArg(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Address VAListAddr,
5020 QualType Ty) const override;
5021
5022 bool shouldPassIndirectlyForSwift(ArrayRef<llvm::Type*> scalars,
5023 bool asReturnValue) const override {
5024 return occupiesMoreThan(CGT, scalars, /*total*/ 4);
5025 }
5026 bool isSwiftErrorInRegister() const override {
5027 return true;
5028 }
5029
5030 bool isLegalVectorTypeForSwift(CharUnits totalSize, llvm::Type *eltTy,
5031 unsigned elts) const override;
5032};
5033
5034class AArch64TargetCodeGenInfo : public TargetCodeGenInfo {
5035public:
5036 AArch64TargetCodeGenInfo(CodeGenTypes &CGT, AArch64ABIInfo::ABIKind Kind)
5037 : TargetCodeGenInfo(new AArch64ABIInfo(CGT, Kind)) {}
5038
5039 StringRef getARCRetainAutoreleasedReturnValueMarker() const override {
5040 return "mov\tfp, fp\t\t// marker for objc_retainAutoreleaseReturnValue";
5041 }
5042
5043 int getDwarfEHStackPointer(CodeGen::CodeGenModule &M) const override {
5044 return 31;
5045 }
5046
5047 bool doesReturnSlotInterfereWithArgs() const override { return false; }
5048
5049 void setTargetAttributes(const Decl *D, llvm::GlobalValue *GV,
5050 CodeGen::CodeGenModule &CGM) const override {
5051 const FunctionDecl *FD = dyn_cast_or_null<FunctionDecl>(D);
5052 if (!FD)
5053 return;
5054 llvm::Function *Fn = cast<llvm::Function>(GV);
5055
5056 auto Kind = CGM.getCodeGenOpts().getSignReturnAddress();
5057 if (Kind != CodeGenOptions::SignReturnAddressScope::None) {
5058 Fn->addFnAttr("sign-return-address",
5059 Kind == CodeGenOptions::SignReturnAddressScope::All
5060 ? "all"
5061 : "non-leaf");
5062
5063 auto Key = CGM.getCodeGenOpts().getSignReturnAddressKey();
5064 Fn->addFnAttr("sign-return-address-key",
5065 Key == CodeGenOptions::SignReturnAddressKeyValue::AKey
5066 ? "a_key"
5067 : "b_key");
5068 }
5069
5070 if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().BranchTargetEnforcement)
5071 Fn->addFnAttr("branch-target-enforcement");
5072 }
5073};

5077 WindowsAArch64TargetCodeGenInfo(CodeGenTypes &CGT, AArch64ABIInfo::ABIKind K)
5078 : AArch64TargetCodeGenInfo(CGT, K) {}

5086 }

5089 llvm::SmallString<32> &Opt) const override {

5091 }
5092};

5098 return;
5099 addStackProbeTargetAttributes(D, GV, CGM);

5102
5103ABIArgInfo AArch64ABIInfo::classifyArgumentType(QualType Ty) const {
5104 Ty = useFirstFieldIfTransparentUnion(Ty);
5105
5106 // Handle illegal vector types here.
5107 if (isIllegalVectorType(Ty)) {
5108 uint64_t Size = getContext().getTypeSize(Ty);
5109 // Android promotes <2 x i8> to i16, not i32
5110 if (isAndroid() && (Size <= 16)) {
5111 llvm::Type *ResType = llvm::Type::getInt16Ty(getVMContext());
5112 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(ResType);
5113 }
5114 if (Size <= 32) {
5115 llvm::Type *ResType = llvm::Type::getInt32Ty(getVMContext());
5116 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(ResType);
5117 }
5118 if (Size == 64) {
5119 llvm::Type *ResType =
5120 llvm::VectorType::get(llvm::Type::getInt32Ty(getVMContext()), 2);
5121 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(ResType);
5122 }
5123 if (Size == 128) {
5124 llvm::Type *ResType =
5125 llvm::VectorType::get(llvm::Type::getInt32Ty(getVMContext()), 4);
5126 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(ResType);
5127 }
5128 return getNaturalAlignIndirect(Ty, /*ByVal=*/false);
5129 }
5130
5131 if (!isAggregateTypeForABI(Ty)) {
5132 // Treat an enum type as its underlying type.
5133 if (const EnumType *EnumTy = Ty->getAs<EnumType>())
5134 Ty = EnumTy->getDecl()->getIntegerType();
5135
5136 return (Ty->isPromotableIntegerType() && isDarwinPCS()
5137 ? ABIArgInfo::getExtend(Ty)
5138 : ABIArgInfo::getDirect());
5139 }
5140
5141 // Structures with either a non-trivial destructor or a non-trivial
5142 // copy constructor are always indirect.
5143 if (CGCXXABI::RecordArgABI RAA = getRecordArgABI(Ty, getCXXABI())) {
5144 return getNaturalAlignIndirect(Ty, /*ByVal=*/RAA ==
5145 CGCXXABI::RAA_DirectInMemory);
5146 }
5147
5148 // Empty records are always ignored on Darwin, but actually passed in C++ mode
5149 // elsewhere for GNU compatibility.
5150 uint64_t Size = getContext().getTypeSize(Ty);
5151 bool IsEmpty = isEmptyRecord(getContext(), Ty, true);
5152 if (IsEmpty || Size == 0) {
5153 if (!getContext().getLangOpts().CPlusPlus || isDarwinPCS())
5154 return ABIArgInfo::getIgnore();
5155
5156 // GNU C mode. The only argument that gets ignored is an empty one with size
5157 // 0.
5158 if (IsEmpty && Size == 0)
5159 return ABIArgInfo::getIgnore();
5160 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(llvm::Type::getInt8Ty(getVMContext()));
5161 }
5162
5163 // Homogeneous Floating-point Aggregates (HFAs) need to be expanded.
5164 const Type *Base = nullptr;
5165 uint64_t Members = 0;
5166 if (isHomogeneousAggregate(Ty, Base, Members)) {
5167 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(
5168 llvm::ArrayType::get(CGT.ConvertType(QualType(Base, 0)), Members));
5169 }
5170
5171 // Aggregates <= 16 bytes are passed directly in registers or on the stack.
5172 if (Size <= 128) {
5173 // On RenderScript, coerce Aggregates <= 16 bytes to an integer array of
5174 // same size and alignment.
5175 if (getTarget().isRenderScriptTarget()) {
5176 return coerceToIntArray(Ty, getContext(), getVMContext());
5177 }
5178 unsigned Alignment;
5179 if (Kind == AArch64ABIInfo::AAPCS) {
5180 Alignment = getContext().getTypeUnadjustedAlign(Ty);
5181 Alignment = Alignment < 128 ? 64 : 128;
5182 } else {
5183 Alignment = getContext().getTypeAlign(Ty);
5184 }
5185 Size = llvm::alignTo(Size, 64); // round up to multiple of 8 bytes
5186
5187 // We use a pair of i64 for 16-byte aggregate with 8-byte alignment.
5188 // For aggregates with 16-byte alignment, we use i128.
5189 if (Alignment < 128 && Size == 128) {
5190 llvm::Type *BaseTy = llvm::Type::getInt64Ty(getVMContext());
5191 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(llvm::ArrayType::get(BaseTy, Size / 64));
5192 }
5193 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(llvm::IntegerType::get(getVMContext(), Size));
5194 }
5195
5196 return getNaturalAlignIndirect(Ty, /*ByVal=*/false);
5197}
5198
5199ABIArgInfo AArch64ABIInfo::classifyReturnType(QualType RetTy) const {
5200 if (RetTy->isVoidType())
5201 return ABIArgInfo::getIgnore();
5202
5203 // Large vector types should be returned via memory.
5204 if (RetTy->isVectorType() && getContext().getTypeSize(RetTy) > 128)
5205 return getNaturalAlignIndirect(RetTy);
5206
5207 if (!isAggregateTypeForABI(RetTy)) {
5208 // Treat an enum type as its underlying type.
5209 if (const EnumType *EnumTy = RetTy->getAs<EnumType>())
5210 RetTy = EnumTy->getDecl()->getIntegerType();
5211
5212 return (RetTy->isPromotableIntegerType() && isDarwinPCS()
5213 ? ABIArgInfo::getExtend(RetTy)
5214 : ABIArgInfo::getDirect());
5215 }
5216
5217 uint64_t Size = getContext().getTypeSize(RetTy);
5218 if (isEmptyRecord(getContext(), RetTy, true) || Size == 0)
5219 return ABIArgInfo::getIgnore();
5220
5221 const Type *Base = nullptr;
5222 uint64_t Members = 0;
5223 if (isHomogeneousAggregate(RetTy, Base, Members))
5224 // Homogeneous Floating-point Aggregates (HFAs) are returned directly.
5225 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect();
5226
5227 // Aggregates <= 16 bytes are returned directly in registers or on the stack.
5228 if (Size <= 128) {
5229 // On RenderScript, coerce Aggregates <= 16 bytes to an integer array of
5230 // same size and alignment.
5231 if (getTarget().isRenderScriptTarget()) {
5232 return coerceToIntArray(RetTy, getContext(), getVMContext());
5233 }
5234 unsigned Alignment = getContext().getTypeAlign(RetTy);
5235 Size = llvm::alignTo(Size, 64); // round up to multiple of 8 bytes
5236
5237 // We use a pair of i64 for 16-byte aggregate with 8-byte alignment.
5238 // For aggregates with 16-byte alignment, we use i128.
5239 if (Alignment < 128 && Size == 128) {
5240 llvm::Type *BaseTy = llvm::Type::getInt64Ty(getVMContext());
5241 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(llvm::ArrayType::get(BaseTy, Size / 64));
5242 }
5243 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(llvm::IntegerType::get(getVMContext(), Size));
5244 }
5245
5246 return getNaturalAlignIndirect(RetTy);
5247}
5248
5249/// isIllegalVectorType - check whether the vector type is legal for AArch64.
5250bool AArch64ABIInfo::isIllegalVectorType(QualType Ty) const {
5251 if (const VectorType *VT = Ty->getAs<VectorType>()) {
5252 // Check whether VT is legal.
5253 unsigned NumElements = VT->getNumElements();
5254 uint64_t Size = getContext().getTypeSize(VT);
5255 // NumElements should be power of 2.
5256 if (!llvm::isPowerOf2_32(NumElements))
5257 return true;
5258 return Size != 64 && (Size != 128 || NumElements == 1);
5259 }
5260 return false;
5261}
5262
5263bool AArch64ABIInfo::isLegalVectorTypeForSwift(CharUnits totalSize,
5264 llvm::Type *eltTy,
5265 unsigned elts) const {
5266 if (!llvm::isPowerOf2_32(elts))
5267 return false;
5268 if (totalSize.getQuantity() != 8 &&
5269 (totalSize.getQuantity() != 16 || elts == 1))
5270 return false;
5271 return true;
5272}
5273
5274bool AArch64ABIInfo::isHomogeneousAggregateBaseType(QualType Ty) const {
5275 // Homogeneous aggregates for AAPCS64 must have base types of a floating
5276 // point type or a short-vector type. This is the same as the 32-bit ABI,
5277 // but with the difference that any floating-point type is allowed,
5278 // including __fp16.
5279 if (const BuiltinType *BT = Ty->getAs<BuiltinType>()) {
5280 if (BT->isFloatingPoint())
5281 return true;
5282 } else if (const VectorType *VT = Ty->getAs<VectorType>()) {
5283 unsigned VecSize = getContext().getTypeSize(VT);
5284 if (VecSize == 64 || VecSize == 128)
5285 return true;
5286 }
5287 return false;
5288}
5289
5290bool AArch64ABIInfo::isHomogeneousAggregateSmallEnough(const Type *Base,
5291 uint64_t Members) const {
5292 return Members <= 4;
5293}
5294
5295Address AArch64ABIInfo::EmitAAPCSVAArg(Address VAListAddr,
5296 QualType Ty,
5297 CodeGenFunction &CGF) const {
5298 ABIArgInfo AI = classifyArgumentType(Ty);
5299 bool IsIndirect = AI.isIndirect();
5300
5301 llvm::Type *BaseTy = CGF.ConvertType(Ty);
5302 if (IsIndirect)
5303 BaseTy = CGF.CGM.getPointerInDefaultAS(BaseTy);
5304 else if (AI.getCoerceToType())
5305 BaseTy = AI.getCoerceToType();
5306
5307 unsigned NumRegs = 1;
5308 if (llvm::ArrayType *ArrTy = dyn_cast<llvm::ArrayType>(BaseTy)) {
5309 BaseTy = ArrTy->getElementType();
5310 NumRegs = ArrTy->getNumElements();
5311 }
5312 bool IsFPR = BaseTy->isFloatingPointTy() || BaseTy->isVectorTy();
5313
5314 // The AArch64 va_list type and handling is specified in the Procedure Call
5315 // Standard, section B.4:
5316 //
5317 // struct {
5318 // void *__stack;
5319 // void *__gr_top;
5320 // void *__vr_top;
5321 // int __gr_offs;
5322 // int __vr_offs;
5323 // };
5324
5325 llvm::BasicBlock *MaybeRegBlock = CGF.createBasicBlock("vaarg.maybe_reg");
5326 llvm::BasicBlock *InRegBlock = CGF.createBasicBlock("vaarg.in_reg");
5327 llvm::BasicBlock *OnStackBlock = CGF.createBasicBlock("vaarg.on_stack");
5328 llvm::BasicBlock *ContBlock = CGF.createBasicBlock("vaarg.end");
5329
5330 CharUnits TySize = getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(Ty);
5331 CharUnits TyAlign = getContext().getTypeUnadjustedAlignInChars(Ty);
5332
5333 Address reg_offs_p = Address::invalid();
5334 llvm::Value *reg_offs = nullptr;
5335 int reg_top_index;
5336 int RegSize = IsIndirect ? 8 : TySize.getQuantity();
5337 if (!IsFPR) {
5338 // 3 is the field number of __gr_offs
5339 reg_offs_p = CGF.Builder.CreateStructGEP(VAListAddr, 3, "gr_offs_p");
5340 reg_offs = CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(reg_offs_p, "gr_offs");
5341 reg_top_index = 1; // field number for __gr_top
5342 RegSize = llvm::alignTo(RegSize, 8);
5343 } else {
5344 // 4 is the field number of __vr_offs.
5345 reg_offs_p = CGF.Builder.CreateStructGEP(VAListAddr, 4, "vr_offs_p");
5346 reg_offs = CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(reg_offs_p, "vr_offs");
5347 reg_top_index = 2; // field number for __vr_top
5348 RegSize = 16 * NumRegs;
5349 }
5350
5351 //=======================================
5352 // Find out where argument was passed
5353 //=======================================
5354
5355 // If reg_offs >= 0 we're already using the stack for this type of
5356 // argument. We don't want to keep updating reg_offs (in case it overflows,
5357 // though anyone passing 2GB of arguments, each at most 16 bytes, deserves
5358 // whatever they get).
5359 llvm::Value *UsingStack = nullptr;
5360 UsingStack = CGF.Builder.CreateICmpSGE(
5361 reg_offs, llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.Int32Ty, 0));
5362
5363 CGF.Builder.CreateCondBr(UsingStack, OnStackBlock, MaybeRegBlock);
5364
5365 // Otherwise, at least some kind of argument could go in these registers, the
5366 // question is whether this particular type is too big.
5367 CGF.EmitBlock(MaybeRegBlock);
5368
5369 // Integer arguments may need to correct register alignment (for example a
5370 // "struct { __int128 a; };" gets passed in x_2N, x_{2N+1}). In this case we
5371 // align __gr_offs to calculate the potential address.
5372 if (!IsFPR && !IsIndirect && TyAlign.getQuantity() > 8) {
5373 int Align = TyAlign.getQuantity();
5374
5375 reg_offs = CGF.Builder.CreateAdd(
5376 reg_offs, llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.Int32Ty, Align - 1),
5377 "align_regoffs");
5378 reg_offs = CGF.Builder.CreateAnd(
5379 reg_offs, llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.Int32Ty, -Align),
5380 "aligned_regoffs");
5381 }
5382
5383 // Update the gr_offs/vr_offs pointer for next call to va_arg on this va_list.
5384 // The fact that this is done unconditionally reflects the fact that
5385 // allocating an argument to the stack also uses up all the remaining
5386 // registers of the appropriate kind.
5387 llvm::Value *NewOffset = nullptr;
5388 NewOffset = CGF.Builder.CreateAdd(
5389 reg_offs, llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.Int32Ty, RegSize), "new_reg_offs");
5390 CGF.Builder.CreateStore(NewOffset, reg_offs_p);
5391
5392 // Now we're in a position to decide whether this argument really was in
5393 // registers or not.
5394 llvm::Value *InRegs = nullptr;
5395 InRegs = CGF.Builder.CreateICmpSLE(
5396 NewOffset, llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.Int32Ty, 0), "inreg");
5397
5398 CGF.Builder.CreateCondBr(InRegs, InRegBlock, OnStackBlock);
5399
5400 //=======================================
5401 // Argument was in registers
5402 //=======================================
5403
5404 // Now we emit the code for if the argument was originally passed in
5405 // registers. First start the appropriate block:
5406 CGF.EmitBlock(InRegBlock);
5407
5408 llvm::Value *reg_top = nullptr;
5409 Address reg_top_p =
5410 CGF.Builder.CreateStructGEP(VAListAddr, reg_top_index, "reg_top_p");
5411 reg_top = CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(reg_top_p, "reg_top");
5412 Address BaseAddr(CGF.Builder.CreateInBoundsGEP(reg_top, reg_offs),
5413 CharUnits::fromQuantity(IsFPR ? 16 : 8));
5414 Address RegAddr = Address::invalid();
5415 llvm::Type *MemTy = CGF.ConvertTypeForMem(Ty);
5416
5417 if (IsIndirect) {
5418 // If it's been passed indirectly (actually a struct), whatever we find from
5419 // stored registers or on the stack will actually be a struct **.
5420 MemTy = CGF.CGM.getPointerInDefaultAS(MemTy);
5421 }
5422
5423 const Type *Base = nullptr;
5424 uint64_t NumMembers = 0;
5425 bool IsHFA = isHomogeneousAggregate(Ty, Base, NumMembers);
5426 if (IsHFA && NumMembers > 1) {
5427 // Homogeneous aggregates passed in registers will have their elements split
5428 // and stored 16-bytes apart regardless of size (they're notionally in qN,
5429 // qN+1, ...). We reload and store into a temporary local variable
5430 // contiguously.
5431 assert(!IsIndirect && "Homogeneous aggregates should be passed directly");
5432 auto BaseTyInfo = getContext().getTypeInfoInChars(QualType(Base, 0));
5433 llvm::Type *BaseTy = CGF.ConvertType(QualType(Base, 0));
5434 llvm::Type *HFATy = llvm::ArrayType::get(BaseTy, NumMembers);
5435 Address Tmp = CGF.CreateTempAlloca(HFATy,
5436 std::max(TyAlign, BaseTyInfo.second));
5437
5438 // On big-endian platforms, the value will be right-aligned in its slot.
5439 int Offset = 0;
5440 if (CGF.CGM.getDataLayout().isBigEndian() &&
5441 BaseTyInfo.first.getQuantity() < 16)
5442 Offset = 16 - BaseTyInfo.first.getQuantity();
5443
5444 for (unsigned i = 0; i < NumMembers; ++i) {
5445 CharUnits BaseOffset = CharUnits::fromQuantity(16 * i + Offset);
5446 Address LoadAddr =
5447 CGF.Builder.CreateConstInBoundsByteGEP(BaseAddr, BaseOffset);
5448 LoadAddr = CGF.Builder.CreateElementBitCast(LoadAddr, BaseTy);
5449
5450 Address StoreAddr = CGF.Builder.CreateConstArrayGEP(Tmp, i);
5451
5452 llvm::Value *Elem = CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(LoadAddr);
5453 CGF.Builder.CreateStore(Elem, StoreAddr);
5454 }
5455
5456 RegAddr = CGF.Builder.CreateElementBitCast(Tmp, MemTy);
5457 } else {
5458 // Otherwise the object is contiguous in memory.
5459
5460 // It might be right-aligned in its slot.
5461 CharUnits SlotSize = BaseAddr.getAlignment();
5462 if (CGF.CGM.getDataLayout().isBigEndian() && !IsIndirect &&
5463 (IsHFA || !isAggregateTypeForABI(Ty)) &&
5464 TySize < SlotSize) {
5465 CharUnits Offset = SlotSize - TySize;
5466 BaseAddr = CGF.Builder.CreateConstInBoundsByteGEP(BaseAddr, Offset);
5467 }
5468
5469 RegAddr = CGF.Builder.CreateElementBitCast(BaseAddr, MemTy);
5470 }
5471
5472 CGF.EmitBranch(ContBlock);
5473
5474 //=======================================
5475 // Argument was on the stack
5476 //=======================================
5477 CGF.EmitBlock(OnStackBlock);
5478
5479 Address stack_p = CGF.Builder.CreateStructGEP(VAListAddr, 0, "stack_p");
5480 llvm::Value *OnStackPtr = CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(stack_p, "stack");
5481
5482 // Again, stack arguments may need realignment. In this case both integer and
5483 // floating-point ones might be affected.
5484 if (!IsIndirect && TyAlign.getQuantity() > 8) {
5485 int Align = TyAlign.getQuantity();
5486
5487 OnStackPtr = CGF.Builder.CreatePtrToInt(OnStackPtr, CGF.Int64Ty);
5488
5489 OnStackPtr = CGF.Builder.CreateAdd(
5490 OnStackPtr, llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.Int64Ty, Align - 1),
5491 "align_stack");
5492 OnStackPtr = CGF.Builder.CreateAnd(
5493 OnStackPtr, llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.Int64Ty, -Align),
5494 "align_stack");
5495
5496 OnStackPtr = CGF.Builder.CreateIntToPtr(OnStackPtr, CGF.Int8PtrTy);
5497 }
5498 Address OnStackAddr(OnStackPtr,
5499 std::max(CharUnits::fromQuantity(8), TyAlign));
5500
5501 // All stack slots are multiples of 8 bytes.
5502 CharUnits StackSlotSize = CharUnits::fromQuantity(8);
5503 CharUnits StackSize;
5504 if (IsIndirect)
5505 StackSize = StackSlotSize;
5506 else
5507 StackSize = TySize.alignTo(StackSlotSize);
5508
5509 llvm::Value *StackSizeC = CGF.Builder.getSize(StackSize);
5510 llvm::Value *NewStack =
5511 CGF.Builder.CreateInBoundsGEP(OnStackPtr, StackSizeC, "new_stack");
5512
5513 // Write the new value of __stack for the next call to va_arg
5514 CGF.Builder.CreateStore(NewStack, stack_p);
5515
5516 if (CGF.CGM.getDataLayout().isBigEndian() && !isAggregateTypeForABI(Ty) &&
5517 TySize < StackSlotSize) {
5518 CharUnits Offset = StackSlotSize - TySize;
5519 OnStackAddr = CGF.Builder.CreateConstInBoundsByteGEP(OnStackAddr, Offset);
5520 }
5521
5522 OnStackAddr = CGF.Builder.CreateElementBitCast(OnStackAddr, MemTy);
5523
5524 CGF.EmitBranch(ContBlock);
5525
5526 //=======================================
5527 // Tidy up
5528 //=======================================
5529 CGF.EmitBlock(ContBlock);
5530
5531 Address ResAddr = emitMergePHI(CGF, RegAddr, InRegBlock,
5532 OnStackAddr, OnStackBlock, "vaargs.addr");
5533
5534 if (IsIndirect)
5535 return Address(CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(ResAddr, "vaarg.addr"),
5536 TyAlign);
5537
5538 return ResAddr;
5539}
5540
5541Address AArch64ABIInfo::EmitDarwinVAArg(Address VAListAddr, QualType Ty,
5542 CodeGenFunction &CGF) const {
5543 // The backend's lowering doesn't support va_arg for aggregates or
5544 // illegal vector types. Lower VAArg here for these cases and use
5545 // the LLVM va_arg instruction for everything else.
5546 if (!isAggregateTypeForABI(Ty) && !isIllegalVectorType(Ty))
5547 return EmitVAArgInstr(CGF, VAListAddr, Ty, ABIArgInfo::getDirect());
5548
5549 CharUnits SlotSize = CharUnits::fromQuantity(8);
5550
5551 // Empty records are ignored for parameter passing purposes.
5552 if (isEmptyRecord(getContext(), Ty, true)) {
5553 Address Addr(CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(VAListAddr, "ap.cur"), SlotSize);
5554 Addr = CGF.Builder.CreateElementBitCast(Addr, CGF.ConvertTypeForMem(Ty));
5555 return Addr;
5556 }
5557
5558 // The size of the actual thing passed, which might end up just
5559 // being a pointer for indirect types.
5560 auto TyInfo = getContext().getTypeInfoInChars(Ty);
5561
5562 // Arguments bigger than 16 bytes which aren't homogeneous
5563 // aggregates should be passed indirectly.
5564 bool IsIndirect = false;
5565 if (TyInfo.first.getQuantity() > 16) {
5566 const Type *Base = nullptr;
5567 uint64_t Members = 0;
5568 IsIndirect = !isHomogeneousAggregate(Ty, Base, Members);
5569 }
5570
5571 return emitVoidPtrVAArg(CGF, VAListAddr, Ty, IsIndirect,
5572 TyInfo, SlotSize, /*AllowHigherAlign*/ true);
5573}
5574
5575Address AArch64ABIInfo::EmitMSVAArg(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Address VAListAddr,
5576 QualType Ty) const {
5577 return emitVoidPtrVAArg(CGF, VAListAddr, Ty, /*indirect*/ false,
5578 CGF.getContext().getTypeInfoInChars(Ty),
5579 CharUnits::fromQuantity(8),
5580 /*allowHigherAlign*/ false);
5581}
5582
5583//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
5584// ARM ABI Implementation
5585//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
