5587namespace {
5588
5589class ARMABIInfo : public SwiftABIInfo {
5590public:
5591 enum ABIKind {
5592 APCS = 0,
5593 AAPCS = 1,
5594 AAPCS_VFP = 2,
5595 AAPCS16_VFP = 3,
5596 };
5597
5598private:
5599 ABIKind Kind;
5600
5601public:
5602 ARMABIInfo(CodeGenTypes &CGT, ABIKind _Kind)
5603 : SwiftABIInfo(CGT), Kind(_Kind) {
5604 setCCs();
5605 }
5606
5607 bool isEABI() const {
5608 switch (getTarget().getTriple().getEnvironment()) {
5609 case llvm::Triple::Android:
5610 case llvm::Triple::EABI:
5611 case llvm::Triple::EABIHF:
5612 case llvm::Triple::GNUEABI:
5613 case llvm::Triple::GNUEABIHF:
5614 case llvm::Triple::MuslEABI:
5615 case llvm::Triple::MuslEABIHF:
5616 return true;
5617 default:
5618 return false;
5619 }
5620 }
5621
5622 bool isEABIHF() const {
5623 switch (getTarget().getTriple().getEnvironment()) {
5624 case llvm::Triple::EABIHF:
5625 case llvm::Triple::GNUEABIHF:
5626 case llvm::Triple::MuslEABIHF:
5627 return true;
5628 default:
5629 return false;
5630 }
5631 }
5632
5633 ABIKind getABIKind() const { return Kind; }
5634
5635private:
5636 ABIArgInfo classifyReturnType(QualType RetTy, bool isVariadic,
5637 unsigned functionCallConv) const;
5638 ABIArgInfo classifyArgumentType(QualType RetTy, bool isVariadic,
5639 unsigned functionCallConv) const;
5640 ABIArgInfo classifyHomogeneousAggregate(QualType Ty, const Type *Base,
5641 uint64_t Members) const;
5642 ABIArgInfo coerceIllegalVector(QualType Ty) const;
5643 bool isIllegalVectorType(QualType Ty) const;
5644
5645 bool isHomogeneousAggregateBaseType(QualType Ty) const override;
5646 bool isHomogeneousAggregateSmallEnough(const Type *Ty,
5647 uint64_t Members) const override;
5648
5649 bool isEffectivelyAAPCS_VFP(unsigned callConvention, bool acceptHalf) const;
5650
5651 void computeInfo(CGFunctionInfo &FI) const override;
5652
5653 Address EmitVAArg(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Address VAListAddr,
5654 QualType Ty) const override;
5655
5656 llvm::CallingConv::ID getLLVMDefaultCC() const;
5657 llvm::CallingConv::ID getABIDefaultCC() const;
5658 void setCCs();
5659
5660 bool shouldPassIndirectlyForSwift(ArrayRef<llvm::Type*> scalars,
5661 bool asReturnValue) const override {
5662 return occupiesMoreThan(CGT, scalars, /*total*/ 4);
5663 }
5664 bool isSwiftErrorInRegister() const override {
5665 return true;
5666 }
5667 bool isLegalVectorTypeForSwift(CharUnits totalSize, llvm::Type *eltTy,
5668 unsigned elts) const override;
5669};
5670
5671class ARMTargetCodeGenInfo : public TargetCodeGenInfo {
5672public:
5673 ARMTargetCodeGenInfo(CodeGenTypes &CGT, ARMABIInfo::ABIKind K)
5674 :TargetCodeGenInfo(new ARMABIInfo(CGT, K)) {}
5675
5676 const ARMABIInfo &getABIInfo() const {
5677 return static_cast<const ARMABIInfo&>(TargetCodeGenInfo::getABIInfo());
5678 }
5679
5680 int getDwarfEHStackPointer(CodeGen::CodeGenModule &M) const override {
5681 return 13;
5682 }
5683
5684 StringRef getARCRetainAutoreleasedReturnValueMarker() const override {
5685 return "mov\tr7, r7\t\t// marker for objc_retainAutoreleaseReturnValue";
5686 }
5687
5688 bool initDwarfEHRegSizeTable(CodeGen::CodeGenFunction &CGF,
5689 llvm::Value *Address) const override {
5690 llvm::Value *Four8 = llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.Int8Ty, 4);
5691
5692 // 0-15 are the 16 integer registers.
5693 AssignToArrayRange(CGF.Builder, Address, Four8, 0, 15);
5694 return false;
5695 }
5696
5697 unsigned getSizeOfUnwindException() const override {
5698 if (getABIInfo().isEABI()) return 88;
5699 return TargetCodeGenInfo::getSizeOfUnwindException();
5700 }
5701
5702 void setTargetAttributes(const Decl *D, llvm::GlobalValue *GV,
5703 CodeGen::CodeGenModule &CGM) const override {
5704 if (GV->isDeclaration())
5705 return;
5706 const FunctionDecl *FD = dyn_cast_or_null<FunctionDecl>(D);
5707 if (!FD)
5708 return;
5709
5710 const ARMInterruptAttr *Attr = FD->getAttr<ARMInterruptAttr>();
5711 if (!Attr)
5712 return;
5713
5714 const char *Kind;
5715 switch (Attr->getInterrupt()) {
5716 case ARMInterruptAttr::Generic: Kind = ""; break;
5717 case ARMInterruptAttr::IRQ: Kind = "IRQ"; break;
5718 case ARMInterruptAttr::FIQ: Kind = "FIQ"; break;
5719 case ARMInterruptAttr::SWI: Kind = "SWI"; break;
5720 case ARMInterruptAttr::ABORT: Kind = "ABORT"; break;
5721 case ARMInterruptAttr::UNDEF: Kind = "UNDEF"; break;
5722 }
5723
5724 llvm::Function *Fn = cast<llvm::Function>(GV);
5725
5726 Fn->addFnAttr("interrupt", Kind);
5727
5728 ARMABIInfo::ABIKind ABI = cast<ARMABIInfo>(getABIInfo()).getABIKind();
5729 if (ABI == ARMABIInfo::APCS)
5730 return;
5731
5732 // AAPCS guarantees that sp will be 8-byte aligned on any public interface,
5733 // however this is not necessarily true on taking any interrupt. Instruct
5734 // the backend to perform a realignment as part of the function prologue.
5735 llvm::AttrBuilder B;
5736 B.addStackAlignmentAttr(8);
5737 Fn->addAttributes(llvm::AttributeList::FunctionIndex, B);
5738 }
5739};
5740
5741class WindowsARMTargetCodeGenInfo : public ARMTargetCodeGenInfo {
5742public:
5743 WindowsARMTargetCodeGenInfo(CodeGenTypes &CGT, ARMABIInfo::ABIKind K)
5744 : ARMTargetCodeGenInfo(CGT, K) {}
5745
5746 void setTargetAttributes(const Decl *D, llvm::GlobalValue *GV,
5747 CodeGen::CodeGenModule &CGM) const override;
5748
5749 void getDependentLibraryOption(llvm::StringRef Lib,
5750 llvm::SmallString<24> &Opt) const override {
5751 Opt = "/DEFAULTLIB:" + qualifyWindowsLibrary(Lib);
5752 }
5753
5754 void getDetectMismatchOption(llvm::StringRef Name, llvm::StringRef Value,
5755 llvm::SmallString<32> &Opt) const override {
5756 Opt = "/FAILIFMISMATCH:\"" + Name.str() + "=" + Value.str() + "\"";
5757 }
5758};
5759
5760void WindowsARMTargetCodeGenInfo::setTargetAttributes(
5761 const Decl *D, llvm::GlobalValue *GV, CodeGen::CodeGenModule &CGM) const {
5762 ARMTargetCodeGenInfo::setTargetAttributes(D, GV, CGM);
5763 if (GV->isDeclaration())
5764 return;
5765 addStackProbeTargetAttributes(D, GV, CGM);
5766}
5767}
5768
5769void ARMABIInfo::computeInfo(CGFunctionInfo &FI) const {
5770 if (!::classifyReturnType(getCXXABI(), FI, *this))
5771 FI.getReturnInfo() = classifyReturnType(FI.getReturnType(), FI.isVariadic(),
5772 FI.getCallingConvention());
5773
5774 for (auto &I : FI.arguments())
5775 I.info = classifyArgumentType(I.type, FI.isVariadic(),
5776 FI.getCallingConvention());
5777
5778
5779 // Always honor user-specified calling convention.
5780 if (FI.getCallingConvention() != llvm::CallingConv::C)
5781 return;
5782
5783 llvm::CallingConv::ID cc = getRuntimeCC();
5784 if (cc != llvm::CallingConv::C)
5785 FI.setEffectiveCallingConvention(cc);
5786}
5787
5788/// Return the default calling convention that LLVM will use.
5789llvm::CallingConv::ID ARMABIInfo::getLLVMDefaultCC() const {
5790 // The default calling convention that LLVM will infer.
5791 if (isEABIHF() || getTarget().getTriple().isWatchABI())
5792 return llvm::CallingConv::ARM_AAPCS_VFP;
5793 else if (isEABI())
5794 return llvm::CallingConv::ARM_AAPCS;
5795 else
5796 return llvm::CallingConv::ARM_APCS;
5797}
5798
5799/// Return the calling convention that our ABI would like us to use
5800/// as the C calling convention.
5801llvm::CallingConv::ID ARMABIInfo::getABIDefaultCC() const {
5802 switch (getABIKind()) {
5803 case APCS: return llvm::CallingConv::ARM_APCS;
5804 case AAPCS: return llvm::CallingConv::ARM_AAPCS;
5805 case AAPCS_VFP: return llvm::CallingConv::ARM_AAPCS_VFP;
5806 case AAPCS16_VFP: return llvm::CallingConv::ARM_AAPCS_VFP;
5807 }
5808 llvm_unreachable("bad ABI kind");
5809}
5810
5811void ARMABIInfo::setCCs() {
5812 assert(getRuntimeCC() == llvm::CallingConv::C);
5813
5814 // Don't muddy up the IR with a ton of explicit annotations if
5815 // they'd just match what LLVM will infer from the triple.
5816 llvm::CallingConv::ID abiCC = getABIDefaultCC();
5817 if (abiCC != getLLVMDefaultCC())
5818 RuntimeCC = abiCC;
5819}
5820
5821ABIArgInfo ARMABIInfo::coerceIllegalVector(QualType Ty) const {
5822 uint64_t Size = getContext().getTypeSize(Ty);
5823 if (Size <= 32) {
5824 llvm::Type *ResType =
5825 llvm::Type::getInt32Ty(getVMContext());
5826 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(ResType);
5827 }
5828 if (Size == 64 || Size == 128) {
5829 llvm::Type *ResType = llvm::VectorType::get(
5830 llvm::Type::getInt32Ty(getVMContext()), Size / 32);
5831 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(ResType);
5832 }
5833 return getNaturalAlignIndirect(Ty, /*ByVal=*/false);
5834}
5835
5836ABIArgInfo ARMABIInfo::classifyHomogeneousAggregate(QualType Ty,
5837 const Type *Base,
5838 uint64_t Members) const {
5839 assert(Base && "Base class should be set for homogeneous aggregate");
5840 // Base can be a floating-point or a vector.
5841 if (const VectorType *VT = Base->getAs<VectorType>()) {
5842 // FP16 vectors should be converted to integer vectors
5843 if (!getTarget().hasLegalHalfType() &&
5844 (VT->getElementType()->isFloat16Type() ||
5845 VT->getElementType()->isHalfType())) {
5846 uint64_t Size = getContext().getTypeSize(VT);
5847 llvm::Type *NewVecTy = llvm::VectorType::get(
5848 llvm::Type::getInt32Ty(getVMContext()), Size / 32);
5849 llvm::Type *Ty = llvm::ArrayType::get(NewVecTy, Members);
5850 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(Ty, 0, nullptr, false);
5851 }
5852 }
5853 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(nullptr, 0, nullptr, false);
5854}
5855
5856ABIArgInfo ARMABIInfo::classifyArgumentType(QualType Ty, bool isVariadic,
5857 unsigned functionCallConv) const {
5858 // 6.1.2.1 The following argument types are VFP CPRCs:
5859 // A single-precision floating-point type (including promoted
5860 // half-precision types); A double-precision floating-point type;
5861 // A 64-bit or 128-bit containerized vector type; Homogeneous Aggregate
5862 // with a Base Type of a single- or double-precision floating-point type,
5863 // 64-bit containerized vectors or 128-bit containerized vectors with one
5864 // to four Elements.
5865 // Variadic functions should always marshal to the base standard.
5866 bool IsAAPCS_VFP =
5867 !isVariadic && isEffectivelyAAPCS_VFP(functionCallConv, /* AAPCS16 */ false);
5868
5869 Ty = useFirstFieldIfTransparentUnion(Ty);
5870
5871 // Handle illegal vector types here.
5872 if (isIllegalVectorType(Ty))
5873 return coerceIllegalVector(Ty);
5874
5875 // _Float16 and __fp16 get passed as if it were an int or float, but with
5876 // the top 16 bits unspecified. This is not done for OpenCL as it handles the
5877 // half type natively, and does not need to interwork with AAPCS code.
5878 if ((Ty->isFloat16Type() || Ty->isHalfType()) &&
5879 !getContext().getLangOpts().NativeHalfArgsAndReturns) {
5880 llvm::Type *ResType = IsAAPCS_VFP ?
5881 llvm::Type::getFloatTy(getVMContext()) :
5882 llvm::Type::getInt32Ty(getVMContext());
5883 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(ResType);
5884 }
5885
5886 if (!isAggregateTypeForABI(Ty)) {
5887 // Treat an enum type as its underlying type.
5888 if (const EnumType *EnumTy = Ty->getAs<EnumType>()) {
5889 Ty = EnumTy->getDecl()->getIntegerType();
5890 }
5891
5892 return (Ty->isPromotableIntegerType() ? ABIArgInfo::getExtend(Ty)
5893 : ABIArgInfo::getDirect());
5894 }
5895
5896 if (CGCXXABI::RecordArgABI RAA = getRecordArgABI(Ty, getCXXABI())) {
5897 return getNaturalAlignIndirect(Ty, RAA == CGCXXABI::RAA_DirectInMemory);
5898 }
5899
5900 // Ignore empty records.
5901 if (isEmptyRecord(getContext(), Ty, true))
5902 return ABIArgInfo::getIgnore();
5903
5904 if (IsAAPCS_VFP) {
5905 // Homogeneous Aggregates need to be expanded when we can fit the aggregate
5906 // into VFP registers.
5907 const Type *Base = nullptr;
5908 uint64_t Members = 0;
5909 if (isHomogeneousAggregate(Ty, Base, Members))
5910 return classifyHomogeneousAggregate(Ty, Base, Members);
5911 } else if (getABIKind() == ARMABIInfo::AAPCS16_VFP) {
5912 // WatchOS does have homogeneous aggregates. Note that we intentionally use
5913 // this convention even for a variadic function: the backend will use GPRs
5914 // if needed.
5915 const Type *Base = nullptr;
5916 uint64_t Members = 0;
5917 if (isHomogeneousAggregate(Ty, Base, Members)) {
5918 assert(Base && Members <= 4 && "unexpected homogeneous aggregate");
5919 llvm::Type *Ty =
5920 llvm::ArrayType::get(CGT.ConvertType(QualType(Base, 0)), Members);
5921 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(Ty, 0, nullptr, false);
5922 }
5923 }
5924
5925 if (getABIKind() == ARMABIInfo::AAPCS16_VFP &&
5926 getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(Ty) > CharUnits::fromQuantity(16)) {
5927 // WatchOS is adopting the 64-bit AAPCS rule on composite types: if they're
5928 // bigger than 128-bits, they get placed in space allocated by the caller,
5929 // and a pointer is passed.
5930 return ABIArgInfo::getIndirect(
5931 CharUnits::fromQuantity(getContext().getTypeAlign(Ty) / 8), false);
5932 }
5933
5934 // Support byval for ARM.
5935 // The ABI alignment for APCS is 4-byte and for AAPCS at least 4-byte and at
5936 // most 8-byte. We realign the indirect argument if type alignment is bigger
5937 // than ABI alignment.
5938 uint64_t ABIAlign = 4;
5939 uint64_t TyAlign;
5940 if (getABIKind() == ARMABIInfo::AAPCS_VFP ||
5941 getABIKind() == ARMABIInfo::AAPCS) {
5942 TyAlign = getContext().getTypeUnadjustedAlignInChars(Ty).getQuantity();
5943 ABIAlign = std::min(std::max(TyAlign, (uint64_t)4), (uint64_t)8);
5944 } else {
5945 TyAlign = getContext().getTypeAlignInChars(Ty).getQuantity();
5946 }
5947 if (getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(Ty) > CharUnits::fromQuantity(64)) {
5948 assert(getABIKind() != ARMABIInfo::AAPCS16_VFP && "unexpected byval");
5949 return ABIArgInfo::getIndirect(CharUnits::fromQuantity(ABIAlign),
5950 /*ByVal=*/true,
5951 /*Realign=*/TyAlign > ABIAlign);
5952 }
5953
5954 // On RenderScript, coerce Aggregates <= 64 bytes to an integer array of
5955 // same size and alignment.
5956 if (getTarget().isRenderScriptTarget()) {
5957 return coerceToIntArray(Ty, getContext(), getVMContext());
5958 }
5959
5960 // Otherwise, pass by coercing to a structure of the appropriate size.
5961 llvm::Type* ElemTy;
5962 unsigned SizeRegs;
5963 // FIXME: Try to match the types of the arguments more accurately where
5964 // we can.
5965 if (TyAlign <= 4) {
5966 ElemTy = llvm::Type::getInt32Ty(getVMContext());
5967 SizeRegs = (getContext().getTypeSize(Ty) + 31) / 32;
5968 } else {
5969 ElemTy = llvm::Type::getInt64Ty(getVMContext());
5970 SizeRegs = (getContext().getTypeSize(Ty) + 63) / 64;
5971 }
5972
5973 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(llvm::ArrayType::get(ElemTy, SizeRegs));
5974}
5975
5976static bool isIntegerLikeType(QualType Ty, ASTContext &Context,
5977 llvm::LLVMContext &VMContext) {
5978 // APCS, C Language Calling Conventions, Non-Simple Return Values: A structure
5979 // is called integer-like if its size is less than or equal to one word, and
5980 // the offset of each of its addressable sub-fields is zero.
5981
5982 uint64_t Size = Context.getTypeSize(Ty);
5983
5984 // Check that the type fits in a word.
5985 if (Size > 32)
5986 return false;
5987
5988 // FIXME: Handle vector types!
5989 if (Ty->isVectorType())
5990 return false;
5991
5992 // Float types are never treated as "integer like".
5993 if (Ty->isRealFloatingType())
5994 return false;
5995
5996 // If this is a builtin or pointer type then it is ok.
5997 if (Ty->getAs<BuiltinType>() || Ty->isPointerType())
5998 return true;
5999
6000 // Small complex integer types are "integer like".
6001 if (const ComplexType *CT = Ty->getAs<ComplexType>())
6002 return isIntegerLikeType(CT->getElementType(), Context, VMContext);
6003
6004 // Single element and zero sized arrays should be allowed, by the definition
6005 // above, but they are not.
6006
6007 // Otherwise, it must be a record type.
6008 const RecordType *RT = Ty->getAs<RecordType>();
6009 if (!RT) return false;
6010
6011 // Ignore records with flexible arrays.
6012 const RecordDecl *RD = RT->getDecl();
6013 if (RD->hasFlexibleArrayMember())
6014 return false;
6015
6016 // Check that all sub-fields are at offset 0, and are themselves "integer
6017 // like".
6018 const ASTRecordLayout &Layout = Context.getASTRecordLayout(RD);
6019
6020 bool HadField = false;
6021 unsigned idx = 0;
6022 for (RecordDecl::field_iterator i = RD->field_begin(), e = RD->field_end();
6023 i != e; ++i, ++idx) {
6024 const FieldDecl *FD = *i;
6025
6026 // Bit-fields are not addressable, we only need to verify they are "integer
6027 // like". We still have to disallow a subsequent non-bitfield, for example:
6028 // struct { int : 0; int x }
6029 // is non-integer like according to gcc.
6030 if (FD->isBitField()) {
6031 if (!RD->isUnion())
6032 HadField = true;
6033
6034 if (!isIntegerLikeType(FD->getType(), Context, VMContext))
6035 return false;
6036
6037 continue;
6038 }
6039
6040 // Check if this field is at offset 0.
6041 if (Layout.getFieldOffset(idx) != 0)
6042 return false;
6043
6044 if (!isIntegerLikeType(FD->getType(), Context, VMContext))
6045 return false;
6046
6047 // Only allow at most one field in a structure. This doesn't match the
6048 // wording above, but follows gcc in situations with a field following an
6049 // empty structure.
6050 if (!RD->isUnion()) {
6051 if (HadField)
6052 return false;
6053
6054 HadField = true;
6055 }
6056 }
6057
6058 return true;
6059}
6060
6061ABIArgInfo ARMABIInfo::classifyReturnType(QualType RetTy, bool isVariadic,
6062 unsigned functionCallConv) const {
6063
6064 // Variadic functions should always marshal to the base standard.
6065 bool IsAAPCS_VFP =
6066 !isVariadic && isEffectivelyAAPCS_VFP(functionCallConv, /* AAPCS16 */ true);
6067
6068 if (RetTy->isVoidType())
6069 return ABIArgInfo::getIgnore();
6070
6071 if (const VectorType *VT = RetTy->getAs<VectorType>()) {
6072 // Large vector types should be returned via memory.
6073 if (getContext().getTypeSize(RetTy) > 128)
6074 return getNaturalAlignIndirect(RetTy);
6075 // FP16 vectors should be converted to integer vectors
6076 if (!getTarget().hasLegalHalfType() &&
6077 (VT->getElementType()->isFloat16Type() ||
6078 VT->getElementType()->isHalfType()))
6079 return coerceIllegalVector(RetTy);
6080 }
6081
6082 // _Float16 and __fp16 get returned as if it were an int or float, but with
6083 // the top 16 bits unspecified. This is not done for OpenCL as it handles the
6084 // half type natively, and does not need to interwork with AAPCS code.
6085 if ((RetTy->isFloat16Type() || RetTy->isHalfType()) &&
6086 !getContext().getLangOpts().NativeHalfArgsAndReturns) {
6087 llvm::Type *ResType = IsAAPCS_VFP ?
6088 llvm::Type::getFloatTy(getVMContext()) :
6089 llvm::Type::getInt32Ty(getVMContext());
6090 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(ResType);
6091 }
6092
6093 if (!isAggregateTypeForABI(RetTy)) {
6094 // Treat an enum type as its underlying type.
6095 if (const EnumType *EnumTy = RetTy->getAs<EnumType>())
6096 RetTy = EnumTy->getDecl()->getIntegerType();
6097
6098 return RetTy->isPromotableIntegerType() ? ABIArgInfo::getExtend(RetTy)
6099 : ABIArgInfo::getDirect();
6100 }
6101
6102 // Are we following APCS?
6103 if (getABIKind() == APCS) {
6104 if (isEmptyRecord(getContext(), RetTy, false))
6105 return ABIArgInfo::getIgnore();
6106
6107 // Complex types are all returned as packed integers.
6108 //
6109 // FIXME: Consider using 2 x vector types if the back end handles them
6110 // correctly.
6111 if (RetTy->isAnyComplexType())
6112 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(llvm::IntegerType::get(
6113 getVMContext(), getContext().getTypeSize(RetTy)));
6114
6115 // Integer like structures are returned in r0.
6116 if (isIntegerLikeType(RetTy, getContext(), getVMContext())) {
6117 // Return in the smallest viable integer type.
6118 uint64_t Size = getContext().getTypeSize(RetTy);
6119 if (Size <= 8)
6120 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(llvm::Type::getInt8Ty(getVMContext()));
6121 if (Size <= 16)
6122 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(llvm::Type::getInt16Ty(getVMContext()));
6123 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(llvm::Type::getInt32Ty(getVMContext()));
6124 }
6125
6126 // Otherwise return in memory.
6127 return getNaturalAlignIndirect(RetTy);
6128 }
6129
6130 // Otherwise this is an AAPCS variant.
6131
6132 if (isEmptyRecord(getContext(), RetTy, true))
6133 return ABIArgInfo::getIgnore();
6134
6135 // Check for homogeneous aggregates with AAPCS-VFP.
6136 if (IsAAPCS_VFP) {
6137 const Type *Base = nullptr;
6138 uint64_t Members = 0;
6139 if (isHomogeneousAggregate(RetTy, Base, Members))
6140 return classifyHomogeneousAggregate(RetTy, Base, Members);
6141 }
6142
6143 // Aggregates <= 4 bytes are returned in r0; other aggregates
6144 // are returned indirectly.
6145 uint64_t Size = getContext().getTypeSize(RetTy);
6146 if (Size <= 32) {
6147 // On RenderScript, coerce Aggregates <= 4 bytes to an integer array of
6148 // same size and alignment.
6149 if (getTarget().isRenderScriptTarget()) {
6150 return coerceToIntArray(RetTy, getContext(), getVMContext());
6151 }
6152 if (getDataLayout().isBigEndian())
6153 // Return in 32 bit integer integer type (as if loaded by LDR, AAPCS 5.4)
6154 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(llvm::Type::getInt32Ty(getVMContext()));
6155
6156 // Return in the smallest viable integer type.
6157 if (Size <= 8)
6158 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(llvm::Type::getInt8Ty(getVMContext()));
6159 if (Size <= 16)
6160 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(llvm::Type::getInt16Ty(getVMContext()));
6161 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(llvm::Type::getInt32Ty(getVMContext()));
6162 } else if (Size <= 128 && getABIKind() == AAPCS16_VFP) {
6163 llvm::Type *Int32Ty = llvm::Type::getInt32Ty(getVMContext());
6164 llvm::Type *CoerceTy =
6165 llvm::ArrayType::get(Int32Ty, llvm::alignTo(Size, 32) / 32);
6166 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(CoerceTy);
6167 }
6168
6169 return getNaturalAlignIndirect(RetTy);
6170}
6171
6172/// isIllegalVector - check whether Ty is an illegal vector type.
6173bool ARMABIInfo::isIllegalVectorType(QualType Ty) const {
6174 if (const VectorType *VT = Ty->getAs<VectorType> ()) {
6175 // On targets that don't support FP16, FP16 is expanded into float, and we
6176 // don't want the ABI to depend on whether or not FP16 is supported in
6177 // hardware. Thus return false to coerce FP16 vectors into integer vectors.
6178 if (!getTarget().hasLegalHalfType() &&
6179 (VT->getElementType()->isFloat16Type() ||
6180 VT->getElementType()->isHalfType()))
6181 return true;
6182 if (isAndroid()) {
6183 // Android shipped using Clang 3.1, which supported a slightly different
6184 // vector ABI. The primary differences were that 3-element vector types
6185 // were legal, and so were sub 32-bit vectors (i.e. <2 x i8>). This path
6186 // accepts that legacy behavior for Android only.
6187 // Check whether VT is legal.
6188 unsigned NumElements = VT->getNumElements();
6189 // NumElements should be power of 2 or equal to 3.
6190 if (!llvm::isPowerOf2_32(NumElements) && NumElements != 3)
6191 return true;
6192 } else {
6193 // Check whether VT is legal.
6194 unsigned NumElements = VT->getNumElements();
6195 uint64_t Size = getContext().getTypeSize(VT);
6196 // NumElements should be power of 2.
6197 if (!llvm::isPowerOf2_32(NumElements))
6198 return true;
6199 // Size should be greater than 32 bits.
6200 return Size <= 32;
6201 }
6202 }
6203 return false;
6204}
6205
6206bool ARMABIInfo::isLegalVectorTypeForSwift(CharUnits vectorSize,
6207 llvm::Type *eltTy,
6208 unsigned numElts) const {
6209 if (!llvm::isPowerOf2_32(numElts))
6210 return false;
6211 unsigned size = getDataLayout().getTypeStoreSizeInBits(eltTy);
6212 if (size > 64)
6213 return false;
6214 if (vectorSize.getQuantity() != 8 &&
6215 (vectorSize.getQuantity() != 16 || numElts == 1))
6216 return false;
6217 return true;
6218}
6219
6220bool ARMABIInfo::isHomogeneousAggregateBaseType(QualType Ty) const {
6221 // Homogeneous aggregates for AAPCS-VFP must have base types of float,
6222 // double, or 64-bit or 128-bit vectors.
6223 if (const BuiltinType *BT = Ty->getAs<BuiltinType>()) {
6224 if (BT->getKind() == BuiltinType::Float ||
6225 BT->getKind() == BuiltinType::Double ||
6226 BT->getKind() == BuiltinType::LongDouble)
6227 return true;
6228 } else if (const VectorType *VT = Ty->getAs<VectorType>()) {
6229 unsigned VecSize = getContext().getTypeSize(VT);
6230 if (VecSize == 64 || VecSize == 128)
6231 return true;
6232 }
6233 return false;
6234}
6235
6236bool ARMABIInfo::isHomogeneousAggregateSmallEnough(const Type *Base,
6237 uint64_t Members) const {
6238 return Members <= 4;
6239}
6240
6241bool ARMABIInfo::isEffectivelyAAPCS_VFP(unsigned callConvention,
6242 bool acceptHalf) const {
6243 // Give precedence to user-specified calling conventions.
6244 if (callConvention != llvm::CallingConv::C)
6245 return (callConvention == llvm::CallingConv::ARM_AAPCS_VFP);
6246 else
6247 return (getABIKind() == AAPCS_VFP) ||
6248 (acceptHalf && (getABIKind() == AAPCS16_VFP));
6249}
6250
6251Address ARMABIInfo::EmitVAArg(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Address VAListAddr,
6252 QualType Ty) const {
6253 CharUnits SlotSize = CharUnits::fromQuantity(4);
6254
6255 // Empty records are ignored for parameter passing purposes.
6256 if (isEmptyRecord(getContext(), Ty, true)) {
6257 Address Addr(CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(VAListAddr), SlotSize);
6258 Addr = CGF.Builder.CreateElementBitCast(Addr, CGF.ConvertTypeForMem(Ty));
6259 return Addr;
6260 }
6261
6262 CharUnits TySize = getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(Ty);
6263 CharUnits TyAlignForABI = getContext().getTypeUnadjustedAlignInChars(Ty);
6264
6265 // Use indirect if size of the illegal vector is bigger than 16 bytes.
6266 bool IsIndirect = false;
6267 const Type *Base = nullptr;
6268 uint64_t Members = 0;
6269 if (TySize > CharUnits::fromQuantity(16) && isIllegalVectorType(Ty)) {
6270 IsIndirect = true;
6271
6272 // ARMv7k passes structs bigger than 16 bytes indirectly, in space
6273 // allocated by the caller.
6274 } else if (TySize > CharUnits::fromQuantity(16) &&
6275 getABIKind() == ARMABIInfo::AAPCS16_VFP &&
6276 !isHomogeneousAggregate(Ty, Base, Members)) {
6277 IsIndirect = true;
6278
6279 // Otherwise, bound the type's ABI alignment.
6280 // The ABI alignment for 64-bit or 128-bit vectors is 8 for AAPCS and 4 for
6281 // APCS. For AAPCS, the ABI alignment is at least 4-byte and at most 8-byte.
6282 // Our callers should be prepared to handle an under-aligned address.
6283 } else if (getABIKind() == ARMABIInfo::AAPCS_VFP ||
6284 getABIKind() == ARMABIInfo::AAPCS) {
6285 TyAlignForABI = std::max(TyAlignForABI, CharUnits::fromQuantity(4));
6286 TyAlignForABI = std::min(TyAlignForABI, CharUnits::fromQuantity(8));
6287 } else if (getABIKind() == ARMABIInfo::AAPCS16_VFP) {
6288 // ARMv7k allows type alignment up to 16 bytes.
6289 TyAlignForABI = std::max(TyAlignForABI, CharUnits::fromQuantity(4));
6290 TyAlignForABI = std::min(TyAlignForABI, CharUnits::fromQuantity(16));
6291 } else {
6292 TyAlignForABI = CharUnits::fromQuantity(4);
6293 }
6294
6295 std::pair<CharUnits, CharUnits> TyInfo = { TySize, TyAlignForABI };
6296 return emitVoidPtrVAArg(CGF, VAListAddr, Ty, IsIndirect, TyInfo,
6297 SlotSize, /*AllowHigherAlign*/ true);
6298}

6304namespace {

6306class NVPTXABIInfo : public ABIInfo {
6307public:
6308 NVPTXABIInfo(CodeGenTypes &CGT) : ABIInfo(CGT) {}
6309
6310 ABIArgInfo classifyReturnType(QualType RetTy) const;
6311 ABIArgInfo classifyArgumentType(QualType Ty) const;
6312
6313 void computeInfo(CGFunctionInfo &FI) const override;
6314 Address EmitVAArg(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Address VAListAddr,
6315 QualType Ty) const override;
6316};
6317
6318class NVPTXTargetCodeGenInfo : public TargetCodeGenInfo {
6319public:
6320 NVPTXTargetCodeGenInfo(CodeGenTypes &CGT)
6321 : TargetCodeGenInfo(new NVPTXABIInfo(CGT)) {}
6322
6323 void setTargetAttributes(const Decl *D, llvm::GlobalValue *GV,
6324 CodeGen::CodeGenModule &M) const override;
6325 bool shouldEmitStaticExternCAliases() const override;
6326
6327private:
6328 // Adds a NamedMDNode with F, Name, and Operand as operands, and adds the
6329 // resulting MDNode to the nvvm.annotations MDNode.
6330 static void addNVVMMetadata(llvm::Function *F, StringRef Name, int Operand);
6331};
6332
6333/// Checks if the type is unsupported directly by the current target.
6334static bool isUnsupportedType(ASTContext &Context, QualType T) {
6335 if (!Context.getTargetInfo().hasFloat16Type() && T->isFloat16Type())
6336 return true;
6337 if (!Context.getTargetInfo().hasFloat128Type() && T->isFloat128Type())
6338 return true;
6339 if (!Context.getTargetInfo().hasInt128Type() && T->isIntegerType() &&
6340 Context.getTypeSize(T) > 64)
6341 return true;
6342 if (const auto *AT = T->getAsArrayTypeUnsafe())
6343 return isUnsupportedType(Context, AT->getElementType());
6344 const auto *RT = T->getAs<RecordType>();
6345 if (!RT)
6346 return false;
6347 const RecordDecl *RD = RT->getDecl();
6348
6349 // If this is a C++ record, check the bases first.
6350 if (const CXXRecordDecl *CXXRD = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RD))
6351 for (const CXXBaseSpecifier &I : CXXRD->bases())
6352 if (isUnsupportedType(Context, I.getType()))
6353 return true;
6354
6355 for (const FieldDecl *I : RD->fields())
6356 if (isUnsupportedType(Context, I->getType()))
6357 return true;
6358 return false;
6359}
6360
6361/// Coerce the given type into an array with maximum allowed size of elements.
6362static ABIArgInfo coerceToIntArrayWithLimit(QualType Ty, ASTContext &Context,
6363 llvm::LLVMContext &LLVMContext,
6364 unsigned MaxSize) {
6365 // Alignment and Size are measured in bits.
6366 const uint64_t Size = Context.getTypeSize(Ty);
6367 const uint64_t Alignment = Context.getTypeAlign(Ty);
6368 const unsigned Div = std::min<unsigned>(MaxSize, Alignment);
6369 llvm::Type *IntType = llvm::Type::getIntNTy(LLVMContext, Div);
6370 const uint64_t NumElements = (Size + Div - 1) / Div;
6371 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(llvm::ArrayType::get(IntType, NumElements));
6372}
6373
6374ABIArgInfo NVPTXABIInfo::classifyReturnType(QualType RetTy) const {
6375 if (RetTy->isVoidType())
6376 return ABIArgInfo::getIgnore();
6377
6378 if (getContext().getLangOpts().OpenMP &&
6379 getContext().getLangOpts().OpenMPIsDevice &&
6380 isUnsupportedType(getContext(), RetTy))
6381 return coerceToIntArrayWithLimit(RetTy, getContext(), getVMContext(), 64);
6382
6383 // note: this is different from default ABI
6384 if (!RetTy->isScalarType())
6385 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect();
6386
6387 // Treat an enum type as its underlying type.
6388 if (const EnumType *EnumTy = RetTy->getAs<EnumType>())
6389 RetTy = EnumTy->getDecl()->getIntegerType();
6390
6391 return (RetTy->isPromotableIntegerType() ? ABIArgInfo::getExtend(RetTy)
6392 : ABIArgInfo::getDirect());
6393}
6394
6395ABIArgInfo NVPTXABIInfo::classifyArgumentType(QualType Ty) const {
6396 // Treat an enum type as its underlying type.
6397 if (const EnumType *EnumTy = Ty->getAs<EnumType>())
6398 Ty = EnumTy->getDecl()->getIntegerType();
6399
6400 // Return aggregates type as indirect by value
6401 if (isAggregateTypeForABI(Ty))
6402 return getNaturalAlignIndirect(Ty, /* byval */ true);
6403
6404 return (Ty->isPromotableIntegerType() ? ABIArgInfo::getExtend(Ty)
6405 : ABIArgInfo::getDirect());
6406}
6407
6408void NVPTXABIInfo::computeInfo(CGFunctionInfo &FI) const {
6409 if (!getCXXABI().classifyReturnType(FI))
6410 FI.getReturnInfo() = classifyReturnType(FI.getReturnType());
6411 for (auto &I : FI.arguments())
6412 I.info = classifyArgumentType(I.type);
6413
6414 // Always honor user-specified calling convention.
6415 if (FI.getCallingConvention() != llvm::CallingConv::C)
6416 return;
6417
6418 FI.setEffectiveCallingConvention(getRuntimeCC());
6419}
6420
6421Address NVPTXABIInfo::EmitVAArg(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Address VAListAddr,
6422 QualType Ty) const {
6423 llvm_unreachable("NVPTX does not support varargs");
6424}
6425
6426void NVPTXTargetCodeGenInfo::setTargetAttributes(
6427 const Decl *D, llvm::GlobalValue *GV, CodeGen::CodeGenModule &M) const {
6428 if (GV->isDeclaration())
6429 return;
6430 const FunctionDecl *FD = dyn_cast_or_null<FunctionDecl>(D);
6431 if (!FD) return;
6432
6433 llvm::Function *F = cast<llvm::Function>(GV);
6434
6435 // Perform special handling in OpenCL mode
6436 if (M.getLangOpts().OpenCL) {
6437 // Use OpenCL function attributes to check for kernel functions
6438 // By default, all functions are device functions
6439 if (FD->hasAttr<OpenCLKernelAttr>()) {
6440 // OpenCL __kernel functions get kernel metadata
6441 // Create !{<func-ref>, metadata !"kernel", i32 1} node
6442 addNVVMMetadata(F, "kernel", 1);
6443 // And kernel functions are not subject to inlining
6444 F->addFnAttr(llvm::Attribute::NoInline);
6445 }
6446 }
6447
6448 // Perform special handling in CUDA mode.
6449 if (M.getLangOpts().CUDA) {
6450 // CUDA __global__ functions get a kernel metadata entry. Since
6451 // __global__ functions cannot be called from the device, we do not
6452 // need to set the noinline attribute.
6453 if (FD->hasAttr<CUDAGlobalAttr>()) {
6454 // Create !{<func-ref>, metadata !"kernel", i32 1} node
6455 addNVVMMetadata(F, "kernel", 1);
6456 }
6457 if (CUDALaunchBoundsAttr *Attr = FD->getAttr<CUDALaunchBoundsAttr>()) {
6458 // Create !{<func-ref>, metadata !"maxntidx", i32 <val>} node
6459 llvm::APSInt MaxThreads(32);
6460 MaxThreads = Attr->getMaxThreads()->EvaluateKnownConstInt(M.getContext());
6461 if (MaxThreads > 0)
6462 addNVVMMetadata(F, "maxntidx", MaxThreads.getExtValue());
6463
6464 // min blocks is an optional argument for CUDALaunchBoundsAttr. If it was
6465 // not specified in __launch_bounds__ or if the user specified a 0 value,
6466 // we don't have to add a PTX directive.
6467 if (Attr->getMinBlocks()) {
6468 llvm::APSInt MinBlocks(32);
6469 MinBlocks = Attr->getMinBlocks()->EvaluateKnownConstInt(M.getContext());
6470 if (MinBlocks > 0)
6471 // Create !{<func-ref>, metadata !"minctasm", i32 <val>} node
6472 addNVVMMetadata(F, "minctasm", MinBlocks.getExtValue());
6473 }
6474 }
6475 }
6476}
6477
6478void NVPTXTargetCodeGenInfo::addNVVMMetadata(llvm::Function *F, StringRef Name,
6479 int Operand) {
6480 llvm::Module *M = F->getParent();
6481 llvm::LLVMContext &Ctx = M->getContext();
6482
6483 // Get "nvvm.annotations" metadata node
6484 llvm::NamedMDNode *MD = M->getOrInsertNamedMetadata("nvvm.annotations");
6485
6486 llvm::Metadata *MDVals[] = {
6487 llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(F), llvm::MDString::get(Ctx, Name),
6488 llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(
6489 llvm::ConstantInt::get(llvm::Type::getInt32Ty(Ctx), Operand))};
6490 // Append metadata to nvvm.annotations
6491 MD->addOperand(llvm::MDNode::get(Ctx, MDVals));
6492}
6493
6494bool NVPTXTargetCodeGenInfo::shouldEmitStaticExternCAliases() const {
6495 return false;
6496}
6497}

6505class SystemZABIInfo : public SwiftABIInfo {

6513 bool isCompoundType(QualType Ty) const;

6519 ABIArgInfo classifyArgumentType(QualType ArgTy) const;

6529 QualType Ty) const override;

6536 return false;

6539
6540class SystemZTargetCodeGenInfo : public TargetCodeGenInfo {
6541public:
6542 SystemZTargetCodeGenInfo(CodeGenTypes &CGT, bool HasVector)
6543 : TargetCodeGenInfo(new SystemZABIInfo(CGT, HasVector)) {}
6544};

6546}
6547
6548bool SystemZABIInfo::isPromotableIntegerType(QualType Ty) const {
6549 // Treat an enum type as its underlying type.
6550 if (const EnumType *EnumTy = Ty->getAs<EnumType>())
6551 Ty = EnumTy->getDecl()->getIntegerType();
6552
6553 // Promotable integer types are required to be promoted by the ABI.
6554 if (Ty->isPromotableIntegerType())
6555 return true;
6556
6557 // 32-bit values must also be promoted.
6558 if (const BuiltinType *BT = Ty->getAs<BuiltinType>())
6559 switch (BT->getKind()) {
6560 case BuiltinType::Int:
6561 case BuiltinType::UInt:
6562 return true;
6563 default:
6564 return false;
6565 }
6566 return false;
6567}
6568
6569bool SystemZABIInfo::isCompoundType(QualType Ty) const {
6570 return (Ty->isAnyComplexType() ||
6571 Ty->isVectorType() ||
6572 isAggregateTypeForABI(Ty));
6573}
6574
6575bool SystemZABIInfo::isVectorArgumentType(QualType Ty) const {
6576 return (HasVector &&
6577 Ty->isVectorType() &&
6578 getContext().getTypeSize(Ty) <= 128);
6579}
6580
6581bool SystemZABIInfo::isFPArgumentType(QualType Ty) const {
6582 if (const BuiltinType *BT = Ty->getAs<BuiltinType>())
6583 switch (BT->getKind()) {
6584 case BuiltinType::Float:
6585 case BuiltinType::Double:
6586 return true;
6587 default:
6588 return false;
6589 }
6590
6591 return false;
6592}
6593
6594QualType SystemZABIInfo::GetSingleElementType(QualType Ty) const {
6595 if (const RecordType *RT = Ty->getAsStructureType()) {
6596 const RecordDecl *RD = RT->getDecl();
6597 QualType Found;
6598
6599 // If this is a C++ record, check the bases first.
6600 if (const CXXRecordDecl *CXXRD = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RD))
6601 for (const auto &I : CXXRD->bases()) {
6602 QualType Base = I.getType();
6603
6604 // Empty bases don't affect things either way.
6605 if (isEmptyRecord(getContext(), Base, true))
6606 continue;
6607
6608 if (!Found.isNull())
6609 return Ty;
6610 Found = GetSingleElementType(Base);
6611 }
6612
6613 // Check the fields.
6614 for (const auto *FD : RD->fields()) {
6615 // For compatibility with GCC, ignore empty bitfields in C++ mode.
6616 // Unlike isSingleElementStruct(), empty structure and array fields
6617 // do count. So do anonymous bitfields that aren't zero-sized.
6618 if (getContext().getLangOpts().CPlusPlus &&
6619 FD->isZeroLengthBitField(getContext()))
6620 continue;
6621
6622 // Unlike isSingleElementStruct(), arrays do not count.
6623 // Nested structures still do though.
6624 if (!Found.isNull())
6625 return Ty;
6626 Found = GetSingleElementType(FD->getType());
6627 }
6628
6629 // Unlike isSingleElementStruct(), trailing padding is allowed.
6630 // An 8-byte aligned struct s { float f; } is passed as a double.
6631 if (!Found.isNull())
6632 return Found;
6633 }
6634
6635 return Ty;
6636}
6637
6638Address SystemZABIInfo::EmitVAArg(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Address VAListAddr,
6639 QualType Ty) const {
6640 // Assume that va_list type is correct; should be pointer to LLVM type:
6641 // struct {
6642 // i64 __gpr;
6643 // i64 __fpr;
6644 // i8 *__overflow_arg_area;
6645 // i8 *__reg_save_area;
6646 // };
6647
6648 // Every non-vector argument occupies 8 bytes and is passed by preference
6649 // in either GPRs or FPRs. Vector arguments occupy 8 or 16 bytes and are
6650 // always passed on the stack.
6651 Ty = getContext().getCanonicalType(Ty);
6652 auto TyInfo = getContext().getTypeInfoInChars(Ty);
6653 llvm::Type *ArgTy = CGF.ConvertTypeForMem(Ty);
6654 llvm::Type *DirectTy = ArgTy;
6655 ABIArgInfo AI = classifyArgumentType(Ty);
6656 bool IsIndirect = AI.isIndirect();
6657 bool InFPRs = false;
6658 bool IsVector = false;
6659 CharUnits UnpaddedSize;
6660 CharUnits DirectAlign;
6661 if (IsIndirect) {
6662 DirectTy = CGF.CGM.getPointerInDefaultAS(DirectTy);
6663 UnpaddedSize = DirectAlign = CharUnits::fromQuantity(8);
6664 } else {
6665 if (AI.getCoerceToType())
6666 ArgTy = AI.getCoerceToType();
6667 InFPRs = ArgTy->isFloatTy() || ArgTy->isDoubleTy();
6668 IsVector = ArgTy->isVectorTy();
6669 UnpaddedSize = TyInfo.first;
6670 DirectAlign = TyInfo.second;
6671 }
6672 CharUnits PaddedSize = CharUnits::fromQuantity(8);
6673 if (IsVector && UnpaddedSize > PaddedSize)
6674 PaddedSize = CharUnits::fromQuantity(16);
6675 assert((UnpaddedSize <= PaddedSize) && "Invalid argument size.");
6676
6677 CharUnits Padding = (PaddedSize - UnpaddedSize);
6678
6679 llvm::Type *IndexTy = CGF.Int64Ty;
6680 llvm::Value *PaddedSizeV =
6681 llvm::ConstantInt::get(IndexTy, PaddedSize.getQuantity());
6682
6683 if (IsVector) {
6684 // Work out the address of a vector argument on the stack.
6685 // Vector arguments are always passed in the high bits of a
6686 // single (8 byte) or double (16 byte) stack slot.
6687 Address OverflowArgAreaPtr =
6688 CGF.Builder.CreateStructGEP(VAListAddr, 2, "overflow_arg_area_ptr");
6689 Address OverflowArgArea =
6690 Address(CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(OverflowArgAreaPtr, "overflow_arg_area"),
6691 TyInfo.second);
6692 Address MemAddr =
6693 CGF.Builder.CreateElementBitCast(OverflowArgArea, DirectTy, "mem_addr");
6694
6695 // Update overflow_arg_area_ptr pointer
6696 llvm::Value *NewOverflowArgArea =
6697 CGF.Builder.CreateGEP(OverflowArgArea.getPointer(), PaddedSizeV,
6698 "overflow_arg_area");
6699 CGF.Builder.CreateStore(NewOverflowArgArea, OverflowArgAreaPtr);
6700
6701 return MemAddr;
6702 }
6703
6704 assert(PaddedSize.getQuantity() == 8);
6705
6706 unsigned MaxRegs, RegCountField, RegSaveIndex;
6707 CharUnits RegPadding;
6708 if (InFPRs) {
6709 MaxRegs = 4; // Maximum of 4 FPR arguments
6710 RegCountField = 1; // __fpr
6711 RegSaveIndex = 16; // save offset for f0
6712 RegPadding = CharUnits(); // floats are passed in the high bits of an FPR
6713 } else {
6714 MaxRegs = 5; // Maximum of 5 GPR arguments
6715 RegCountField = 0; // __gpr
6716 RegSaveIndex = 2; // save offset for r2
6717 RegPadding = Padding; // values are passed in the low bits of a GPR
6718 }
6719
6720 Address RegCountPtr =
6721 CGF.Builder.CreateStructGEP(VAListAddr, RegCountField, "reg_count_ptr");
6722 llvm::Value *RegCount = CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(RegCountPtr, "reg_count");
6723 llvm::Value *MaxRegsV = llvm::ConstantInt::get(IndexTy, MaxRegs);
6724 llvm::Value *InRegs = CGF.Builder.CreateICmpULT(RegCount, MaxRegsV,
6725 "fits_in_regs");
6726
6727 llvm::BasicBlock *InRegBlock = CGF.createBasicBlock("vaarg.in_reg");
6728 llvm::BasicBlock *InMemBlock = CGF.createBasicBlock("vaarg.in_mem");
6729 llvm::BasicBlock *ContBlock = CGF.createBasicBlock("vaarg.end");
6730 CGF.Builder.CreateCondBr(InRegs, InRegBlock, InMemBlock);
6731
6732 // Emit code to load the value if it was passed in registers.
6733 CGF.EmitBlock(InRegBlock);
6734
6735 // Work out the address of an argument register.
6736 llvm::Value *ScaledRegCount =
6737 CGF.Builder.CreateMul(RegCount, PaddedSizeV, "scaled_reg_count");
6738 llvm::Value *RegBase =
6739 llvm::ConstantInt::get(IndexTy, RegSaveIndex * PaddedSize.getQuantity()
6740 + RegPadding.getQuantity());
6741 llvm::Value *RegOffset =
6742 CGF.Builder.CreateAdd(ScaledRegCount, RegBase, "reg_offset");
6743 Address RegSaveAreaPtr =
6744 CGF.Builder.CreateStructGEP(VAListAddr, 3, "reg_save_area_ptr");
6745 llvm::Value *RegSaveArea =
6746 CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(RegSaveAreaPtr, "reg_save_area");
6747 Address RawRegAddr(CGF.Builder.CreateGEP(RegSaveArea, RegOffset,
6748 "raw_reg_addr"),
6749 PaddedSize);
6750 Address RegAddr =
6751 CGF.Builder.CreateElementBitCast(RawRegAddr, DirectTy, "reg_addr");
6752
6753 // Update the register count
6754 llvm::Value *One = llvm::ConstantInt::get(IndexTy, 1);
6755 llvm::Value *NewRegCount =
6756 CGF.Builder.CreateAdd(RegCount, One, "reg_count");
6757 CGF.Builder.CreateStore(NewRegCount, RegCountPtr);
6758 CGF.EmitBranch(ContBlock);
6759
6760 // Emit code to load the value if it was passed in memory.
6761 CGF.EmitBlock(InMemBlock);
6762
6763 // Work out the address of a stack argument.
6764 Address OverflowArgAreaPtr =
6765 CGF.Builder.CreateStructGEP(VAListAddr, 2, "overflow_arg_area_ptr");
6766 Address OverflowArgArea =
6767 Address(CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(OverflowArgAreaPtr, "overflow_arg_area"),
6768 PaddedSize);
6769 Address RawMemAddr =
6770 CGF.Builder.CreateConstByteGEP(OverflowArgArea, Padding, "raw_mem_addr");
6771 Address MemAddr =
6772 CGF.Builder.CreateElementBitCast(RawMemAddr, DirectTy, "mem_addr");
6773
6774 // Update overflow_arg_area_ptr pointer
6775 llvm::Value *NewOverflowArgArea =
6776 CGF.Builder.CreateGEP(OverflowArgArea.getPointer(), PaddedSizeV,
6777 "overflow_arg_area");
6778 CGF.Builder.CreateStore(NewOverflowArgArea, OverflowArgAreaPtr);
6779 CGF.EmitBranch(ContBlock);
6780
6781 // Return the appropriate result.
6782 CGF.EmitBlock(ContBlock);
6783 Address ResAddr = emitMergePHI(CGF, RegAddr, InRegBlock,
6784 MemAddr, InMemBlock, "va_arg.addr");
6785
6786 if (IsIndirect)
6787 ResAddr = Address(CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(ResAddr, "indirect_arg"),
6788 TyInfo.second);
6789
6790 return ResAddr;
6791}
6792
6793ABIArgInfo SystemZABIInfo::classifyReturnType(QualType RetTy) const {
6794 if (RetTy->isVoidType())
6795 return ABIArgInfo::getIgnore();
6796 if (isVectorArgumentType(RetTy))
6797 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect();
6798 if (isCompoundType(RetTy) || getContext().getTypeSize(RetTy) > 64)
6799 return getNaturalAlignIndirect(RetTy);
6800 return (isPromotableIntegerType(RetTy) ? ABIArgInfo::getExtend(RetTy)
6801 : ABIArgInfo::getDirect());
6802}
6803
6804ABIArgInfo SystemZABIInfo::classifyArgumentType(QualType Ty) const {
6805 // Handle the generic C++ ABI.
6806 if (CGCXXABI::RecordArgABI RAA = getRecordArgABI(Ty, getCXXABI()))
6807 return getNaturalAlignIndirect(Ty, RAA == CGCXXABI::RAA_DirectInMemory);
6808
6809 // Integers and enums are extended to full register width.
6810 if (isPromotableIntegerType(Ty))
6811 return ABIArgInfo::getExtend(Ty);
6812
6813 // Handle vector types and vector-like structure types. Note that
6814 // as opposed to float-like structure types, we do not allow any
6815 // padding for vector-like structures, so verify the sizes match.
6816 uint64_t Size = getContext().getTypeSize(Ty);
6817 QualType SingleElementTy = GetSingleElementType(Ty);
6818 if (isVectorArgumentType(SingleElementTy) &&
6819 getContext().getTypeSize(SingleElementTy) == Size)
6820 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(CGT.ConvertType(SingleElementTy));
6821
6822 // Values that are not 1, 2, 4 or 8 bytes in size are passed indirectly.
6823 if (Size != 8 && Size != 16 && Size != 32 && Size != 64)
6824 return getNaturalAlignIndirect(Ty, /*ByVal=*/false);
6825
6826 // Handle small structures.
6827 if (const RecordType *RT = Ty->getAs<RecordType>()) {
6828 // Structures with flexible arrays have variable length, so really
6829 // fail the size test above.
6830 const RecordDecl *RD = RT->getDecl();
6831 if (RD->hasFlexibleArrayMember())
6832 return getNaturalAlignIndirect(Ty, /*ByVal=*/false);
6833
6834 // The structure is passed as an unextended integer, a float, or a double.
6835 llvm::Type *PassTy;
6836 if (isFPArgumentType(SingleElementTy)) {
6837 assert(Size == 32 || Size == 64);
6838 if (Size == 32)
6839 PassTy = llvm::Type::getFloatTy(getVMContext());
6840 else
6841 PassTy = llvm::Type::getDoubleTy(getVMContext());
6842 } else
6843 PassTy = llvm::IntegerType::get(getVMContext(), Size);
6844 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(PassTy);
6845 }
6846
6847 // Non-structure compounds are passed indirectly.
6848 if (isCompoundType(Ty))
6849 return getNaturalAlignIndirect(Ty, /*ByVal=*/false);
6850
6851 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(nullptr);
6852}
6853
6854//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
6855// MSP430 ABI Implementation
6856//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
6857
6858namespace {
6859
6860class MSP430TargetCodeGenInfo : public TargetCodeGenInfo {
6861public:
6862 MSP430TargetCodeGenInfo(CodeGenTypes &CGT)
6863 : TargetCodeGenInfo(new DefaultABIInfo(CGT)) {}
6864 void setTargetAttributes(const Decl *D, llvm::GlobalValue *GV,
6865 CodeGen::CodeGenModule &M) const override;
6866};
6867
6868}
6869
6870void MSP430TargetCodeGenInfo::setTargetAttributes(
6871 const Decl *D, llvm::GlobalValue *GV, CodeGen::CodeGenModule &M) const {
6872 if (GV->isDeclaration())
6873 return;
6874 if (const FunctionDecl *FD = dyn_cast_or_null<FunctionDecl>(D)) {
6875 const auto *InterruptAttr = FD->getAttr<MSP430InterruptAttr>();
6876 if (!InterruptAttr)
6877 return;
6878
6879 // Handle 'interrupt' attribute:
6880 llvm::Function *F = cast<llvm::Function>(GV);
6881
6882 // Step 1: Set ISR calling convention.
6883 F->setCallingConv(llvm::CallingConv::MSP430_INTR);
6884
6885 // Step 2: Add attributes goodness.
6886 F->addFnAttr(llvm::Attribute::NoInline);
6887 F->addFnAttr("interrupt", llvm::utostr(InterruptAttr->getNumber()));
6888 }
6889}

6891//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
6892// MIPS ABI Implementation. This works for both little-endian and
6893// big-endian variants.
6894//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//

6896namespace {

6898
6899class MipsABIInfo : public ABIInfo {
6900 bool IsO32;
6901 CodeGenModule &CGM;
6902 unsigned MinABIStackAlignInBytes, StackAlignInBytes;
6903 void CoerceToIntArgs(uint64_t TySize,
6904 SmallVectorImpl<llvm::Type *> &ArgList) const;
6905 llvm::Type* HandleAggregates(QualType Ty, uint64_t TySize) const;
6906 llvm::Type* returnAggregateInRegs(QualType RetTy, uint64_t Size) const;
6907 llvm::Type* getPaddingType(uint64_t Align, uint64_t Offset) const;
6908public:
6909 MipsABIInfo(CodeGenTypes &CGT, bool _IsO32, CodeGenModule &_CGM) :
6910 ABIInfo(CGT),
6911 IsO32(_IsO32), CGM(_CGM), MinABIStackAlignInBytes(IsO32 ? 4 : 8) {
6912 const TargetInfo& TI = _CGM.getTarget();
6913 if (TI.areAllPointersCapabilities())
6914 StackAlignInBytes = TI.getCHERICapabilityWidth();
6915 else
6916 StackAlignInBytes = (IsO32 ? 8 : 16);
6917 }
6918
6919 ABIArgInfo classifyReturnType(QualType RetTy) const;
6920 ABIArgInfo classifyArgumentType(QualType RetTy, uint64_t &Offset) const;
6921 void computeInfo(CGFunctionInfo &FI) const override;
6922 Address EmitVAArg(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Address VAListAddr,
6923 QualType Ty) const override;
6924 ABIArgInfo extendType(QualType Ty) const;
6925};
6926
6927class MIPSTargetCodeGenInfo : public TargetCodeGenInfo {
6928 unsigned SizeOfUnwindException;
6929 mutable llvm::Function *GetOffset = nullptr;
6930 mutable llvm::Function *SetOffset = nullptr;
6931 mutable llvm::Function *SetAddr = nullptr;
6932 mutable llvm::Function *GetBase = nullptr;
6933 mutable llvm::Function *GetAddress = nullptr;
6934 mutable llvm::Function *SetBounds = nullptr;
6935 mutable llvm::PointerType *I8Cap = nullptr;
6936 llvm::PointerType *getI8CapTy(CodeGen::CodeGenFunction &CGF) const {
6937 if (!I8Cap)
6938 I8Cap = llvm::PointerType::get(CGF.Int8Ty, getCHERICapabilityAS());
6939 return I8Cap;
6940 }
6941public:
6942 MIPSTargetCodeGenInfo(CodeGenTypes &CGT, bool IsO32, CodeGenModule &CGM)
6943 : TargetCodeGenInfo(new MipsABIInfo(CGT, IsO32, CGM)),
6944 SizeOfUnwindException(IsO32 ? 24 : 32) {}
6945
6946 int getDwarfEHStackPointer(CodeGen::CodeGenModule &CGM) const override {
6947 return 29;
6948 }
6949
6950 llvm::Value *getPointerOffset(CodeGen::CodeGenFunction &CGF,
6951 llvm::Value *V) const override {
6952 if (!GetOffset)
6953 GetOffset = CGF.CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::cheri_cap_offset_get,
6954 CGF.SizeTy);
6955 V = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(V, getI8CapTy(CGF));
6956 return CGF.Builder.CreateCall(GetOffset, V);
6957 }
6958
6959 llvm::Value *setPointerOffset(CodeGen::CodeGenFunction &CGF,
6960 llvm::Value *Ptr, llvm::Value *Offset) const override {
6961 if (!SetOffset)
6962 SetOffset = CGF.CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::cheri_cap_offset_set,
6963 CGF.SizeTy);
6964 llvm::Type *DstTy = Ptr->getType();
6965 auto &B = CGF.Builder;
6966 Ptr = B.CreateBitCast(Ptr, getI8CapTy(CGF));
6967 return B.CreateBitCast(B.CreateCall(SetOffset, {Ptr, Offset}), DstTy);
6968 }
6969
6970 llvm::Value *setPointerAddress(CodeGen::CodeGenFunction &CGF,
6971 llvm::Value *Ptr,
6972 llvm::Value *Offset) const override {
6973 if (!SetAddr)
6974 SetAddr = CGF.CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::cheri_cap_address_set,
6975 CGF.IntPtrTy);
6976 llvm::Type *DstTy = Ptr->getType();
6977 auto &B = CGF.Builder;
6978 Ptr = B.CreateBitCast(Ptr, getI8CapTy(CGF));
6979 return B.CreateBitCast(B.CreateCall(SetAddr, {Ptr, Offset}), DstTy);
6980 }
6981
6982 llvm::Value *setPointerBounds(CodeGen::CodeGenFunction &CGF, llvm::Value *Ptr,
6983 llvm::Value *Size,
6984 const llvm::Twine &Name) const override {
6985 if (!SetBounds)
6986 SetBounds = CGF.CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::cheri_cap_bounds_set,
6987 CGF.SizeTy);
6988 llvm::Type *DstTy = Ptr->getType();
6989 auto &B = CGF.Builder;
6990 Ptr = B.CreateBitCast(Ptr, getI8CapTy(CGF));
6991 return B.CreateBitCast(B.CreateCall(SetBounds, {Ptr, Size}), DstTy, Name);
6992 }
6993
6994 llvm::Value *getPointerBase(CodeGen::CodeGenFunction &CGF,
6995 llvm::Value *V) const override {
6996 if (!GetBase)
6997 GetBase = CGF.CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::cheri_cap_base_get,
6998 CGF.IntPtrTy);
6999 V = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(V, getI8CapTy(CGF));
7000 return CGF.Builder.CreateCall(GetBase, V);
7001 }
7002
7003 llvm::Value *getPointerAddress(CodeGen::CodeGenFunction &CGF, llvm::Value *V,
7004 const llvm::Twine &Name) const override {
7005 if (!GetAddress)
7006 GetAddress = CGF.CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::cheri_cap_address_get,
7007 CGF.IntPtrTy);
7008 V = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(V, getI8CapTy(CGF));
7009 return CGF.Builder.CreateCall(GetAddress, V, Name);
7010 }
7011
7012 void setTargetAttributes(const Decl *D, llvm::GlobalValue *GV,
7013 CodeGen::CodeGenModule &CGM) const override {
7014 const FunctionDecl *FD = dyn_cast_or_null<FunctionDecl>(D);
7015 if (!FD) return;
7016 llvm::Function *Fn = cast<llvm::Function>(GV);
7017
7018 if (FD->hasAttr<MipsLongCallAttr>())
7019 Fn->addFnAttr("long-call");
7020 else if (FD->hasAttr<MipsShortCallAttr>())
7021 Fn->addFnAttr("short-call");
7022
7023 // Other attributes do not have a meaning for declarations.
7024 if (GV->isDeclaration())
7025 return;
7026
7027 if (FD->hasAttr<Mips16Attr>()) {
7028 Fn->addFnAttr("mips16");
7029 }
7030 else if (FD->hasAttr<NoMips16Attr>()) {
7031 Fn->addFnAttr("nomips16");
7032 }
7033
7034 if (FD->hasAttr<MicroMipsAttr>())
7035 Fn->addFnAttr("micromips");
7036 else if (FD->hasAttr<NoMicroMipsAttr>())
7037 Fn->addFnAttr("nomicromips");
7038
7039 const MipsInterruptAttr *Attr = FD->getAttr<MipsInterruptAttr>();
7040 if (!Attr)
7041 return;
7042
7043 const char *Kind;
7044 switch (Attr->getInterrupt()) {
7045 case MipsInterruptAttr::eic: Kind = "eic"; break;
7046 case MipsInterruptAttr::sw0: Kind = "sw0"; break;
7047 case MipsInterruptAttr::sw1: Kind = "sw1"; break;
7048 case MipsInterruptAttr::hw0: Kind = "hw0"; break;
7049 case MipsInterruptAttr::hw1: Kind = "hw1"; break;
7050 case MipsInterruptAttr::hw2: Kind = "hw2"; break;
7051 case MipsInterruptAttr::hw3: Kind = "hw3"; break;
7052 case MipsInterruptAttr::hw4: Kind = "hw4"; break;
7053 case MipsInterruptAttr::hw5: Kind = "hw5"; break;
7054 }
7055
7056 Fn->addFnAttr("interrupt", Kind);
7057
7058 }
7059
7060 bool initDwarfEHRegSizeTable(CodeGen::CodeGenFunction &CGF,
7061 llvm::Value *Address) const override;
7062
7063 unsigned getSizeOfUnwindException() const override {
7064 return SizeOfUnwindException;
7065 }
7066
7067 unsigned getDefaultAS() const override {
7068 const TargetInfo &Target = getABIInfo().getContext().getTargetInfo();
7069 return Target.areAllPointersCapabilities() ? getCHERICapabilityAS() : 0;
7070 }
7071 unsigned getTlsAddressSpace() const override {
7072 const TargetInfo &Target = getABIInfo().getContext().getTargetInfo();
7073 if (Target.areAllPointersCapabilities()) {
7074 // For the legacy ABI we still need rdhwr29 for TLS (which is AS0)
7075 if (!llvm::MCTargetOptions::cheriUsesCapabilityTls())
7076 return 0;
7077 return getCHERICapabilityAS();
7078 }
7079 return getDefaultAS();
7080 }
7081 unsigned getCHERICapabilityAS() const override {
7082 return 200;
7083 }
7084
7085 bool cheriCapabilityAtomicNeedsLibcall(AtomicExpr::AtomicOp Op) const override {
7086 switch (Op) {
7087 case AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_init:
7088 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_load:
7089 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_load_n:
7090 case AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_load:
7091 case AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_store:
7092 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_store:
7093 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_store_n:
7094 case AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_exchange:
7095 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_exchange:
7096 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_exchange_n:
7097 case AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_compare_exchange_strong:
7098 case AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_compare_exchange_weak:
7099 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_compare_exchange:
7100 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_compare_exchange_n:
7101 return false;
7102 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_fetch_add:
7103 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_fetch_sub:
7104 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_add_fetch:
7105 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_sub_fetch:
7106 case AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_fetch_add:
7107 case AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_fetch_sub:
7108 return true; // TODO: allow emitting this without a libcall
7109
7110 default:
7111 llvm_unreachable("Atomic op should not be supported for capabilities");
7112 return true;
7113 }
7114 }
7115};
7116}
7117
7118void MipsABIInfo::CoerceToIntArgs(
7119 uint64_t TySize, SmallVectorImpl<llvm::Type *> &ArgList) const {
7120 llvm::IntegerType *IntTy =
7121 llvm::IntegerType::get(getVMContext(), MinABIStackAlignInBytes * 8);
7122
7123 // Add (TySize / MinABIStackAlignInBytes) args of IntTy.
7124 for (unsigned N = TySize / (MinABIStackAlignInBytes * 8); N; --N)
7125 ArgList.push_back(IntTy);
7126
7127 // If necessary, add one more integer type to ArgList.
7128 unsigned R = TySize % (MinABIStackAlignInBytes * 8);
7129
7130 if (R)
7131 ArgList.push_back(llvm::IntegerType::get(getVMContext(), R));
7132}
7133
7134// In N32/64, an aligned double precision floating point field is passed in
7135// a register.
7136llvm::Type* MipsABIInfo::HandleAggregates(QualType Ty, uint64_t TySize) const {
7137 SmallVector<llvm::Type*, 8> ArgList, IntArgList;
7138
7139 if (IsO32) {
7140 CoerceToIntArgs(TySize, ArgList);
7141 return llvm::StructType::get(getVMContext(), ArgList);
7142 }
7143
7144 if (Ty->isComplexType())
7145 return CGT.ConvertType(Ty);
7146
7147 const RecordType *RT = Ty->getAs<RecordType>();
7148
7149 // On CHERI, we must pass unions containing capabilities in capability
7150 // registers. Otherwise, pass them as integers.
7151 if (RT &&
7152 (RT->isUnionType() && getContext().containsCapabilities(RT->getDecl()))
7153 && getTarget().SupportsCapabilities())
7154 return llvm::Type::getInt8Ty(getVMContext())->getPointerTo(
7155 CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getCHERICapabilityAS());
7156
7157 // Unions/vectors are passed in integer registers.
7158 if (!RT || !RT->isStructureOrClassType()) {
7159 const TargetInfo &Target = getContext().getTargetInfo();
7160 if (Target.areAllPointersCapabilities()) {
7161 if (Ty->isMemberFunctionPointerType()) {
7162 return llvm::StructType::get(CGM.VoidPtrTy, CGM.PtrDiffTy);
7163 }
7164 }
7165 CoerceToIntArgs(TySize, ArgList);
7166 return llvm::StructType::get(getVMContext(), ArgList);
7167 }
7168
7169 const RecordDecl *RD = RT->getDecl();
7170 const ASTRecordLayout &Layout = getContext().getASTRecordLayout(RD);
7171 assert(!(TySize % 8) && "Size of structure must be multiple of 8.");
7172
7173
7174 uint64_t LastOffset = 0;
7175 llvm::IntegerType *I64 = llvm::IntegerType::get(getVMContext(), 64);
7176 unsigned CapSize = getTarget().getCHERICapabilityWidth();
7177
7178 // If this is a C++ record, look for any capabilities in base classes first
7179 if (const CXXRecordDecl *CXXRD = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RD)) {
7180 for (const auto &I : CXXRD->bases()) {
7181 unsigned idx = 0;
7182 RecordDecl *BRD = I.getType()->getAs<RecordType>()->getDecl();
7183 const ASTRecordLayout &BaseLayout = getContext().getASTRecordLayout(BRD);
7184 for (RecordDecl::field_iterator i = BRD->field_begin(), e = BRD->field_end();
7185 i != e; ++i, ++idx) {
7186 const QualType Ty = i->getType();
7187 uint64_t Offset = BaseLayout.getFieldOffset(idx);
7188 if (const RecordType *FRT = Ty->getAs<RecordType>()) {
7189 if (getContext().containsCapabilities(FRT->getDecl())) {
7190 uint64_t FieldSize = getContext().getTypeSize(Ty);
7191 LastOffset = Offset + FieldSize;
7192 ArgList.push_back(HandleAggregates(Ty, FieldSize));
7193 continue;
7194 }
7195 }
7196 if (!Ty->isConstantArrayType() && Ty->isCHERICapabilityType(getContext())) {
7197 // Add ((Offset - LastOffset) / 64) args of type i64.
7198 for (unsigned j = (Offset - LastOffset) / 64; j > 0; --j)
7199 ArgList.push_back(I64);
7200 const uint64_t TySize = getContext().getTypeSize(Ty);
7201 LastOffset = Offset + TySize;
7202 assert(CapSize == TySize || (Ty->isMemberFunctionPointerType() && TySize == 2 * CapSize));
7203 ArgList.push_back(CGT.ConvertType(Ty));
7204 continue;
7205 }
7206 }
7207 }
7208 }
7209 unsigned idx = 0;
7210
7211 // Iterate over fields in the struct/class and check if there are any aligned
7212 // double fields.
7213 for (RecordDecl::field_iterator i = RD->field_begin(), e = RD->field_end();
7214 i != e; ++i, ++idx) {
7215 const QualType Ty = i->getType();
7216 const BuiltinType *BT = Ty->getAs<BuiltinType>();
7217 uint64_t Offset = Layout.getFieldOffset(idx);
7218
7219 if (const RecordType *FRT = Ty->getAs<RecordType>()) {
7220 if (getContext().containsCapabilities(FRT->getDecl())) {
7221 uint64_t FieldSize = getContext().getTypeSize(Ty);
7222 LastOffset = Layout.getFieldOffset(idx) + FieldSize;
7223 ArgList.push_back(HandleAggregates(Ty, FieldSize));
7224 continue;
7225 }
7226 }
7227 if (!Ty->isConstantArrayType() && Ty->isCHERICapabilityType(getContext())) {
7228 // Add ((Offset - LastOffset) / 64) args of type i64.
7229 for (unsigned j = (Offset - LastOffset) / 64; j > 0; --j)
7230 ArgList.push_back(I64);
7231 const uint64_t TySize = getContext().getTypeSize(Ty);
7232 LastOffset = Layout.getFieldOffset(idx) + TySize;
7233 assert(CapSize == TySize || (Ty->isMemberFunctionPointerType() && TySize == 2 * CapSize));
7234 ArgList.push_back(CGT.ConvertType(Ty));
7235 continue;
7236 }
7237 if (const ConstantArrayType *CAT = dyn_cast<ConstantArrayType>(Ty)) {
7238 auto ElementType = CAT->getElementType();
7239 unsigned Elements = CAT->getSize().getLimitedValue();
7240 if (ElementType->isCHERICapabilityType(getContext())) {
7241 llvm::Type *ElTy = CGT.ConvertType(ElementType);
7242 for (unsigned i=0 ; i<Elements ; ++i)
7243 ArgList.push_back(ElTy);
7244 const uint64_t ElemSize = getContext().getTypeSize(ElementType);
7245 LastOffset += Elements * ElemSize;
7246 assert(CapSize == ElemSize || (Ty->isMemberFunctionPointerType() && ElemSize == 2 * CapSize));
7247 continue;
7248 } else if (getContext().containsCapabilities(ElementType)) {
7249 uint64_t FieldSize = getContext().getTypeSize(ElementType);
7250 LastOffset += FieldSize * Elements;
7251 auto ElTy = HandleAggregates(ElementType, FieldSize);
7252 for (unsigned i=0 ; i<Elements ; ++i)
7253 ArgList.push_back(ElTy);
7254 continue;
7255 }
7256 }
7257
7258 if (!BT || BT->getKind() != BuiltinType::Double)
7259 continue;
7260
7261 if (Offset % 64) // Ignore doubles that are not aligned.
7262 continue;
7263
7264 // Add ((Offset - LastOffset) / 64) args of type i64.
7265 for (unsigned j = (Offset - LastOffset) / 64; j > 0; --j)
7266 ArgList.push_back(I64);
7267
7268 // Add double type.
7269 ArgList.push_back(llvm::Type::getDoubleTy(getVMContext()));
7270 LastOffset = Offset + 64;
7271 }
7272
7273 CoerceToIntArgs(TySize - LastOffset, IntArgList);
7274 ArgList.append(IntArgList.begin(), IntArgList.end());
7275
7276 return llvm::StructType::get(getVMContext(), ArgList);
7277}
7278
7279llvm::Type *MipsABIInfo::getPaddingType(uint64_t OrigOffset,
7280 uint64_t Offset) const {
7281 if (OrigOffset + MinABIStackAlignInBytes > Offset)
7282 return nullptr;
7283
7284 return llvm::IntegerType::get(getVMContext(), (Offset - OrigOffset) * 8);
7285}
7286
7287ABIArgInfo
7288MipsABIInfo::classifyArgumentType(QualType Ty, uint64_t &Offset) const {
7289 Ty = useFirstFieldIfTransparentUnion(Ty);
7290
7291 uint64_t OrigOffset = Offset;
7292 uint64_t TySize = getContext().getTypeSize(Ty);
7293 uint64_t Align = getContext().getTypeAlign(Ty) / 8;
7294
7295 Align = std::min(std::max(Align, (uint64_t)MinABIStackAlignInBytes),
7296 (uint64_t)StackAlignInBytes);
7297 unsigned CurrOffset = llvm::alignTo(Offset, Align);
7298 Offset = CurrOffset + llvm::alignTo(TySize, Align * 8) / 8;
7299
7300 if (isAggregateTypeForABI(Ty) || Ty->isVectorType()) {
7301 // Ignore empty aggregates.
7302 if (TySize == 0)
7303 return ABIArgInfo::getIgnore();
7304
7305 if (CGCXXABI::RecordArgABI RAA = getRecordArgABI(Ty, getCXXABI())) {
7306 Offset = OrigOffset + MinABIStackAlignInBytes;
7307 return getNaturalAlignIndirect(Ty, RAA == CGCXXABI::RAA_DirectInMemory);
7308 }
7309
7310 // Use indirect if the aggregate cannot fit into registers for
7311 // passing arguments according to the ABI
7312 unsigned Threshold = IsO32 ? 16 : 64;
7313 const TargetInfo &Target = getContext().getTargetInfo();
7314 if (Target.areAllPointersCapabilities()) {
7315 // assume we can pass structs up to 8 capabilities in size directly
7316 Threshold = 8 * (Target.getCHERICapabilityWidth() / 8);
7317 }
7318 bool PassIndirect = false;
7319 if (getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(Ty) > CharUnits::fromQuantity(Threshold))
7320 PassIndirect = true;
7321 // For CHERI, also pass C++ classes and structs that contain capabilities
7322 // indirectly (for now).
7323 // XXXKG: We should revisit passing fields in registers.
7324 else if (Ty->isCXXStructureOrClassType() &&
7325 Target.SupportsCapabilities() &&
7326 getContext().containsCapabilities(Ty))
7327 PassIndirect = true;
7328 if (PassIndirect)
7329 return ABIArgInfo::getIndirect(CharUnits::fromQuantity(Align), true,
7330 getContext().getTypeAlign(Ty) / 8 > Align);
7331
7332 // If we have reached here, aggregates are passed directly by coercing to
7333 // another structure type. Padding is inserted if the offset of the
7334 // aggregate is unaligned.
7335 ABIArgInfo ArgInfo =
7336 ABIArgInfo::getDirect(HandleAggregates(Ty, TySize), 0,
7337 getPaddingType(OrigOffset, CurrOffset));
7338 ArgInfo.setInReg(true);
7339 return ArgInfo;
7340 }
7341
7342 // Treat an enum type as its underlying type.
7343 if (const EnumType *EnumTy = Ty->getAs<EnumType>())
7344 Ty = EnumTy->getDecl()->getIntegerType();
7345
7346 // All integral types are promoted to the GPR width.
7347 if (Ty->isIntegralOrEnumerationType() &&
7348 !Ty->isCHERICapabilityType(getContext()))
7349 return extendType(Ty);
7350
7351 if (Ty->isCHERICapabilityType(getContext()))
7352 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(CGT.ConvertType(Ty));
7353
7354 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(
7355 nullptr, 0, IsO32 ? nullptr : getPaddingType(OrigOffset, CurrOffset));
7356}
7357
7358llvm::Type*
7359MipsABIInfo::returnAggregateInRegs(QualType RetTy, uint64_t Size) const {
7360 const RecordType *RT = RetTy->getAs<RecordType>();
7361 SmallVector<llvm::Type*, 8> RTList;
7362
7363 if (RT && RT->isStructureOrClassType()) {
7364 const RecordDecl *RD = RT->getDecl();
7365 const ASTRecordLayout &Layout = getContext().getASTRecordLayout(RD);
7366 unsigned FieldCnt = Layout.getFieldCount();
7367
7368 // N32/64 returns struct/classes in floating point registers if the
7369 // following conditions are met:
7370 // 1. The size of the struct/class is no larger than 128-bit.
7371 // 2. The struct/class has one or two fields all of which are floating
7372 // point types.
7373 // 3. The offset of the first field is zero (this follows what gcc does).
7374 //
7375 // Any other composite results are returned in integer registers.
7376 //
7377 if (FieldCnt && (FieldCnt <= 2) && Layout.getFieldOffset(0) == 0) {
7378 RecordDecl::field_iterator b = RD->field_begin(), e = RD->field_end();
7379 for (; b != e; ++b) {
7380 const BuiltinType *BT = b->getType()->getAs<BuiltinType>();
7381
7382 if (!BT || !BT->isFloatingPoint())
7383 break;
7384
7385 RTList.push_back(CGT.ConvertType(b->getType()));
7386 }
7387
7388 if (b == e)
7389 return llvm::StructType::get(getVMContext(), RTList,
7390 RD->hasAttr<PackedAttr>());
7391
7392 RTList.clear();
7393 }
7394 }
7395 // TODO: if containscapabilities
7396 // XXXAR: keeping old upstream code here in case I broke something
7397 // CoerceToIntArgs(Size, RTList);
7398 // return llvm::StructType::get(getVMContext(), RTList);
7399 return HandleAggregates(RetTy, Size);
7400}
7401
7402ABIArgInfo MipsABIInfo::classifyReturnType(QualType RetTy) const {
7403 uint64_t Size = getContext().getTypeSize(RetTy);
7404
7405 if (RetTy->isVoidType())
7406 return ABIArgInfo::getIgnore();
7407
7408 // O32 doesn't treat zero-sized structs differently from other structs.
7409 // However, N32/N64 ignores zero sized return values.
7410 if (!IsO32 && Size == 0)
7411 return ABIArgInfo::getIgnore();
7412
7413 if (isAggregateTypeForABI(RetTy) || RetTy->isVectorType()) {
7414 if (Size <= 128) {
7415 if (RetTy->isAnyComplexType())
7416 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect();
7417
7418 // O32 returns integer vectors in registers and N32/N64 returns all small
7419 // aggregates in registers.
7420 if (!IsO32 ||
7421 (RetTy->isVectorType() && !RetTy->hasFloatingRepresentation())) {
7422 ABIArgInfo ArgInfo =
7423 ABIArgInfo::getDirect(returnAggregateInRegs(RetTy, Size));
7424 ArgInfo.setInReg(true);
7425 return ArgInfo;
7426 }
7427 } else if (getTarget().SupportsCapabilities() &&
7428 Size <= getTarget().getCHERICapabilityWidth()) {
7429 // On CHERI, we can return unions containing capabilities or
7430 // structs containing only one capability directly
7431 const RecordType *RT = RetTy->getAs<RecordType>();
7432 if (RT && getContext().containsCapabilities(RT->getDecl())) {
7433 ABIArgInfo ArgInfo =
7434 ABIArgInfo::getDirect(returnAggregateInRegs(RetTy, Size));
7435 ArgInfo.setInReg(true);
7436 return ArgInfo;
7437 }
7438 }
7439 return getNaturalAlignIndirect(RetTy);
7440 }
7441
7442 // Treat an enum type as its underlying type.
7443 if (const EnumType *EnumTy = RetTy->getAs<EnumType>())
7444 RetTy = EnumTy->getDecl()->getIntegerType();
7445
7446 if (RetTy->isPromotableIntegerType())
7447 return ABIArgInfo::getExtend(RetTy);
7448
7449 if ((RetTy->isUnsignedIntegerOrEnumerationType() ||
7450 RetTy->isSignedIntegerOrEnumerationType()) && Size == 32 && !IsO32)
7451 return ABIArgInfo::getSignExtend(RetTy);
7452
7453 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect();
7454}
7455
7456void MipsABIInfo::computeInfo(CGFunctionInfo &FI) const {
7457 ABIArgInfo &RetInfo = FI.getReturnInfo();
7458 if (!getCXXABI().classifyReturnType(FI))
7459 RetInfo = classifyReturnType(FI.getReturnType());
7460
7461 // Check if a pointer to an aggregate is passed as a hidden argument.
7462 uint64_t Offset = RetInfo.isIndirect() ? MinABIStackAlignInBytes : 0;
7463
7464 for (auto &I : FI.arguments())
7465 I.info = classifyArgumentType(I.type, Offset);
7466}
7467
7468Address MipsABIInfo::EmitVAArg(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Address VAListAddr,
7469 QualType OrigTy) const {
7470 QualType Ty = OrigTy;
7471
7472 // Integer arguments are promoted to 32-bit on O32 and 64-bit on N32/N64.
7473 // Pointers are also promoted in the same way but this only matters for N32.
7474 unsigned SlotSizeInBits = IsO32 ? 32 : 64;
7475 unsigned PtrWidth = getTarget().getPointerWidth(0);
7476 bool DidPromote = false;
7477 if ((Ty->isIntegerType() &&
7478 getContext().getIntWidth(Ty) < SlotSizeInBits) ||
7479 (Ty->isPointerType() && PtrWidth < SlotSizeInBits)) {
7480 DidPromote = true;
7481 Ty = getContext().getIntTypeForBitwidth(SlotSizeInBits,
7482 Ty->isSignedIntegerType());
7483 }
7484
7485 auto TyInfo = getContext().getTypeInfoInChars(Ty);
7486
7487 // The alignment of things in the argument area is never larger than
7488 // StackAlignInBytes for O32.
7489 if (IsO32)
7490 TyInfo.second =
7491 std::min(TyInfo.second, CharUnits::fromQuantity(StackAlignInBytes));
7492
7493 // MinABIStackAlignInBytes is the size of argument slots on the stack.
7494 CharUnits ArgSlotSize = CharUnits::fromQuantity(MinABIStackAlignInBytes);
7495
7496 Address Addr = emitVoidPtrVAArg(CGF, VAListAddr, Ty, /*indirect*/ false,
7497 TyInfo, ArgSlotSize, /*AllowHigherAlign*/ true);
7498
7499
7500 // If there was a promotion, "unpromote" into a temporary.
7501 // TODO: can we just use a pointer into a subset of the original slot?
7502 if (DidPromote) {
7503 Address Temp = CGF.CreateMemTemp(OrigTy, "vaarg.promotion-temp");
7504 llvm::Value *Promoted = CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(Addr);
7505
7506 // Truncate down to the right width.
7507 llvm::Type *IntTy = (OrigTy->isIntegerType() ? Temp.getElementType()
7508 : CGF.IntPtrTy);
7509 llvm::Value *V = CGF.Builder.CreateTrunc(Promoted, IntTy);
7510 if (OrigTy->isPointerType())
7511 V = CGF.Builder.CreateIntToPtr(V, Temp.getElementType());
7512
7513 CGF.Builder.CreateStore(V, Temp);
7514 Addr = Temp;
7515 }
7516
7517 return Addr;
7518}
7519
7520ABIArgInfo MipsABIInfo::extendType(QualType Ty) const {
7521 int TySize = getContext().getTypeSize(Ty);
7522
7523 // MIPS64 ABI requires unsigned 32 bit integers to be sign extended.
7524 if (Ty->isUnsignedIntegerOrEnumerationType() && TySize == 32)
7525 return ABIArgInfo::getSignExtend(Ty);
7526
7527 return ABIArgInfo::getExtend(Ty);
7528}
7529
7530bool
7531MIPSTargetCodeGenInfo::initDwarfEHRegSizeTable(CodeGen::CodeGenFunction &CGF,
7532 llvm::Value *Address) const {
7533 // This information comes from gcc's implementation, which seems to
7534 // as canonical as it gets.
7535
7536 // Everything on MIPS is 4 bytes. Double-precision FP registers
7537 // are aliased to pairs of single-precision FP registers.
7538 llvm::Value *Four8 = llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.Int8Ty, 4);
7539
7540 // 0-31 are the general purpose registers, $0 - $31.
7541 // 32-63 are the floating-point registers, $f0 - $f31.
7542 // 64 and 65 are the multiply/divide registers, $hi and $lo.
7543 // 66 is the (notional, I think) register for signal-handler return.
7544 AssignToArrayRange(CGF.Builder, Address, Four8, 0, 65);
7545
7546 // 67-74 are the floating-point status registers, $fcc0 - $fcc7.
7547 // They are one bit wide and ignored here.
7548
7549 // 80-111 are the coprocessor 0 registers, $c0r0 - $c0r31.
7550 // (coprocessor 1 is the FP unit)
7551 // 112-143 are the coprocessor 2 registers, $c2r0 - $c2r31.
7552 // 144-175 are the coprocessor 3 registers, $c3r0 - $c3r31.
7553 // 176-181 are the DSP accumulator registers.
7554 AssignToArrayRange(CGF.Builder, Address, Four8, 80, 181);
7555 return false;
7556}
7557
7558//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
7559// AVR ABI Implementation.
7560//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
7561
7562namespace {
7563class AVRTargetCodeGenInfo : public TargetCodeGenInfo {
7564public:
7565 AVRTargetCodeGenInfo(CodeGenTypes &CGT)
7566 : TargetCodeGenInfo(new DefaultABIInfo(CGT)) { }
7567
7568 void setTargetAttributes(const Decl *D, llvm::GlobalValue *GV,
7569 CodeGen::CodeGenModule &CGM) const override {
7570 if (GV->isDeclaration())
7571 return;
7572 const auto *FD = dyn_cast_or_null<FunctionDecl>(D);
7573 if (!FD) return;
7574 auto *Fn = cast<llvm::Function>(GV);
7575
7576 if (FD->getAttr<AVRInterruptAttr>())
7577 Fn->addFnAttr("interrupt");
7578
7579 if (FD->getAttr<AVRSignalAttr>())
7580 Fn->addFnAttr("signal");
7581 }
7582};
7583}

7585//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
7586// TCE ABI Implementation (see http://tce.cs.tut.fi). Uses mostly the defaults.
7587// Currently subclassed only to implement custom OpenCL C function attribute
7588// handling.
7589//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
7590
7591namespace {
7592
7593class TCETargetCodeGenInfo : public DefaultTargetCodeGenInfo {
7594public:
7595 TCETargetCodeGenInfo(CodeGenTypes &CGT)
7596 : DefaultTargetCodeGenInfo(CGT) {}
7597
7598 void setTargetAttributes(const Decl *D, llvm::GlobalValue *GV,
7599 CodeGen::CodeGenModule &M) const override;
7600};
7601
7602void TCETargetCodeGenInfo::setTargetAttributes(
7603 const Decl *D, llvm::GlobalValue *GV, CodeGen::CodeGenModule &M) const {
7604 if (GV->isDeclaration())
7605 return;
7606 const FunctionDecl *FD = dyn_cast_or_null<FunctionDecl>(D);
7607 if (!FD) return;
7608
7609 llvm::Function *F = cast<llvm::Function>(GV);
7610
7611 if (M.getLangOpts().OpenCL) {
7612 if (FD->hasAttr<OpenCLKernelAttr>()) {
7613 // OpenCL C Kernel functions are not subject to inlining
7614 F->addFnAttr(llvm::Attribute::NoInline);
7615 const ReqdWorkGroupSizeAttr *Attr = FD->getAttr<ReqdWorkGroupSizeAttr>();
7616 if (Attr) {
7617 // Convert the reqd_work_group_size() attributes to metadata.
7618 llvm::LLVMContext &Context = F->getContext();
7619 llvm::NamedMDNode *OpenCLMetadata =
7620 M.getModule().getOrInsertNamedMetadata(
7621 "opencl.kernel_wg_size_info");
7622
7623 SmallVector<llvm::Metadata *, 5> Operands;
7624 Operands.push_back(llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(F));
7625
7626 Operands.push_back(
7627 llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(llvm::Constant::getIntegerValue(
7628 M.Int32Ty, llvm::APInt(32, Attr->getXDim()))));
7629 Operands.push_back(
7630 llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(llvm::Constant::getIntegerValue(
7631 M.Int32Ty, llvm::APInt(32, Attr->getYDim()))));
7632 Operands.push_back(
7633 llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(llvm::Constant::getIntegerValue(
7634 M.Int32Ty, llvm::APInt(32, Attr->getZDim()))));
7635
7636 // Add a boolean constant operand for "required" (true) or "hint"
7637 // (false) for implementing the work_group_size_hint attr later.
7638 // Currently always true as the hint is not yet implemented.
7639 Operands.push_back(
7640 llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(llvm::ConstantInt::getTrue(Context)));
7641 OpenCLMetadata->addOperand(llvm::MDNode::get(Context, Operands));
7642 }
7643 }
7644 }
7645}
7646
7647}
