7650// Hexagon ABI Implementation
7651//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
7652
7653namespace {
7654
7655class HexagonABIInfo : public ABIInfo {
7656
7657
7658public:
7659 HexagonABIInfo(CodeGenTypes &CGT) : ABIInfo(CGT) {}
7660
7661private:
7662
7663 ABIArgInfo classifyReturnType(QualType RetTy) const;
7664 ABIArgInfo classifyArgumentType(QualType RetTy) const;
7665
7666 void computeInfo(CGFunctionInfo &FI) const override;
7667
7668 Address EmitVAArg(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Address VAListAddr,
7669 QualType Ty) const override;
7670};
7671
7672class HexagonTargetCodeGenInfo : public TargetCodeGenInfo {
7673public:
7674 HexagonTargetCodeGenInfo(CodeGenTypes &CGT)
7675 :TargetCodeGenInfo(new HexagonABIInfo(CGT)) {}
7676
7677 int getDwarfEHStackPointer(CodeGen::CodeGenModule &M) const override {
7678 return 29;
7679 }
7680};
7681
7682}
7683
7684void HexagonABIInfo::computeInfo(CGFunctionInfo &FI) const {
7685 if (!getCXXABI().classifyReturnType(FI))
7686 FI.getReturnInfo() = classifyReturnType(FI.getReturnType());
7687 for (auto &I : FI.arguments())
7688 I.info = classifyArgumentType(I.type);
7689}
7690
7691ABIArgInfo HexagonABIInfo::classifyArgumentType(QualType Ty) const {
7692 if (!isAggregateTypeForABI(Ty)) {
7693 // Treat an enum type as its underlying type.
7694 if (const EnumType *EnumTy = Ty->getAs<EnumType>())
7695 Ty = EnumTy->getDecl()->getIntegerType();
7696
7697 return (Ty->isPromotableIntegerType() ? ABIArgInfo::getExtend(Ty)
7698 : ABIArgInfo::getDirect());
7699 }
7700
7701 if (CGCXXABI::RecordArgABI RAA = getRecordArgABI(Ty, getCXXABI()))
7702 return getNaturalAlignIndirect(Ty, RAA == CGCXXABI::RAA_DirectInMemory);
7703
7704 // Ignore empty records.
7705 if (isEmptyRecord(getContext(), Ty, true))
7706 return ABIArgInfo::getIgnore();
7707
7708 uint64_t Size = getContext().getTypeSize(Ty);
7709 if (Size > 64)
7710 return getNaturalAlignIndirect(Ty, /*ByVal=*/true);
7711 // Pass in the smallest viable integer type.
7712 else if (Size > 32)
7713 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(llvm::Type::getInt64Ty(getVMContext()));
7714 else if (Size > 16)
7715 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(llvm::Type::getInt32Ty(getVMContext()));
7716 else if (Size > 8)
7717 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(llvm::Type::getInt16Ty(getVMContext()));
7718 else
7719 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(llvm::Type::getInt8Ty(getVMContext()));
7720}
7721
7722ABIArgInfo HexagonABIInfo::classifyReturnType(QualType RetTy) const {
7723 if (RetTy->isVoidType())
7724 return ABIArgInfo::getIgnore();
7725
7726 // Large vector types should be returned via memory.
7727 if (RetTy->isVectorType() && getContext().getTypeSize(RetTy) > 64)
7728 return getNaturalAlignIndirect(RetTy);
7729
7730 if (!isAggregateTypeForABI(RetTy)) {
7731 // Treat an enum type as its underlying type.
7732 if (const EnumType *EnumTy = RetTy->getAs<EnumType>())
7733 RetTy = EnumTy->getDecl()->getIntegerType();
7734
7735 return (RetTy->isPromotableIntegerType() ? ABIArgInfo::getExtend(RetTy)
7736 : ABIArgInfo::getDirect());
7737 }
7738
7739 if (isEmptyRecord(getContext(), RetTy, true))
7740 return ABIArgInfo::getIgnore();
7741
7742 // Aggregates <= 8 bytes are returned in r0; other aggregates
7743 // are returned indirectly.
7744 uint64_t Size = getContext().getTypeSize(RetTy);
7745 if (Size <= 64) {
7746 // Return in the smallest viable integer type.
7747 if (Size <= 8)
7748 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(llvm::Type::getInt8Ty(getVMContext()));
7749 if (Size <= 16)
7750 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(llvm::Type::getInt16Ty(getVMContext()));
7751 if (Size <= 32)
7752 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(llvm::Type::getInt32Ty(getVMContext()));
7753 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(llvm::Type::getInt64Ty(getVMContext()));
7754 }
7755
7756 return getNaturalAlignIndirect(RetTy, /*ByVal=*/true);
7757}
7758
7759Address HexagonABIInfo::EmitVAArg(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Address VAListAddr,
7760 QualType Ty) const {
7761 // FIXME: Someone needs to audit that this handle alignment correctly.
7762 return emitVoidPtrVAArg(CGF, VAListAddr, Ty, /*indirect*/ false,
7763 getContext().getTypeInfoInChars(Ty),
7764 CharUnits::fromQuantity(4),
7765 /*AllowHigherAlign*/ true);
7766}
7767
7768//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
7769// Lanai ABI Implementation
7770//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
7771
7772namespace {
7773class LanaiABIInfo : public DefaultABIInfo {
7774public:
7775 LanaiABIInfo(CodeGen::CodeGenTypes &CGT) : DefaultABIInfo(CGT) {}
7776
7777 bool shouldUseInReg(QualType Ty, CCState &State) const;
7778
7779 void computeInfo(CGFunctionInfo &FI) const override {
7780 CCState State(FI.getCallingConvention());
7781 // Lanai uses 4 registers to pass arguments unless the function has the
7782 // regparm attribute set.
7783 if (FI.getHasRegParm()) {
7784 State.FreeRegs = FI.getRegParm();
7785 } else {
7786 State.FreeRegs = 4;
7787 }
7788
7789 if (!getCXXABI().classifyReturnType(FI))
7790 FI.getReturnInfo() = classifyReturnType(FI.getReturnType());
7791 for (auto &I : FI.arguments())
7792 I.info = classifyArgumentType(I.type, State);
7793 }
7794
7795 ABIArgInfo getIndirectResult(QualType Ty, bool ByVal, CCState &State) const;
7796 ABIArgInfo classifyArgumentType(QualType RetTy, CCState &State) const;
7797};
7798} // end anonymous namespace
7799
7800bool LanaiABIInfo::shouldUseInReg(QualType Ty, CCState &State) const {
7801 unsigned Size = getContext().getTypeSize(Ty);
7802 unsigned SizeInRegs = llvm::alignTo(Size, 32U) / 32U;
7803
7804 if (SizeInRegs == 0)
7805 return false;
7806
7807 if (SizeInRegs > State.FreeRegs) {
7808 State.FreeRegs = 0;
7809 return false;
7810 }
7811
7812 State.FreeRegs -= SizeInRegs;
7813
7814 return true;
7815}
7816
7817ABIArgInfo LanaiABIInfo::getIndirectResult(QualType Ty, bool ByVal,
7818 CCState &State) const {
7819 if (!ByVal) {
7820 if (State.FreeRegs) {
7821 --State.FreeRegs; // Non-byval indirects just use one pointer.
7822 return getNaturalAlignIndirectInReg(Ty);
7823 }
7824 return getNaturalAlignIndirect(Ty, false);
7825 }
7826
7827 // Compute the byval alignment.
7828 const unsigned MinABIStackAlignInBytes = 4;
7829 unsigned TypeAlign = getContext().getTypeAlign(Ty) / 8;
7830 return ABIArgInfo::getIndirect(CharUnits::fromQuantity(4), /*ByVal=*/true,
7831 /*Realign=*/TypeAlign >
7832 MinABIStackAlignInBytes);
7833}
7834
7835ABIArgInfo LanaiABIInfo::classifyArgumentType(QualType Ty,
7836 CCState &State) const {
7837 // Check with the C++ ABI first.
7838 const RecordType *RT = Ty->getAs<RecordType>();
7839 if (RT) {
7840 CGCXXABI::RecordArgABI RAA = getRecordArgABI(RT, getCXXABI());
7841 if (RAA == CGCXXABI::RAA_Indirect) {
7842 return getIndirectResult(Ty, /*ByVal=*/false, State);
7843 } else if (RAA == CGCXXABI::RAA_DirectInMemory) {
7844 return getNaturalAlignIndirect(Ty, /*ByRef=*/true);
7845 }
7846 }
7847
7848 if (isAggregateTypeForABI(Ty)) {
7849 // Structures with flexible arrays are always indirect.
7850 if (RT && RT->getDecl()->hasFlexibleArrayMember())
7851 return getIndirectResult(Ty, /*ByVal=*/true, State);
7852
7853 // Ignore empty structs/unions.
7854 if (isEmptyRecord(getContext(), Ty, true))
7855 return ABIArgInfo::getIgnore();
7856
7857 llvm::LLVMContext &LLVMContext = getVMContext();
7858 unsigned SizeInRegs = (getContext().getTypeSize(Ty) + 31) / 32;
7859 if (SizeInRegs <= State.FreeRegs) {
7860 llvm::IntegerType *Int32 = llvm::Type::getInt32Ty(LLVMContext);
7861 SmallVector<llvm::Type *, 3> Elements(SizeInRegs, Int32);
7862 llvm::Type *Result = llvm::StructType::get(LLVMContext, Elements);
7863 State.FreeRegs -= SizeInRegs;
7864 return ABIArgInfo::getDirectInReg(Result);
7865 } else {
7866 State.FreeRegs = 0;
7867 }
7868 return getIndirectResult(Ty, true, State);
7869 }
7870
7871 // Treat an enum type as its underlying type.
7872 if (const auto *EnumTy = Ty->getAs<EnumType>())
7873 Ty = EnumTy->getDecl()->getIntegerType();
7874
7875 bool InReg = shouldUseInReg(Ty, State);
7876 if (Ty->isPromotableIntegerType()) {
7877 if (InReg)
7878 return ABIArgInfo::getDirectInReg();
7879 return ABIArgInfo::getExtend(Ty);
7880 }
7881 if (InReg)
7882 return ABIArgInfo::getDirectInReg();
7883 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect();
7884}
7885
7886namespace {
7887class LanaiTargetCodeGenInfo : public TargetCodeGenInfo {
7888public:
7889 LanaiTargetCodeGenInfo(CodeGen::CodeGenTypes &CGT)
7890 : TargetCodeGenInfo(new LanaiABIInfo(CGT)) {}
7891};
7892}

7894//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
7895// AMDGPU ABI Implementation
7896//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
7897
7898namespace {
7899
7900class AMDGPUABIInfo final : public DefaultABIInfo {
7901private:
7902 static const unsigned MaxNumRegsForArgsRet = 16;
7903
7904 unsigned numRegsForType(QualType Ty) const;
7905
7906 bool isHomogeneousAggregateBaseType(QualType Ty) const override;
7907 bool isHomogeneousAggregateSmallEnough(const Type *Base,
7908 uint64_t Members) const override;
7909
7910public:
7911 explicit AMDGPUABIInfo(CodeGen::CodeGenTypes &CGT) :
7912 DefaultABIInfo(CGT) {}
7913
7914 ABIArgInfo classifyReturnType(QualType RetTy) const;
7915 ABIArgInfo classifyKernelArgumentType(QualType Ty) const;
7916 ABIArgInfo classifyArgumentType(QualType Ty, unsigned &NumRegsLeft) const;
7917
7918 void computeInfo(CGFunctionInfo &FI) const override;
7919};
7920
7921bool AMDGPUABIInfo::isHomogeneousAggregateBaseType(QualType Ty) const {
7922 return true;
7923}
7924
7925bool AMDGPUABIInfo::isHomogeneousAggregateSmallEnough(
7926 const Type *Base, uint64_t Members) const {
7927 uint32_t NumRegs = (getContext().getTypeSize(Base) + 31) / 32;
7928
7929 // Homogeneous Aggregates may occupy at most 16 registers.
7930 return Members * NumRegs <= MaxNumRegsForArgsRet;
7931}
7932
7933/// Estimate number of registers the type will use when passed in registers.
7934unsigned AMDGPUABIInfo::numRegsForType(QualType Ty) const {
7935 unsigned NumRegs = 0;
7936
7937 if (const VectorType *VT = Ty->getAs<VectorType>()) {
7938 // Compute from the number of elements. The reported size is based on the
7939 // in-memory size, which includes the padding 4th element for 3-vectors.
7940 QualType EltTy = VT->getElementType();
7941 unsigned EltSize = getContext().getTypeSize(EltTy);
7942
7943 // 16-bit element vectors should be passed as packed.
7944 if (EltSize == 16)
7945 return (VT->getNumElements() + 1) / 2;
7946
7947 unsigned EltNumRegs = (EltSize + 31) / 32;
7948 return EltNumRegs * VT->getNumElements();
7949 }
7950
7951 if (const RecordType *RT = Ty->getAs<RecordType>()) {
7952 const RecordDecl *RD = RT->getDecl();
7953 assert(!RD->hasFlexibleArrayMember());
7954
7955 for (const FieldDecl *Field : RD->fields()) {
7956 QualType FieldTy = Field->getType();
7957 NumRegs += numRegsForType(FieldTy);
7958 }
7959
7960 return NumRegs;
7961 }
7962
7963 return (getContext().getTypeSize(Ty) + 31) / 32;
7964}
7965
7966void AMDGPUABIInfo::computeInfo(CGFunctionInfo &FI) const {
7967 llvm::CallingConv::ID CC = FI.getCallingConvention();
7968
7969 if (!getCXXABI().classifyReturnType(FI))
7970 FI.getReturnInfo() = classifyReturnType(FI.getReturnType());
7971
7972 unsigned NumRegsLeft = MaxNumRegsForArgsRet;
7973 for (auto &Arg : FI.arguments()) {
7974 if (CC == llvm::CallingConv::AMDGPU_KERNEL) {
7975 Arg.info = classifyKernelArgumentType(Arg.type);
7976 } else {
7977 Arg.info = classifyArgumentType(Arg.type, NumRegsLeft);
7978 }
7979 }
7980}
7981
7982ABIArgInfo AMDGPUABIInfo::classifyReturnType(QualType RetTy) const {
7983 if (isAggregateTypeForABI(RetTy)) {
7984 // Records with non-trivial destructors/copy-constructors should not be
7985 // returned by value.
7986 if (!getRecordArgABI(RetTy, getCXXABI())) {
7987 // Ignore empty structs/unions.
7988 if (isEmptyRecord(getContext(), RetTy, true))
7989 return ABIArgInfo::getIgnore();
7990
7991 // Lower single-element structs to just return a regular value.
7992 if (const Type *SeltTy = isSingleElementStruct(RetTy, getContext()))
7993 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(CGT.ConvertType(QualType(SeltTy, 0)));
7994
7995 if (const RecordType *RT = RetTy->getAs<RecordType>()) {
7996 const RecordDecl *RD = RT->getDecl();
7997 if (RD->hasFlexibleArrayMember())
7998 return DefaultABIInfo::classifyReturnType(RetTy);
7999 }
8000
8001 // Pack aggregates <= 4 bytes into single VGPR or pair.
8002 uint64_t Size = getContext().getTypeSize(RetTy);
8003 if (Size <= 16)
8004 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(llvm::Type::getInt16Ty(getVMContext()));
8005
8006 if (Size <= 32)
8007 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(llvm::Type::getInt32Ty(getVMContext()));
8008
8009 if (Size <= 64) {
8010 llvm::Type *I32Ty = llvm::Type::getInt32Ty(getVMContext());
8011 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(llvm::ArrayType::get(I32Ty, 2));
8012 }
8013
8014 if (numRegsForType(RetTy) <= MaxNumRegsForArgsRet)
8015 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect();
8016 }
8017 }
8018
8019 // Otherwise just do the default thing.
8020 return DefaultABIInfo::classifyReturnType(RetTy);
8021}
8022
8023/// For kernels all parameters are really passed in a special buffer. It doesn't
8024/// make sense to pass anything byval, so everything must be direct.
8025ABIArgInfo AMDGPUABIInfo::classifyKernelArgumentType(QualType Ty) const {
8026 Ty = useFirstFieldIfTransparentUnion(Ty);
8027
8028 // TODO: Can we omit empty structs?
8029
8030 // Coerce single element structs to its element.
8031 if (const Type *SeltTy = isSingleElementStruct(Ty, getContext()))
8032 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(CGT.ConvertType(QualType(SeltTy, 0)));
8033
8034 // If we set CanBeFlattened to true, CodeGen will expand the struct to its
8035 // individual elements, which confuses the Clover OpenCL backend; therefore we
8036 // have to set it to false here. Other args of getDirect() are just defaults.
8037 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(nullptr, 0, nullptr, false);
8038}
8039
8040ABIArgInfo AMDGPUABIInfo::classifyArgumentType(QualType Ty,
8041 unsigned &NumRegsLeft) const {
8042 assert(NumRegsLeft <= MaxNumRegsForArgsRet && "register estimate underflow");
8043
8044 Ty = useFirstFieldIfTransparentUnion(Ty);
8045
8046 if (isAggregateTypeForABI(Ty)) {
8047 // Records with non-trivial destructors/copy-constructors should not be
8048 // passed by value.
8049 if (auto RAA = getRecordArgABI(Ty, getCXXABI()))
8050 return getNaturalAlignIndirect(Ty, RAA == CGCXXABI::RAA_DirectInMemory);
8051
8052 // Ignore empty structs/unions.
8053 if (isEmptyRecord(getContext(), Ty, true))
8054 return ABIArgInfo::getIgnore();
8055
8056 // Lower single-element structs to just pass a regular value. TODO: We
8057 // could do reasonable-size multiple-element structs too, using getExpand(),
8058 // though watch out for things like bitfields.
8059 if (const Type *SeltTy = isSingleElementStruct(Ty, getContext()))
8060 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(CGT.ConvertType(QualType(SeltTy, 0)));
8061
8062 if (const RecordType *RT = Ty->getAs<RecordType>()) {
8063 const RecordDecl *RD = RT->getDecl();
8064 if (RD->hasFlexibleArrayMember())
8065 return DefaultABIInfo::classifyArgumentType(Ty);
8066 }
8067
8068 // Pack aggregates <= 8 bytes into single VGPR or pair.
8069 uint64_t Size = getContext().getTypeSize(Ty);
8070 if (Size <= 64) {
8071 unsigned NumRegs = (Size + 31) / 32;
8072 NumRegsLeft -= std::min(NumRegsLeft, NumRegs);
8073
8074 if (Size <= 16)
8075 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(llvm::Type::getInt16Ty(getVMContext()));
8076
8077 if (Size <= 32)
8078 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(llvm::Type::getInt32Ty(getVMContext()));
8079
8080 // XXX: Should this be i64 instead, and should the limit increase?
8081 llvm::Type *I32Ty = llvm::Type::getInt32Ty(getVMContext());
8082 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(llvm::ArrayType::get(I32Ty, 2));
8083 }
8084
8085 if (NumRegsLeft > 0) {
8086 unsigned NumRegs = numRegsForType(Ty);
8087 if (NumRegsLeft >= NumRegs) {
8088 NumRegsLeft -= NumRegs;
8089 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect();
8090 }
8091 }
8092 }
8093
8094 // Otherwise just do the default thing.
8095 ABIArgInfo ArgInfo = DefaultABIInfo::classifyArgumentType(Ty);
8096 if (!ArgInfo.isIndirect()) {
8097 unsigned NumRegs = numRegsForType(Ty);
8098 NumRegsLeft -= std::min(NumRegs, NumRegsLeft);
8099 }
8100
8101 return ArgInfo;
8102}

8104class AMDGPUTargetCodeGenInfo : public TargetCodeGenInfo {
8105public:
8106 AMDGPUTargetCodeGenInfo(CodeGenTypes &CGT)
8107 : TargetCodeGenInfo(new AMDGPUABIInfo(CGT)) {}
8108 void setTargetAttributes(const Decl *D, llvm::GlobalValue *GV,
8109 CodeGen::CodeGenModule &M) const override;
8110 unsigned getOpenCLKernelCallingConv() const override;
8111
8112 llvm::Constant *getNullPointer(const CodeGen::CodeGenModule &CGM,
8113 llvm::PointerType *T, QualType QT) const override;
8114
8115 LangAS getASTAllocaAddressSpace() const override {
8116 return getLangASFromTargetAS(
8117 getABIInfo().getDataLayout().getAllocaAddrSpace());
8118 }
8119 LangAS getGlobalVarAddressSpace(CodeGenModule &CGM,
8120 const VarDecl *D) const override;
8121 llvm::SyncScope::ID getLLVMSyncScopeID(const LangOptions &LangOpts,
8122 SyncScope Scope,
8123 llvm::AtomicOrdering Ordering,
8124 llvm::LLVMContext &Ctx) const override;

8127 llvm::Function *BlockInvokeFunc,

8130 void setCUDAKernelCallingConvention(const FunctionType *&FT) const override;
8131};
8132}
8133
8134static bool requiresAMDGPUProtectedVisibility(const Decl *D,
8135 llvm::GlobalValue *GV) {
8136 if (GV->getVisibility() != llvm::GlobalValue::HiddenVisibility)
8137 return false;
8138
8139 return D->hasAttr<OpenCLKernelAttr>() ||
8140 (isa<FunctionDecl>(D) && D->hasAttr<CUDAGlobalAttr>()) ||
8141 (isa<VarDecl>(D) &&
8142 (D->hasAttr<CUDADeviceAttr>() || D->hasAttr<CUDAConstantAttr>()));
8143}
8144
8145void AMDGPUTargetCodeGenInfo::setTargetAttributes(
8146 const Decl *D, llvm::GlobalValue *GV, CodeGen::CodeGenModule &M) const {
8147 if (requiresAMDGPUProtectedVisibility(D, GV)) {
8148 GV->setVisibility(llvm::GlobalValue::ProtectedVisibility);
8149 GV->setDSOLocal(true);
8150 }
8151
8152 if (GV->isDeclaration())
8153 return;
8154 const FunctionDecl *FD = dyn_cast_or_null<FunctionDecl>(D);
8155 if (!FD)
8156 return;
8157
8158 llvm::Function *F = cast<llvm::Function>(GV);
8159
8160 const auto *ReqdWGS = M.getLangOpts().OpenCL ?
8161 FD->getAttr<ReqdWorkGroupSizeAttr>() : nullptr;
8162
8163 if (M.getLangOpts().OpenCL && FD->hasAttr<OpenCLKernelAttr>() &&
8164 (M.getTriple().getOS() == llvm::Triple::AMDHSA))
8165 F->addFnAttr("amdgpu-implicitarg-num-bytes", "48");
8166
8167 const auto *FlatWGS = FD->getAttr<AMDGPUFlatWorkGroupSizeAttr>();
8168 if (ReqdWGS || FlatWGS) {
8169 unsigned Min = 0;
8170 unsigned Max = 0;
8171 if (FlatWGS) {
8172 Min = FlatWGS->getMin()
8173 ->EvaluateKnownConstInt(M.getContext())
8174 .getExtValue();
8175 Max = FlatWGS->getMax()
8176 ->EvaluateKnownConstInt(M.getContext())
8177 .getExtValue();
8178 }
8179 if (ReqdWGS && Min == 0 && Max == 0)
8180 Min = Max = ReqdWGS->getXDim() * ReqdWGS->getYDim() * ReqdWGS->getZDim();
8181
8182 if (Min != 0) {
8183 assert(Min <= Max && "Min must be less than or equal Max");
8184
8185 std::string AttrVal = llvm::utostr(Min) + "," + llvm::utostr(Max);
8186 F->addFnAttr("amdgpu-flat-work-group-size", AttrVal);
8187 } else
8188 assert(Max == 0 && "Max must be zero");
8189 }
8190
8191 if (const auto *Attr = FD->getAttr<AMDGPUWavesPerEUAttr>()) {
8192 unsigned Min =
8193 Attr->getMin()->EvaluateKnownConstInt(M.getContext()).getExtValue();
8194 unsigned Max = Attr->getMax() ? Attr->getMax()
8195 ->EvaluateKnownConstInt(M.getContext())
8196 .getExtValue()
8197 : 0;
8198
8199 if (Min != 0) {
8200 assert((Max == 0 || Min <= Max) && "Min must be less than or equal Max");
8201
8202 std::string AttrVal = llvm::utostr(Min);
8203 if (Max != 0)
8204 AttrVal = AttrVal + "," + llvm::utostr(Max);
8205 F->addFnAttr("amdgpu-waves-per-eu", AttrVal);
8206 } else
8207 assert(Max == 0 && "Max must be zero");
8208 }
8209
8210 if (const auto *Attr = FD->getAttr<AMDGPUNumSGPRAttr>()) {
8211 unsigned NumSGPR = Attr->getNumSGPR();
8212
8213 if (NumSGPR != 0)
8214 F->addFnAttr("amdgpu-num-sgpr", llvm::utostr(NumSGPR));
8215 }
8216
8217 if (const auto *Attr = FD->getAttr<AMDGPUNumVGPRAttr>()) {
8218 uint32_t NumVGPR = Attr->getNumVGPR();
8219
8220 if (NumVGPR != 0)
8221 F->addFnAttr("amdgpu-num-vgpr", llvm::utostr(NumVGPR));
8222 }
8223}
8224
8225unsigned AMDGPUTargetCodeGenInfo::getOpenCLKernelCallingConv() const {
8226 return llvm::CallingConv::AMDGPU_KERNEL;
8227}
8228
8229// Currently LLVM assumes null pointers always have value 0,
8230// which results in incorrectly transformed IR. Therefore, instead of
8231// emitting null pointers in private and local address spaces, a null
8232// pointer in generic address space is emitted which is casted to a
8233// pointer in local or private address space.
8234llvm::Constant *AMDGPUTargetCodeGenInfo::getNullPointer(
8235 const CodeGen::CodeGenModule &CGM, llvm::PointerType *PT,
8236 QualType QT) const {
8237 if (CGM.getContext().getTargetNullPointerValue(QT) == 0)
8238 return llvm::ConstantPointerNull::get(PT);
8239 // XXXAR: FIXME: remove const_cast here
8240 auto NPT = llvm::PointerType::get(PT->getElementType(),
8241 const_cast<CodeGen::CodeGenModule &>(CGM).getTargetAddressSpace(LangAS::opencl_generic));
8242 return llvm::ConstantExpr::getAddrSpaceCast(
8243 llvm::ConstantPointerNull::get(NPT), PT);
8244}
8245
8246LangAS
8247AMDGPUTargetCodeGenInfo::getGlobalVarAddressSpace(CodeGenModule &CGM,
8248 const VarDecl *D) const {
8249 assert(!CGM.getLangOpts().OpenCL &&
8250 !(CGM.getLangOpts().CUDA && CGM.getLangOpts().CUDAIsDevice) &&
8251 "Address space agnostic languages only");
8252 LangAS DefaultGlobalAS = getLangASFromTargetAS(
8253 CGM.getTargetAddressSpace(LangAS::opencl_global));
8254 if (!D)
8255 return DefaultGlobalAS;
8256
8257 LangAS AddrSpace = D->getType().getAddressSpace();
8258 assert(AddrSpace == LangAS::Default || isTargetAddressSpace(AddrSpace));
8259 if (AddrSpace != LangAS::Default)
8260 return AddrSpace;
8261
8262 if (CGM.isTypeConstant(D->getType(), false)) {
8263 if (auto ConstAS = CGM.getTarget().getConstantAddressSpace())
8264 return ConstAS.getValue();
8265 }
8266 return DefaultGlobalAS;
8267}
8268
8269llvm::SyncScope::ID
8270AMDGPUTargetCodeGenInfo::getLLVMSyncScopeID(const LangOptions &LangOpts,
8271 SyncScope Scope,
8272 llvm::AtomicOrdering Ordering,
8273 llvm::LLVMContext &Ctx) const {
8274 std::string Name;
8275 switch (Scope) {
8276 case SyncScope::OpenCLWorkGroup:
8277 Name = "workgroup";
8278 break;
8279 case SyncScope::OpenCLDevice:
8280 Name = "agent";
8281 break;
8282 case SyncScope::OpenCLAllSVMDevices:
8283 Name = "";
8284 break;
8285 case SyncScope::OpenCLSubGroup:
8286 Name = "wavefront";
8287 }
8288
8289 if (Ordering != llvm::AtomicOrdering::SequentiallyConsistent) {
8290 if (!Name.empty())
8291 Name = Twine(Twine(Name) + Twine("-")).str();
8292
8293 Name = Twine(Twine(Name) + Twine("one-as")).str();
8294 }
8295
8296 return Ctx.getOrInsertSyncScopeID(Name);
8297}
8298
8299bool AMDGPUTargetCodeGenInfo::shouldEmitStaticExternCAliases() const {
8300 return false;
8301}
8302
8303void AMDGPUTargetCodeGenInfo::setCUDAKernelCallingConvention(
8304 const FunctionType *&FT) const {
8305 FT = getABIInfo().getContext().adjustFunctionType(
8306 FT, FT->getExtInfo().withCallingConv(CC_OpenCLKernel));
8307}

8309//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
8310// SPARC v8 ABI Implementation.
8311// Based on the SPARC Compliance Definition version 2.4.1.
8312//
8313// Ensures that complex values are passed in registers.
8314//
8315namespace {
8316class SparcV8ABIInfo : public DefaultABIInfo {
8317public:
8318 SparcV8ABIInfo(CodeGenTypes &CGT) : DefaultABIInfo(CGT) {}
8319
8320private:
8321 ABIArgInfo classifyReturnType(QualType RetTy) const;
8322 void computeInfo(CGFunctionInfo &FI) const override;
8323};
8324} // end anonymous namespace
8325
8326
8327ABIArgInfo
8328SparcV8ABIInfo::classifyReturnType(QualType Ty) const {
8329 if (Ty->isAnyComplexType()) {
8330 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect();
8331 }
8332 else {
8333 return DefaultABIInfo::classifyReturnType(Ty);
8334 }
8335}
8336
8337void SparcV8ABIInfo::computeInfo(CGFunctionInfo &FI) const {
8338
8339 FI.getReturnInfo() = classifyReturnType(FI.getReturnType());
8340 for (auto &Arg : FI.arguments())
8341 Arg.info = classifyArgumentType(Arg.type);
8342}
8343
8344namespace {
8345class SparcV8TargetCodeGenInfo : public TargetCodeGenInfo {
8346public:
8347 SparcV8TargetCodeGenInfo(CodeGenTypes &CGT)
8348 : TargetCodeGenInfo(new SparcV8ABIInfo(CGT)) {}
8349};
8350} // end anonymous namespace
8351
8352//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
8353// SPARC v9 ABI Implementation.
8354// Based on the SPARC Compliance Definition version 2.4.1.
8355//
8356// Function arguments a mapped to a nominal "parameter array" and promoted to
8357// registers depending on their type. Each argument occupies 8 or 16 bytes in
8358// the array, structs larger than 16 bytes are passed indirectly.
8359//
8360// One case requires special care:
8361//
8362// struct mixed {
8363// int i;
8364// float f;
8365// };
8366//
8367// When a struct mixed is passed by value, it only occupies 8 bytes in the
8368// parameter array, but the int is passed in an integer register, and the float
8369// is passed in a floating point register. This is represented as two arguments
8370// with the LLVM IR inreg attribute:
8371//
8372// declare void f(i32 inreg %i, float inreg %f)
8373//
8374// The code generator will only allocate 4 bytes from the parameter array for
8375// the inreg arguments. All other arguments are allocated a multiple of 8
8376// bytes.
8377//
8378namespace {
8379class SparcV9ABIInfo : public ABIInfo {
8380public:
8381 SparcV9ABIInfo(CodeGenTypes &CGT) : ABIInfo(CGT) {}
8382
8383private:
8384 ABIArgInfo classifyType(QualType RetTy, unsigned SizeLimit) const;
8385 void computeInfo(CGFunctionInfo &FI) const override;
8386 Address EmitVAArg(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Address VAListAddr,
8387 QualType Ty) const override;
8388
8389 // Coercion type builder for structs passed in registers. The coercion type
8390 // serves two purposes:
8391 //
8392 // 1. Pad structs to a multiple of 64 bits, so they are passed 'left-aligned'
8393 // in registers.
8394 // 2. Expose aligned floating point elements as first-level elements, so the
8395 // code generator knows to pass them in floating point registers.
8396 //
8397 // We also compute the InReg flag which indicates that the struct contains
8398 // aligned 32-bit floats.
8399 //
8400 struct CoerceBuilder {
8401 llvm::LLVMContext &Context;
8402 const llvm::DataLayout &DL;
8403 SmallVector<llvm::Type*, 8> Elems;
8404 uint64_t Size;
8405 bool InReg;
8406
8407 CoerceBuilder(llvm::LLVMContext &c, const llvm::DataLayout &dl)
8408 : Context(c), DL(dl), Size(0), InReg(false) {}
8409
8410 // Pad Elems with integers until Size is ToSize.
8411 void pad(uint64_t ToSize) {
8412 assert(ToSize >= Size && "Cannot remove elements");
8413 if (ToSize == Size)
8414 return;
8415
8416 // Finish the current 64-bit word.
8417 uint64_t Aligned = llvm::alignTo(Size, 64);
8418 if (Aligned > Size && Aligned <= ToSize) {
8419 Elems.push_back(llvm::IntegerType::get(Context, Aligned - Size));
8420 Size = Aligned;
8421 }
8422
8423 // Add whole 64-bit words.
8424 while (Size + 64 <= ToSize) {
8425 Elems.push_back(llvm::Type::getInt64Ty(Context));
8426 Size += 64;
8427 }
8428
8429 // Final in-word padding.
8430 if (Size < ToSize) {
8431 Elems.push_back(llvm::IntegerType::get(Context, ToSize - Size));
8432 Size = ToSize;
8433 }
8434 }
8435
8436 // Add a floating point element at Offset.
8437 void addFloat(uint64_t Offset, llvm::Type *Ty, unsigned Bits) {
8438 // Unaligned floats are treated as integers.
8439 if (Offset % Bits)
8440 return;
8441 // The InReg flag is only required if there are any floats < 64 bits.
8442 if (Bits < 64)
8443 InReg = true;
8444 pad(Offset);
8445 Elems.push_back(Ty);
8446 Size = Offset + Bits;
8447 }
8448
8449 // Add a struct type to the coercion type, starting at Offset (in bits).
8450 void addStruct(uint64_t Offset, llvm::StructType *StrTy) {
8451 const llvm::StructLayout *Layout = DL.getStructLayout(StrTy);
8452 for (unsigned i = 0, e = StrTy->getNumElements(); i != e; ++i) {
8453 llvm::Type *ElemTy = StrTy->getElementType(i);
8454 uint64_t ElemOffset = Offset + Layout->getElementOffsetInBits(i);
8455 switch (ElemTy->getTypeID()) {
8456 case llvm::Type::StructTyID:
8457 addStruct(ElemOffset, cast<llvm::StructType>(ElemTy));
8458 break;
8459 case llvm::Type::FloatTyID:
8460 addFloat(ElemOffset, ElemTy, 32);
8461 break;
8462 case llvm::Type::DoubleTyID:
8463 addFloat(ElemOffset, ElemTy, 64);
8464 break;
8465 case llvm::Type::FP128TyID:
8466 addFloat(ElemOffset, ElemTy, 128);
8467 break;
8468 case llvm::Type::PointerTyID:
8469 if (ElemOffset % 64 == 0) {
8470 pad(ElemOffset);
8471 Elems.push_back(ElemTy);
8472 Size += 64;
8473 }
8474 break;
8475 default:
8476 break;
8477 }
8478 }
8479 }
8480
8481 // Check if Ty is a usable substitute for the coercion type.
8482 bool isUsableType(llvm::StructType *Ty) const {
8483 return llvm::makeArrayRef(Elems) == Ty->elements();
8484 }
8485
8486 // Get the coercion type as a literal struct type.
8487 llvm::Type *getType() const {
8488 if (Elems.size() == 1)
8489 return Elems.front();
8490 else
8491 return llvm::StructType::get(Context, Elems);
8492 }
8493 };
8494};
8495} // end anonymous namespace
8496
8497ABIArgInfo
8498SparcV9ABIInfo::classifyType(QualType Ty, unsigned SizeLimit) const {
8499 if (Ty->isVoidType())
8500 return ABIArgInfo::getIgnore();
8501
8502 uint64_t Size = getContext().getTypeSize(Ty);
8503
8504 // Anything too big to fit in registers is passed with an explicit indirect
8505 // pointer / sret pointer.
8506 if (Size > SizeLimit)
8507 return getNaturalAlignIndirect(Ty, /*ByVal=*/false);
8508
8509 // Treat an enum type as its underlying type.
8510 if (const EnumType *EnumTy = Ty->getAs<EnumType>())
8511 Ty = EnumTy->getDecl()->getIntegerType();
8512
8513 // Integer types smaller than a register are extended.
8514 if (Size < 64 && Ty->isIntegerType())
8515 return ABIArgInfo::getExtend(Ty);
8516
8517 // Other non-aggregates go in registers.
8518 if (!isAggregateTypeForABI(Ty))
8519 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect();
8520
8521 // If a C++ object has either a non-trivial copy constructor or a non-trivial
8522 // destructor, it is passed with an explicit indirect pointer / sret pointer.
8523 if (CGCXXABI::RecordArgABI RAA = getRecordArgABI(Ty, getCXXABI()))
8524 return getNaturalAlignIndirect(Ty, RAA == CGCXXABI::RAA_DirectInMemory);
8525
8526 // This is a small aggregate type that should be passed in registers.
8527 // Build a coercion type from the LLVM struct type.
8528 llvm::StructType *StrTy = dyn_cast<llvm::StructType>(CGT.ConvertType(Ty));
8529 if (!StrTy)
8530 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect();
8531
8532 CoerceBuilder CB(getVMContext(), getDataLayout());
8533 CB.addStruct(0, StrTy);
8534 CB.pad(llvm::alignTo(CB.DL.getTypeSizeInBits(StrTy), 64));
8535
8536 // Try to use the original type for coercion.
8537 llvm::Type *CoerceTy = CB.isUsableType(StrTy) ? StrTy : CB.getType();
8538
8539 if (CB.InReg)
8540 return ABIArgInfo::getDirectInReg(CoerceTy);
8541 else
8542 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(CoerceTy);
8543}
8544
8545Address SparcV9ABIInfo::EmitVAArg(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Address VAListAddr,
8546 QualType Ty) const {
8547 ABIArgInfo AI = classifyType(Ty, 16 * 8);
8548 llvm::Type *ArgTy = CGT.ConvertType(Ty);
8549 if (AI.canHaveCoerceToType() && !AI.getCoerceToType())
8550 AI.setCoerceToType(ArgTy);
8551
8552 CharUnits SlotSize = CharUnits::fromQuantity(8);
8553
8554 CGBuilderTy &Builder = CGF.Builder;
8555 Address Addr(Builder.CreateLoad(VAListAddr, "ap.cur"), SlotSize);
8556 llvm::Type *ArgPtrTy = CGF.CGM.getPointerInDefaultAS(ArgTy);
8557
8558 auto TypeInfo = getContext().getTypeInfoInChars(Ty);
8559
8560 Address ArgAddr = Address::invalid();
8561 CharUnits Stride;
8562 switch (AI.getKind()) {
8563 case ABIArgInfo::Expand:
8564 case ABIArgInfo::CoerceAndExpand:
8565 case ABIArgInfo::InAlloca:
8566 llvm_unreachable("Unsupported ABI kind for va_arg");
8567
8568 case ABIArgInfo::Extend: {
8569 Stride = SlotSize;
8570 CharUnits Offset = SlotSize - TypeInfo.first;
8571 ArgAddr = Builder.CreateConstInBoundsByteGEP(Addr, Offset, "extend");
8572 break;
8573 }
8574
8575 case ABIArgInfo::Direct: {
8576 auto AllocSize = getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(AI.getCoerceToType());
8577 Stride = CharUnits::fromQuantity(AllocSize).alignTo(SlotSize);
8578 ArgAddr = Addr;
8579 break;
8580 }
8581
8582 case ABIArgInfo::Indirect:
8583 Stride = SlotSize;
8584 ArgAddr = Builder.CreateElementBitCast(Addr, ArgPtrTy, "indirect");
8585 ArgAddr = Address(Builder.CreateLoad(ArgAddr, "indirect.arg"),
8586 TypeInfo.second);
8587 break;
8588
8589 case ABIArgInfo::Ignore:
8590 return Address(llvm::UndefValue::get(ArgPtrTy), TypeInfo.second);
8591 }
8592
8593 // Update VAList.
8594 Address NextPtr = Builder.CreateConstInBoundsByteGEP(Addr, Stride, "ap.next");
8595 Builder.CreateStore(NextPtr.getPointer(), VAListAddr);
8596
8597 return Builder.CreateBitCast(ArgAddr, ArgPtrTy, "arg.addr");
8598}
8599
8600void SparcV9ABIInfo::computeInfo(CGFunctionInfo &FI) const {
8601 FI.getReturnInfo() = classifyType(FI.getReturnType(), 32 * 8);
8602 for (auto &I : FI.arguments())
8603 I.info = classifyType(I.type, 16 * 8);
8604}
8605
8606namespace {
8607class SparcV9TargetCodeGenInfo : public TargetCodeGenInfo {
8608public:
8609 SparcV9TargetCodeGenInfo(CodeGenTypes &CGT)
8610 : TargetCodeGenInfo(new SparcV9ABIInfo(CGT)) {}
8611
8612 int getDwarfEHStackPointer(CodeGen::CodeGenModule &M) const override {
8613 return 14;
8614 }
8615
8616 bool initDwarfEHRegSizeTable(CodeGen::CodeGenFunction &CGF,
8617 llvm::Value *Address) const override;
8618};
8619} // end anonymous namespace
8620
8621bool
8622SparcV9TargetCodeGenInfo::initDwarfEHRegSizeTable(CodeGen::CodeGenFunction &CGF,
8623 llvm::Value *Address) const {
8624 // This is calculated from the LLVM and GCC tables and verified
8625 // against gcc output. AFAIK all ABIs use the same encoding.
8626
8627 CodeGen::CGBuilderTy &Builder = CGF.Builder;
8628
8629 llvm::IntegerType *i8 = CGF.Int8Ty;
8630 llvm::Value *Four8 = llvm::ConstantInt::get(i8, 4);
8631 llvm::Value *Eight8 = llvm::ConstantInt::get(i8, 8);
8632
8633 // 0-31: the 8-byte general-purpose registers
8634 AssignToArrayRange(Builder, Address, Eight8, 0, 31);
8635
8636 // 32-63: f0-31, the 4-byte floating-point registers
8637 AssignToArrayRange(Builder, Address, Four8, 32, 63);
8638
8639 // Y = 64
8640 // PSR = 65
8641 // WIM = 66
8642 // TBR = 67
8643 // PC = 68
8644 // NPC = 69
8645 // FSR = 70
8646 // CSR = 71
8647 AssignToArrayRange(Builder, Address, Eight8, 64, 71);
8648
8649 // 72-87: d0-15, the 8-byte floating-point registers
8650 AssignToArrayRange(Builder, Address, Eight8, 72, 87);
8651
8652 return false;
8653}
8654
8655// ARC ABI implementation.
8656namespace {
8657
8658class ARCABIInfo : public DefaultABIInfo {
8659public:
8660 using DefaultABIInfo::DefaultABIInfo;
8661
8662private:
8663 Address EmitVAArg(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Address VAListAddr,
8664 QualType Ty) const override;
8665
8666 void updateState(const ABIArgInfo &Info, QualType Ty, CCState &State) const {
8667 if (!State.FreeRegs)
8668 return;
8669 if (Info.isIndirect() && Info.getInReg())
8670 State.FreeRegs--;
8671 else if (Info.isDirect() && Info.getInReg()) {
8672 unsigned sz = (getContext().getTypeSize(Ty) + 31) / 32;
8673 if (sz < State.FreeRegs)
8674 State.FreeRegs -= sz;
8675 else
8676 State.FreeRegs = 0;
8677 }
8678 }
8679
8680 void computeInfo(CGFunctionInfo &FI) const override {
8681 CCState State(FI.getCallingConvention());
8682 // ARC uses 8 registers to pass arguments.
8683 State.FreeRegs = 8;
8684
8685 if (!getCXXABI().classifyReturnType(FI))
8686 FI.getReturnInfo() = classifyReturnType(FI.getReturnType());
8687 updateState(FI.getReturnInfo(), FI.getReturnType(), State);
8688 for (auto &I : FI.arguments()) {
8689 I.info = classifyArgumentType(I.type, State.FreeRegs);
8690 updateState(I.info, I.type, State);
8691 }
8692 }
8693
8694 ABIArgInfo getIndirectByRef(QualType Ty, bool HasFreeRegs) const;
8695 ABIArgInfo getIndirectByValue(QualType Ty) const;
8696 ABIArgInfo classifyArgumentType(QualType Ty, uint8_t FreeRegs) const;
8697 ABIArgInfo classifyReturnType(QualType RetTy) const;
8698};
8699
8700class ARCTargetCodeGenInfo : public TargetCodeGenInfo {
8701public:
8702 ARCTargetCodeGenInfo(CodeGenTypes &CGT)
8703 : TargetCodeGenInfo(new ARCABIInfo(CGT)) {}
8704};
8705
8706
8707ABIArgInfo ARCABIInfo::getIndirectByRef(QualType Ty, bool HasFreeRegs) const {
8708 return HasFreeRegs ? getNaturalAlignIndirectInReg(Ty) :
8709 getNaturalAlignIndirect(Ty, false);
8710}
8711
8712ABIArgInfo ARCABIInfo::getIndirectByValue(QualType Ty) const {
8713 // Compute the byval alignment.
8714 const unsigned MinABIStackAlignInBytes = 4;
8715 unsigned TypeAlign = getContext().getTypeAlign(Ty) / 8;
8716 return ABIArgInfo::getIndirect(CharUnits::fromQuantity(4), /*ByVal=*/true,
8717 TypeAlign > MinABIStackAlignInBytes);
8718}
8719
8720Address ARCABIInfo::EmitVAArg(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Address VAListAddr,
8721 QualType Ty) const {
8722 return emitVoidPtrVAArg(CGF, VAListAddr, Ty, /*indirect*/ false,
8723 getContext().getTypeInfoInChars(Ty),
8724 CharUnits::fromQuantity(4), true);
8725}
8726
8727ABIArgInfo ARCABIInfo::classifyArgumentType(QualType Ty,
8728 uint8_t FreeRegs) const {
8729 // Handle the generic C++ ABI.
8730 const RecordType *RT = Ty->getAs<RecordType>();
8731 if (RT) {
8732 CGCXXABI::RecordArgABI RAA = getRecordArgABI(RT, getCXXABI());
8733 if (RAA == CGCXXABI::RAA_Indirect)
8734 return getIndirectByRef(Ty, FreeRegs > 0);
8735
8736 if (RAA == CGCXXABI::RAA_DirectInMemory)
8737 return getIndirectByValue(Ty);
8738 }
8739
8740 // Treat an enum type as its underlying type.
8741 if (const EnumType *EnumTy = Ty->getAs<EnumType>())
8742 Ty = EnumTy->getDecl()->getIntegerType();
8743
8744 auto SizeInRegs = llvm::alignTo(getContext().getTypeSize(Ty), 32) / 32;
8745
8746 if (isAggregateTypeForABI(Ty)) {
8747 // Structures with flexible arrays are always indirect.
8748 if (RT && RT->getDecl()->hasFlexibleArrayMember())
8749 return getIndirectByValue(Ty);
8750
8751 // Ignore empty structs/unions.
8752 if (isEmptyRecord(getContext(), Ty, true))
8753 return ABIArgInfo::getIgnore();
8754
8755 llvm::LLVMContext &LLVMContext = getVMContext();
8756
8757 llvm::IntegerType *Int32 = llvm::Type::getInt32Ty(LLVMContext);
8758 SmallVector<llvm::Type *, 3> Elements(SizeInRegs, Int32);
8759 llvm::Type *Result = llvm::StructType::get(LLVMContext, Elements);
8760
8761 return FreeRegs >= SizeInRegs ?
8762 ABIArgInfo::getDirectInReg(Result) :
8763 ABIArgInfo::getDirect(Result, 0, nullptr, false);
8764 }
8765
8766 return Ty->isPromotableIntegerType() ?
8767 (FreeRegs >= SizeInRegs ? ABIArgInfo::getExtendInReg(Ty) :
8768 ABIArgInfo::getExtend(Ty)) :
8769 (FreeRegs >= SizeInRegs ? ABIArgInfo::getDirectInReg() :
8770 ABIArgInfo::getDirect());
8771}
8772
8773ABIArgInfo ARCABIInfo::classifyReturnType(QualType RetTy) const {
8774 if (RetTy->isAnyComplexType())
8775 return ABIArgInfo::getDirectInReg();
8776
8777 // Arguments of size > 4 registers are indirect.
8778 auto RetSize = llvm::alignTo(getContext().getTypeSize(RetTy), 32) / 32;
8779 if (RetSize > 4)
8780 return getIndirectByRef(RetTy, /*HasFreeRegs*/ true);
8781
8782 return DefaultABIInfo::classifyReturnType(RetTy);
8783}
8784
8785} // End anonymous namespace.
8786
8787//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
8788// XCore ABI Implementation
8789//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
8790
8791namespace {
8792
8793/// A SmallStringEnc instance is used to build up the TypeString by passing
8794/// it by reference between functions that append to it.
8795typedef llvm::SmallString<128> SmallStringEnc;
8796
8797/// TypeStringCache caches the meta encodings of Types.
8798///
8799/// The reason for caching TypeStrings is two fold:
8800/// 1. To cache a type's encoding for later uses;
8801/// 2. As a means to break recursive member type inclusion.
8802///
8803/// A cache Entry can have a Status of:
8804/// NonRecursive: The type encoding is not recursive;
8805/// Recursive: The type encoding is recursive;
8806/// Incomplete: An incomplete TypeString;
8807/// IncompleteUsed: An incomplete TypeString that has been used in a
8808/// Recursive type encoding.
8809///
8810/// A NonRecursive entry will have all of its sub-members expanded as fully
8811/// as possible. Whilst it may contain types which are recursive, the type
8812/// itself is not recursive and thus its encoding may be safely used whenever
8813/// the type is encountered.
8814///
8815/// A Recursive entry will have all of its sub-members expanded as fully as
8816/// possible. The type itself is recursive and it may contain other types which
8817/// are recursive. The Recursive encoding must not be used during the expansion
8818/// of a recursive type's recursive branch. For simplicity the code uses
8819/// IncompleteCount to reject all usage of Recursive encodings for member types.
8820///
8821/// An Incomplete entry is always a RecordType and only encodes its
8822/// identifier e.g. "s(S){}". Incomplete 'StubEnc' entries are ephemeral and
8823/// are placed into the cache during type expansion as a means to identify and
8824/// handle recursive inclusion of types as sub-members. If there is recursion
8825/// the entry becomes IncompleteUsed.
8826///
8827/// During the expansion of a RecordType's members:
8828///
8829/// If the cache contains a NonRecursive encoding for the member type, the
8830/// cached encoding is used;
8831///
8832/// If the cache contains a Recursive encoding for the member type, the
8833/// cached encoding is 'Swapped' out, as it may be incorrect, and...
8834///
8835/// If the member is a RecordType, an Incomplete encoding is placed into the
8836/// cache to break potential recursive inclusion of itself as a sub-member;
8837///
8838/// Once a member RecordType has been expanded, its temporary incomplete
8839/// entry is removed from the cache. If a Recursive encoding was swapped out
8840/// it is swapped back in;
8841///
8842/// If an incomplete entry is used to expand a sub-member, the incomplete
8843/// entry is marked as IncompleteUsed. The cache keeps count of how many
8844/// IncompleteUsed entries it currently contains in IncompleteUsedCount;
8845///
8846/// If a member's encoding is found to be a NonRecursive or Recursive viz:
8847/// IncompleteUsedCount==0, the member's encoding is added to the cache.
8848/// Else the member is part of a recursive type and thus the recursion has
8849/// been exited too soon for the encoding to be correct for the member.
8850///
8851class TypeStringCache {
8852 enum Status {NonRecursive, Recursive, Incomplete, IncompleteUsed};
8853 struct Entry {
8854 std::string Str; // The encoded TypeString for the type.
8855 enum Status State; // Information about the encoding in 'Str'.
8856 std::string Swapped; // A temporary place holder for a Recursive encoding
8857 // during the expansion of RecordType's members.
8858 };
8859 std::map<const IdentifierInfo *, struct Entry> Map;
8860 unsigned IncompleteCount; // Number of Incomplete entries in the Map.
8861 unsigned IncompleteUsedCount; // Number of IncompleteUsed entries in the Map.
8862public:
8863 TypeStringCache() : IncompleteCount(0), IncompleteUsedCount(0) {}
8864 void addIncomplete(const IdentifierInfo *ID, std::string StubEnc);
8865 bool removeIncomplete(const IdentifierInfo *ID);
8866 void addIfComplete(const IdentifierInfo *ID, StringRef Str,
8867 bool IsRecursive);
8868 StringRef lookupStr(const IdentifierInfo *ID);
8869};
8870
8871/// TypeString encodings for enum & union fields must be order.
8872/// FieldEncoding is a helper for this ordering process.
8873class FieldEncoding {
8874 bool HasName;
8875 std::string Enc;
8876public:
8877 FieldEncoding(bool b, SmallStringEnc &e) : HasName(b), Enc(e.c_str()) {}
8878 StringRef str() { return Enc; }
8879 bool operator<(const FieldEncoding &rhs) const {
8880 if (HasName != rhs.HasName) return HasName;
8881 return Enc < rhs.Enc;
8882 }
8883};
8884
8885class XCoreABIInfo : public DefaultABIInfo {
8886public:
8887 XCoreABIInfo(CodeGen::CodeGenTypes &CGT) : DefaultABIInfo(CGT) {}
8888 Address EmitVAArg(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Address VAListAddr,
8889 QualType Ty) const override;
8890};
8891
8892class XCoreTargetCodeGenInfo : public TargetCodeGenInfo {
8893 mutable TypeStringCache TSC;
8894public:
8895 XCoreTargetCodeGenInfo(CodeGenTypes &CGT)
8896 :TargetCodeGenInfo(new XCoreABIInfo(CGT)) {}
8897 void emitTargetMD(const Decl *D, llvm::GlobalValue *GV,
8898 CodeGen::CodeGenModule &M) const override;
8899};
8900
8901} // End anonymous namespace.
8902
8903// TODO: this implementation is likely now redundant with the default
8904// EmitVAArg.
8905Address XCoreABIInfo::EmitVAArg(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Address VAListAddr,
8906 QualType Ty) const {
8907 CGBuilderTy &Builder = CGF.Builder;
8908
8909 // Get the VAList.
8910 CharUnits SlotSize = CharUnits::fromQuantity(4);
8911 Address AP(Builder.CreateLoad(VAListAddr), SlotSize);
8912
8913 // Handle the argument.
8914 ABIArgInfo AI = classifyArgumentType(Ty);
8915 CharUnits TypeAlign = getContext().getTypeAlignInChars(Ty);
8916 llvm::Type *ArgTy = CGT.ConvertType(Ty);
8917 if (AI.canHaveCoerceToType() && !AI.getCoerceToType())
8918 AI.setCoerceToType(ArgTy);
8919 llvm::Type *ArgPtrTy = CGF.CGM.getPointerInDefaultAS(ArgTy);
8920
8921 Address Val = Address::invalid();
8922 CharUnits ArgSize = CharUnits::Zero();
8923 switch (AI.getKind()) {
8924 case ABIArgInfo::Expand:
8925 case ABIArgInfo::CoerceAndExpand:
8926 case ABIArgInfo::InAlloca:
8927 llvm_unreachable("Unsupported ABI kind for va_arg");
8928 case ABIArgInfo::Ignore:
8929 Val = Address(llvm::UndefValue::get(ArgPtrTy), TypeAlign);
8930 ArgSize = CharUnits::Zero();
8931 break;
8932 case ABIArgInfo::Extend:
8933 case ABIArgInfo::Direct:
8934 Val = Builder.CreateBitCast(AP, ArgPtrTy);
8935 ArgSize = CharUnits::fromQuantity(
8936 getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(AI.getCoerceToType()));
8937 ArgSize = ArgSize.alignTo(SlotSize);
8938 break;
8939 case ABIArgInfo::Indirect:
8940 Val = Builder.CreateElementBitCast(AP, ArgPtrTy);
8941 Val = Address(Builder.CreateLoad(Val), TypeAlign);
8942 ArgSize = SlotSize;
8943 break;
8944 }
8945
8946 // Increment the VAList.
8947 if (!ArgSize.isZero()) {
8948 Address APN = Builder.CreateConstInBoundsByteGEP(AP, ArgSize);
8949 Builder.CreateStore(APN.getPointer(), VAListAddr);
8950 }
8951
8952 return Val;
8953}
8954
8955/// During the expansion of a RecordType, an incomplete TypeString is placed
8956/// into the cache as a means to identify and break recursion.
8957/// If there is a Recursive encoding in the cache, it is swapped out and will
8958/// be reinserted by removeIncomplete().
8959/// All other types of encoding should have been used rather than arriving here.
8960void TypeStringCache::addIncomplete(const IdentifierInfo *ID,
8961 std::string StubEnc) {
8962 if (!ID)
8963 return;
8964 Entry &E = Map[ID];
8965 assert( (E.Str.empty() || E.State == Recursive) &&
8966 "Incorrectly use of addIncomplete");
8967 assert(!StubEnc.empty() && "Passing an empty string to addIncomplete()");
8968 E.Swapped.swap(E.Str); // swap out the Recursive
8969 E.Str.swap(StubEnc);
8970 E.State = Incomplete;
8971 ++IncompleteCount;
8972}
8973
8974/// Once the RecordType has been expanded, the temporary incomplete TypeString
8975/// must be removed from the cache.
8976/// If a Recursive was swapped out by addIncomplete(), it will be replaced.
8977/// Returns true if the RecordType was defined recursively.
8978bool TypeStringCache::removeIncomplete(const IdentifierInfo *ID) {
8979 if (!ID)
8980 return false;
8981 auto I = Map.find(ID);
8982 assert(I != Map.end() && "Entry not present");
8983 Entry &E = I->second;
8984 assert( (E.State == Incomplete ||
8985 E.State == IncompleteUsed) &&
8986 "Entry must be an incomplete type");
8987 bool IsRecursive = false;
8988 if (E.State == IncompleteUsed) {
8989 // We made use of our Incomplete encoding, thus we are recursive.
8990 IsRecursive = true;
8991 --IncompleteUsedCount;
8992 }
8993 if (E.Swapped.empty())
8994 Map.erase(I);
8995 else {
8996 // Swap the Recursive back.
8997 E.Swapped.swap(E.Str);
8998 E.Swapped.clear();
8999 E.State = Recursive;
9000 }
9001 --IncompleteCount;
9002 return IsRecursive;
9003}
9004
9005/// Add the encoded TypeString to the cache only if it is NonRecursive or
9006/// Recursive (viz: all sub-members were expanded as fully as possible).
9007void TypeStringCache::addIfComplete(const IdentifierInfo *ID, StringRef Str,
9008 bool IsRecursive) {
9009 if (!ID || IncompleteUsedCount)
9010 return; // No key or it is is an incomplete sub-type so don't add.
9011 Entry &E = Map[ID];
9012 if (IsRecursive && !E.Str.empty()) {
9013 assert(E.State==Recursive && E.Str.size() == Str.size() &&
9014 "This is not the same Recursive entry");
9015 // The parent container was not recursive after all, so we could have used
9016 // this Recursive sub-member entry after all, but we assumed the worse when
9017 // we started viz: IncompleteCount!=0.
9018 return;
9019 }
9020 assert(E.Str.empty() && "Entry already present");
9021 E.Str = Str.str();
9022 E.State = IsRecursive? Recursive : NonRecursive;
9023}
9024
9025/// Return a cached TypeString encoding for the ID. If there isn't one, or we
9026/// are recursively expanding a type (IncompleteCount != 0) and the cached
9027/// encoding is Recursive, return an empty StringRef.
9028StringRef TypeStringCache::lookupStr(const IdentifierInfo *ID) {
9029 if (!ID)
9030 return StringRef(); // We have no key.
9031 auto I = Map.find(ID);
9032 if (I == Map.end())
9033 return StringRef(); // We have no encoding.
9034 Entry &E = I->second;
9035 if (E.State == Recursive && IncompleteCount)
9036 return StringRef(); // We don't use Recursive encodings for member types.
9037
9038 if (E.State == Incomplete) {
9039 // The incomplete type is being used to break out of recursion.
9040 E.State = IncompleteUsed;
9041 ++IncompleteUsedCount;
9042 }
9043 return E.Str;
9044}
9045
9046/// The XCore ABI includes a type information section that communicates symbol
9047/// type information to the linker. The linker uses this information to verify
9048/// safety/correctness of things such as array bound and pointers et al.
9049/// The ABI only requires C (and XC) language modules to emit TypeStrings.
9050/// This type information (TypeString) is emitted into meta data for all global
9051/// symbols: definitions, declarations, functions & variables.
9052///
9053/// The TypeString carries type, qualifier, name, size & value details.
9054/// Please see 'Tools Development Guide' section 2.16.2 for format details:
9055/// https://www.xmos.com/download/public/Tools-Development-Guide%28X9114A%29.pdf
9056/// The output is tested by test/CodeGen/xcore-stringtype.c.
9057///
9058static bool getTypeString(SmallStringEnc &Enc, const Decl *D,
9059 CodeGen::CodeGenModule &CGM, TypeStringCache &TSC);
9060
9061/// XCore uses emitTargetMD to emit TypeString metadata for global symbols.
9062void XCoreTargetCodeGenInfo::emitTargetMD(const Decl *D, llvm::GlobalValue *GV,
9063 CodeGen::CodeGenModule &CGM) const {
9064 SmallStringEnc Enc;
9065 if (getTypeString(Enc, D, CGM, TSC)) {
9066 llvm::LLVMContext &Ctx = CGM.getModule().getContext();
9067 llvm::Metadata *MDVals[] = {llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(GV),
9068 llvm::MDString::get(Ctx, Enc.str())};
9069 llvm::NamedMDNode *MD =
9070 CGM.getModule().getOrInsertNamedMetadata("xcore.typestrings");
9071 MD->addOperand(llvm::MDNode::get(Ctx, MDVals));
9072 }
9073}
9074

9082 SPIRTargetCodeGenInfo(CodeGen::CodeGenTypes &CGT)
9083 : TargetCodeGenInfo(new DefaultABIInfo(CGT)) {}
9084 unsigned getOpenCLKernelCallingConv() const override;
9085};

9087} // End anonymous namespace.

9093 SPIRABI.computeInfo(FI);

9100}
9101
9102static bool appendType(SmallStringEnc &Enc, QualType QType,
9103 const CodeGen::CodeGenModule &CGM,
9104 TypeStringCache &TSC);
9105
9106/// Helper function for appendRecordType().
9107/// Builds a SmallVector containing the encoded field types in declaration
9108/// order.
9109static bool extractFieldType(SmallVectorImpl<FieldEncoding> &FE,
9110 const RecordDecl *RD,
9111 const CodeGen::CodeGenModule &CGM,
9112 TypeStringCache &TSC) {
9113 for (const auto *Field : RD->fields()) {
9114 SmallStringEnc Enc;
9115 Enc += "m(";
9116 Enc += Field->getName();
9117 Enc += "){";
9118 if (Field->isBitField()) {
9119 Enc += "b(";
9120 llvm::raw_svector_ostream OS(Enc);
9121 OS << Field->getBitWidthValue(CGM.getContext());
9122 Enc += ':';
9123 }
9124 if (!appendType(Enc, Field->getType(), CGM, TSC))
9125 return false;
9126 if (Field->isBitField())
9127 Enc += ')';
9128 Enc += '}';
9129 FE.emplace_back(!Field->getName().empty(), Enc);
9130 }
9131 return true;
9132}
9133
9134/// Appends structure and union types to Enc and adds encoding to cache.
9135/// Recursively calls appendType (via extractFieldType) for each field.
9136/// Union types have their fields ordered according to the ABI.
9137static bool appendRecordType(SmallStringEnc &Enc, const RecordType *RT,
9138 const CodeGen::CodeGenModule &CGM,
9139 TypeStringCache &TSC, const IdentifierInfo *ID) {
9140 // Append the cached TypeString if we have one.
9141 StringRef TypeString = TSC.lookupStr(ID);
9142 if (!TypeString.empty()) {
9143 Enc += TypeString;
9144 return true;
9145 }
9146
9147 // Start to emit an incomplete TypeString.
9148 size_t Start = Enc.size();
9149 Enc += (RT->isUnionType()? 'u' : 's');
9150 Enc += '(';
9151 if (ID)
9152 Enc += ID->getName();
9153 Enc += "){";
9154
9155 // We collect all encoded fields and order as necessary.
9156 bool IsRecursive = false;
9157 const RecordDecl *RD = RT->getDecl()->getDefinition();
9158 if (RD && !RD->field_empty()) {
9159 // An incomplete TypeString stub is placed in the cache for this RecordType
9160 // so that recursive calls to this RecordType will use it whilst building a
9161 // complete TypeString for this RecordType.
9162 SmallVector<FieldEncoding, 16> FE;
9163 std::string StubEnc(Enc.substr(Start).str());
9164 StubEnc += '}'; // StubEnc now holds a valid incomplete TypeString.
9165 TSC.addIncomplete(ID, std::move(StubEnc));
9166 if (!extractFieldType(FE, RD, CGM, TSC)) {
9167 (void) TSC.removeIncomplete(ID);
9168 return false;
9169 }
9170 IsRecursive = TSC.removeIncomplete(ID);
9171 // The ABI requires unions to be sorted but not structures.
9172 // See FieldEncoding::operator< for sort algorithm.
9173 if (RT->isUnionType())
9174 llvm::sort(FE);
9175 // We can now complete the TypeString.
9176 unsigned E = FE.size();
9177 for (unsigned I = 0; I != E; ++I) {
9178 if (I)
9179 Enc += ',';
9180 Enc += FE[I].str();
9181 }
9182 }
9183 Enc += '}';
9184 TSC.addIfComplete(ID, Enc.substr(Start), IsRecursive);
9185 return true;
9186}
9187
9188/// Appends enum types to Enc and adds the encoding to the cache.
9189static bool appendEnumType(SmallStringEnc &Enc, const EnumType *ET,
9190 TypeStringCache &TSC,
9191 const IdentifierInfo *ID) {
9192 // Append the cached TypeString if we have one.
9193 StringRef TypeString = TSC.lookupStr(ID);
9194 if (!TypeString.empty()) {
9195 Enc += TypeString;
9196 return true;
9197 }
9198
9199 size_t Start = Enc.size();
9200 Enc += "e(";
9201 if (ID)
9202 Enc += ID->getName();
9203 Enc += "){";
9204
9205 // We collect all encoded enumerations and order them alphanumerically.
9206 if (const EnumDecl *ED = ET->getDecl()->getDefinition()) {
9207 SmallVector<FieldEncoding, 16> FE;
9208 for (auto I = ED->enumerator_begin(), E = ED->enumerator_end(); I != E;
9209 ++I) {
9210 SmallStringEnc EnumEnc;
9211 EnumEnc += "m(";
9212 EnumEnc += I->getName();
9213 EnumEnc += "){";
9214 I->getInitVal().toString(EnumEnc);
9215 EnumEnc += '}';
9216 FE.push_back(FieldEncoding(!I->getName().empty(), EnumEnc));
9217 }
9218 llvm::sort(FE);
9219 unsigned E = FE.size();
9220 for (unsigned I = 0; I != E; ++I) {
9221 if (I)
9222 Enc += ',';
9223 Enc += FE[I].str();
9224 }
9225 }
9226 Enc += '}';
9227 TSC.addIfComplete(ID, Enc.substr(Start), false);
9228 return true;
9229}
9230
9231/// Appends type's qualifier to Enc.
9232/// This is done prior to appending the type's encoding.
9233static void appendQualifier(SmallStringEnc &Enc, QualType QT) {
9234 // Qualifiers are emitted in alphabetical order.
9235 static const char *const Table[]={"","c:","r:","cr:","v:","cv:","rv:","crv:"};
9236 int Lookup = 0;
9237 if (QT.isConstQualified())
9238 Lookup += 1<<0;
9239 if (QT.isRestrictQualified())
9240 Lookup += 1<<1;
9241 if (QT.isVolatileQualified())
9242 Lookup += 1<<2;
9243 Enc += Table[Lookup];
9244}
9245
9246/// Appends built-in types to Enc.
9247static bool appendBuiltinType(SmallStringEnc &Enc, const BuiltinType *BT) {
9248 const char *EncType;
9249 switch (BT->getKind()) {
9250 case BuiltinType::Void:
9251 EncType = "0";
9252 break;
9253 case BuiltinType::Bool:
9254 EncType = "b";
9255 break;
9256 case BuiltinType::Char_U:
9257 EncType = "uc";
9258 break;
9259 case BuiltinType::UChar:
9260 EncType = "uc";
9261 break;
9262 case BuiltinType::SChar:
9263 EncType = "sc";
9264 break;
9265 case BuiltinType::UShort:
9266 EncType = "us";
9267 break;
9268 case BuiltinType::Short:
9269 EncType = "ss";
9270 break;
9271 case BuiltinType::UInt:
9272 EncType = "ui";
9273 break;
9274 case BuiltinType::Int:
9275 EncType = "si";
9276 break;
9277 case BuiltinType::ULong:
9278 EncType = "ul";
9279 break;
9280 case BuiltinType::Long:
9281 EncType = "sl";
9282 break;
9283 case BuiltinType::ULongLong:
9284 EncType = "ull";
9285 break;
9286 case BuiltinType::LongLong:
9287 EncType = "sll";
9288 break;
9289 case BuiltinType::Float:
9290 EncType = "ft";
9291 break;
9292 case BuiltinType::Double:
9293 EncType = "d";
9294 break;
9295 case BuiltinType::LongDouble:
9296 EncType = "ld";
9297 break;
9298 default:
9299 return false;
9300 }
9301 Enc += EncType;
9302 return true;
9303}
9304
9305/// Appends a pointer encoding to Enc before calling appendType for the pointee.
9306static bool appendPointerType(SmallStringEnc &Enc, const PointerType *PT,
9307 const CodeGen::CodeGenModule &CGM,
9308 TypeStringCache &TSC) {
9309 Enc += "p(";
9310 if (!appendType(Enc, PT->getPointeeType(), CGM, TSC))
9311 return false;
9312 Enc += ')';
9313 return true;
9314}
9315
9316/// Appends array encoding to Enc before calling appendType for the element.
9317static bool appendArrayType(SmallStringEnc &Enc, QualType QT,
9318 const ArrayType *AT,
9319 const CodeGen::CodeGenModule &CGM,
9320 TypeStringCache &TSC, StringRef NoSizeEnc) {
9321 if (AT->getSizeModifier() != ArrayType::Normal)
9322 return false;
9323 Enc += "a(";
9324 if (const ConstantArrayType *CAT = dyn_cast<ConstantArrayType>(AT))
9325 CAT->getSize().toStringUnsigned(Enc);
9326 else
9327 Enc += NoSizeEnc; // Global arrays use "*", otherwise it is "".
9328 Enc += ':';
9329 // The Qualifiers should be attached to the type rather than the array.
9330 appendQualifier(Enc, QT);
9331 if (!appendType(Enc, AT->getElementType(), CGM, TSC))
9332 return false;
9333 Enc += ')';
9334 return true;
9335}
9336
9337/// Appends a function encoding to Enc, calling appendType for the return type
9338/// and the arguments.
9339static bool appendFunctionType(SmallStringEnc &Enc, const FunctionType *FT,
9340 const CodeGen::CodeGenModule &CGM,
9341 TypeStringCache &TSC) {
9342 Enc += "f{";
9343 if (!appendType(Enc, FT->getReturnType(), CGM, TSC))
9344 return false;
9345 Enc += "}(";
9346 if (const FunctionProtoType *FPT = FT->getAs<FunctionProtoType>()) {
9347 // N.B. we are only interested in the adjusted param types.
9348 auto I = FPT->param_type_begin();
9349 auto E = FPT->param_type_end();
9350 if (I != E) {
9351 do {
9352 if (!appendType(Enc, *I, CGM, TSC))
9353 return false;
9354 ++I;
9355 if (I != E)
9356 Enc += ',';
9357 } while (I != E);
9358 if (FPT->isVariadic())
9359 Enc += ",va";
9360 } else {
9361 if (FPT->isVariadic())
9362 Enc += "va";
9363 else
9364 Enc += '0';
9365 }
9366 }
9367 Enc += ')';
9368 return true;
9369}
9370
9371/// Handles the type's qualifier before dispatching a call to handle specific
9372/// type encodings.
9373static bool appendType(SmallStringEnc &Enc, QualType QType,
9374 const CodeGen::CodeGenModule &CGM,
9375 TypeStringCache &TSC) {
9376
9377 QualType QT = QType.getCanonicalType();
9378
9379 if (const ArrayType *AT = QT->getAsArrayTypeUnsafe())
9380 // The Qualifiers should be attached to the type rather than the array.
9381 // Thus we don't call appendQualifier() here.
9382 return appendArrayType(Enc, QT, AT, CGM, TSC, "");
9383
9384 appendQualifier(Enc, QT);
9385
9386 if (const BuiltinType *BT = QT->getAs<BuiltinType>())
9387 return appendBuiltinType(Enc, BT);
9388
9389 if (const PointerType *PT = QT->getAs<PointerType>())
9390 return appendPointerType(Enc, PT, CGM, TSC);
9391
9392 if (const EnumType *ET = QT->getAs<EnumType>())
9393 return appendEnumType(Enc, ET, TSC, QT.getBaseTypeIdentifier());
9394
9395 if (const RecordType *RT = QT->getAsStructureType())
9396 return appendRecordType(Enc, RT, CGM, TSC, QT.getBaseTypeIdentifier());
9397
9398 if (const RecordType *RT = QT->getAsUnionType())
9399 return appendRecordType(Enc, RT, CGM, TSC, QT.getBaseTypeIdentifier());
9400
9401 if (const FunctionType *FT = QT->getAs<FunctionType>())
9402 return appendFunctionType(Enc, FT, CGM, TSC);
9403
9404 return false;
9405}
9406
9407static bool getTypeString(SmallStringEnc &Enc, const Decl *D,
9408 CodeGen::CodeGenModule &CGM, TypeStringCache &TSC) {
9409 if (!D)
9410 return false;
9411
9412 if (const FunctionDecl *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D)) {
9413 if (FD->getLanguageLinkage() != CLanguageLinkage)
9414 return false;
9415 return appendType(Enc, FD->getType(), CGM, TSC);
9416 }
9417
9418 if (const VarDecl *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(D)) {
9419 if (VD->getLanguageLinkage() != CLanguageLinkage)
9420 return false;
9421 QualType QT = VD->getType().getCanonicalType();
9422 if (const ArrayType *AT = QT->getAsArrayTypeUnsafe()) {
9423 // Global ArrayTypes are given a size of '*' if the size is unknown.
9424 // The Qualifiers should be attached to the type rather than the array.
9425 // Thus we don't call appendQualifier() here.
9426 return appendArrayType(Enc, QT, AT, CGM, TSC, "*");
9427 }
9428 return appendType(Enc, QT, CGM, TSC);
9429 }
9430 return false;
9431}
9432
9433//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
9434// RISCV ABI Implementation
9435//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
9436
9437namespace {
9438class RISCVABIInfo : public DefaultABIInfo {
9439private:
9440 unsigned XLen; // Size of the integer ('x') registers in bits.
9441 static const int NumArgGPRs = 8;
9442
9443public:
9444 RISCVABIInfo(CodeGen::CodeGenTypes &CGT, unsigned XLen)
9445 : DefaultABIInfo(CGT), XLen(XLen) {}
9446
9447 // DefaultABIInfo's classifyReturnType and classifyArgumentType are
9448 // non-virtual, but computeInfo is virtual, so we overload it.
9449 void computeInfo(CGFunctionInfo &FI) const override;
9450
9451 ABIArgInfo classifyArgumentType(QualType Ty, bool IsFixed,
9452 int &ArgGPRsLeft) const;
9453 ABIArgInfo classifyReturnType(QualType RetTy) const;
9454
9455 Address EmitVAArg(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Address VAListAddr,
9456 QualType Ty) const override;
9457
9458 ABIArgInfo extendType(QualType Ty) const;
9459};
9460} // end anonymous namespace
9461
9462void RISCVABIInfo::computeInfo(CGFunctionInfo &FI) const {
9463 QualType RetTy = FI.getReturnType();
9464 if (!getCXXABI().classifyReturnType(FI))
9465 FI.getReturnInfo() = classifyReturnType(RetTy);
9466
9467 // IsRetIndirect is true if classifyArgumentType indicated the value should
9468 // be passed indirect or if the type size is greater than 2*xlen. e.g. fp128
9469 // is passed direct in LLVM IR, relying on the backend lowering code to
9470 // rewrite the argument list and pass indirectly on RV32.
9471 bool IsRetIndirect = FI.getReturnInfo().getKind() == ABIArgInfo::Indirect ||
9472 getContext().getTypeSize(RetTy) > (2 * XLen);
9473
9474 // We must track the number of GPRs used in order to conform to the RISC-V
9475 // ABI, as integer scalars passed in registers should have signext/zeroext
9476 // when promoted, but are anyext if passed on the stack. As GPR usage is
9477 // different for variadic arguments, we must also track whether we are
9478 // examining a vararg or not.
9479 int ArgGPRsLeft = IsRetIndirect ? NumArgGPRs - 1 : NumArgGPRs;
9480 int NumFixedArgs = FI.getNumRequiredArgs();
9481
9482 int ArgNum = 0;
9483 for (auto &ArgInfo : FI.arguments()) {
9484 bool IsFixed = ArgNum < NumFixedArgs;
9485 ArgInfo.info = classifyArgumentType(ArgInfo.type, IsFixed, ArgGPRsLeft);
9486 ArgNum++;
9487 }
9488}
9489
9490ABIArgInfo RISCVABIInfo::classifyArgumentType(QualType Ty, bool IsFixed,
9491 int &ArgGPRsLeft) const {
9492 assert(ArgGPRsLeft <= NumArgGPRs && "Arg GPR tracking underflow");
9493 Ty = useFirstFieldIfTransparentUnion(Ty);
9494
9495 // Structures with either a non-trivial destructor or a non-trivial
9496 // copy constructor are always passed indirectly.
9497 if (CGCXXABI::RecordArgABI RAA = getRecordArgABI(Ty, getCXXABI())) {
9498 if (ArgGPRsLeft)
9499 ArgGPRsLeft -= 1;
9500 return getNaturalAlignIndirect(Ty, /*ByVal=*/RAA ==
9501 CGCXXABI::RAA_DirectInMemory);
9502 }
9503
9504 // Ignore empty structs/unions.
9505 if (isEmptyRecord(getContext(), Ty, true))
9506 return ABIArgInfo::getIgnore();
9507
9508 uint64_t Size = getContext().getTypeSize(Ty);
9509 uint64_t NeededAlign = getContext().getTypeAlign(Ty);
9510 bool MustUseStack = false;
9511 // Determine the number of GPRs needed to pass the current argument
9512 // according to the ABI. 2*XLen-aligned varargs are passed in "aligned"
9513 // register pairs, so may consume 3 registers.
9514 int NeededArgGPRs = 1;
9515 if (!IsFixed && NeededAlign == 2 * XLen)
9516 NeededArgGPRs = 2 + (ArgGPRsLeft % 2);
9517 else if (Size > XLen && Size <= 2 * XLen)
9518 NeededArgGPRs = 2;
9519
9520 if (NeededArgGPRs > ArgGPRsLeft) {
9521 MustUseStack = true;
9522 NeededArgGPRs = ArgGPRsLeft;
9523 }
9524
9525 ArgGPRsLeft -= NeededArgGPRs;
9526
9527 if (!isAggregateTypeForABI(Ty) && !Ty->isVectorType()) {
9528 // Treat an enum type as its underlying type.
9529 if (const EnumType *EnumTy = Ty->getAs<EnumType>())
9530 Ty = EnumTy->getDecl()->getIntegerType();
9531
9532 // All integral types are promoted to XLen width, unless passed on the
9533 // stack.
9534 if (Size < XLen && Ty->isIntegralOrEnumerationType() && !MustUseStack) {
9535 return extendType(Ty);
9536 }
9537
9538 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect();
9539 }
9540
9541 // Aggregates which are <= 2*XLen will be passed in registers if possible,
9542 // so coerce to integers.
9543 if (Size <= 2 * XLen) {
9544 unsigned Alignment = getContext().getTypeAlign(Ty);
9545
9546 // Use a single XLen int if possible, 2*XLen if 2*XLen alignment is
9547 // required, and a 2-element XLen array if only XLen alignment is required.
9548 if (Size <= XLen) {
9549 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(
9550 llvm::IntegerType::get(getVMContext(), XLen));
9551 } else if (Alignment == 2 * XLen) {
9552 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(
9553 llvm::IntegerType::get(getVMContext(), 2 * XLen));
9554 } else {
9555 return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(llvm::ArrayType::get(
9556 llvm::IntegerType::get(getVMContext(), XLen), 2));
9557 }
9558 }
9559 return getNaturalAlignIndirect(Ty, /*ByVal=*/false);
9560}
9561
9562ABIArgInfo RISCVABIInfo::classifyReturnType(QualType RetTy) const {
9563 if (RetTy->isVoidType())
9564 return ABIArgInfo::getIgnore();
9565
9566 int ArgGPRsLeft = 2;
9567
9568 // The rules for return and argument types are the same, so defer to
9569 // classifyArgumentType.
9570 return classifyArgumentType(RetTy, /*IsFixed=*/true, ArgGPRsLeft);
9571}
9572
9573Address RISCVABIInfo::EmitVAArg(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Address VAListAddr,
9574 QualType Ty) const {
9575 CharUnits SlotSize = CharUnits::fromQuantity(XLen / 8);
9576
9577 // Empty records are ignored for parameter passing purposes.
9578 if (isEmptyRecord(getContext(), Ty, true)) {
9579 Address Addr(CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(VAListAddr), SlotSize);
9580 Addr = CGF.Builder.CreateElementBitCast(Addr, CGF.ConvertTypeForMem(Ty));
9581 return Addr;
9582 }
9583
9584 std::pair<CharUnits, CharUnits> SizeAndAlign =
9585 getContext().getTypeInfoInChars(Ty);
9586
9587 // Arguments bigger than 2*Xlen bytes are passed indirectly.
9588 bool IsIndirect = SizeAndAlign.first > 2 * SlotSize;
9589
9590 return emitVoidPtrVAArg(CGF, VAListAddr, Ty, IsIndirect, SizeAndAlign,
9591 SlotSize, /*AllowHigherAlign=*/true);
9592}
9593
9594ABIArgInfo RISCVABIInfo::extendType(QualType Ty) const {
9595 int TySize = getContext().getTypeSize(Ty);
9596 // RV64 ABI requires unsigned 32 bit integers to be sign extended.
9597 if (XLen == 64 && Ty->isUnsignedIntegerOrEnumerationType() && TySize == 32)
9598 return ABIArgInfo::getSignExtend(Ty);
9599 return ABIArgInfo::getExtend(Ty);
9600}
9601
9602namespace {
9603class RISCVTargetCodeGenInfo : public TargetCodeGenInfo {
9604public:
9605 RISCVTargetCodeGenInfo(CodeGen::CodeGenTypes &CGT, unsigned XLen)
9606 : TargetCodeGenInfo(new RISCVABIInfo(CGT, XLen)) {}
9607
9608 void setTargetAttributes(const Decl *D, llvm::GlobalValue *GV,
9609 CodeGen::CodeGenModule &CGM) const override {
9610 const auto *FD = dyn_cast_or_null<FunctionDecl>(D);
9611 if (!FD) return;
9612
9613 const auto *Attr = FD->getAttr<RISCVInterruptAttr>();
9614 if (!Attr)
9615 return;
9616
9617 const char *Kind;
9618 switch (Attr->getInterrupt()) {
9619 case RISCVInterruptAttr::user: Kind = "user"; break;
9620 case RISCVInterruptAttr::supervisor: Kind = "supervisor"; break;
9621 case RISCVInterruptAttr::machine: Kind = "machine"; break;
9622 }
9623
9624 auto *Fn = cast<llvm::Function>(GV);
9625
9626 Fn->addFnAttr("interrupt", Kind);
9627 }
9628};
9629} // namespace
