9631//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
9632// Driver code
9633//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
9634
9635bool CodeGenModule::supportsCOMDAT() const {
9636 return getTriple().supportsCOMDAT();
9637}
9638
9639const TargetCodeGenInfo &CodeGenModule::getTargetCodeGenInfo() {
9640 if (TheTargetCodeGenInfo)
9641 return *TheTargetCodeGenInfo;
9642
9643 // Helper to set the unique_ptr while still keeping the return value.
9644 auto SetCGInfo = [&](TargetCodeGenInfo *P) -> const TargetCodeGenInfo & {
9645 this->TheTargetCodeGenInfo.reset(P);
9646 return *P;
9647 };
9648
9649 const llvm::Triple &Triple = getTarget().getTriple();
9650 switch (Triple.getArch()) {
9651 default:
9652 return SetCGInfo(new DefaultTargetCodeGenInfo(Types));
9653
9654 case llvm::Triple::le32:
9655 return SetCGInfo(new PNaClTargetCodeGenInfo(Types));
9656 case llvm::Triple::mips:
9657 case llvm::Triple::mipsel:
9658 if (Triple.getOS() == llvm::Triple::NaCl)
9659 return SetCGInfo(new PNaClTargetCodeGenInfo(Types));
9660 return SetCGInfo(new MIPSTargetCodeGenInfo(Types, true, *this));
9661
9662 case llvm::Triple::mips64:
9663 case llvm::Triple::mips64el:
9664 case llvm::Triple::cheri:
9665 return SetCGInfo(new MIPSTargetCodeGenInfo(Types, false, *this));
9666
9667 case llvm::Triple::avr:
9668 return SetCGInfo(new AVRTargetCodeGenInfo(Types));
9669
9670 case llvm::Triple::aarch64:
9671 case llvm::Triple::aarch64_be: {
9672 AArch64ABIInfo::ABIKind Kind = AArch64ABIInfo::AAPCS;
9673 if (getTarget().getABI() == "darwinpcs")
9674 Kind = AArch64ABIInfo::DarwinPCS;
9675 else if (Triple.isOSWindows())
9676 return SetCGInfo(
9677 new WindowsAArch64TargetCodeGenInfo(Types, AArch64ABIInfo::Win64));
9678
9679 return SetCGInfo(new AArch64TargetCodeGenInfo(Types, Kind));
9680 }
9681
9682 case llvm::Triple::wasm32:
9683 case llvm::Triple::wasm64:
9684 return SetCGInfo(new WebAssemblyTargetCodeGenInfo(Types));
9685
9686 case llvm::Triple::arm:
9687 case llvm::Triple::armeb:
9688 case llvm::Triple::thumb:
9689 case llvm::Triple::thumbeb: {
9690 if (Triple.getOS() == llvm::Triple::Win32) {
9691 return SetCGInfo(
9692 new WindowsARMTargetCodeGenInfo(Types, ARMABIInfo::AAPCS_VFP));
9693 }
9694
9695 ARMABIInfo::ABIKind Kind = ARMABIInfo::AAPCS;
9696 StringRef ABIStr = getTarget().getABI();
9697 if (ABIStr == "apcs-gnu")
9698 Kind = ARMABIInfo::APCS;
9699 else if (ABIStr == "aapcs16")
9700 Kind = ARMABIInfo::AAPCS16_VFP;
9701 else if (CodeGenOpts.FloatABI == "hard" ||
9702 (CodeGenOpts.FloatABI != "soft" &&
9703 (Triple.getEnvironment() == llvm::Triple::GNUEABIHF ||
9704 Triple.getEnvironment() == llvm::Triple::MuslEABIHF ||
9705 Triple.getEnvironment() == llvm::Triple::EABIHF)))
9706 Kind = ARMABIInfo::AAPCS_VFP;
9707
9708 return SetCGInfo(new ARMTargetCodeGenInfo(Types, Kind));
9709 }
9710
9711 case llvm::Triple::ppc:
9712 return SetCGInfo(
9713 new PPC32TargetCodeGenInfo(Types, CodeGenOpts.FloatABI == "soft"));
9714 case llvm::Triple::ppc64:
9715 if (Triple.isOSBinFormatELF()) {
9716 PPC64_SVR4_ABIInfo::ABIKind Kind = PPC64_SVR4_ABIInfo::ELFv1;
9717 if (getTarget().getABI() == "elfv2")
9718 Kind = PPC64_SVR4_ABIInfo::ELFv2;
9719 bool HasQPX = getTarget().getABI() == "elfv1-qpx";
9720 bool IsSoftFloat = CodeGenOpts.FloatABI == "soft";
9721
9722 return SetCGInfo(new PPC64_SVR4_TargetCodeGenInfo(Types, Kind, HasQPX,
9723 IsSoftFloat));
9724 } else
9725 return SetCGInfo(new PPC64TargetCodeGenInfo(Types));
9726 case llvm::Triple::ppc64le: {
9727 assert(Triple.isOSBinFormatELF() && "PPC64 LE non-ELF not supported!");
9728 PPC64_SVR4_ABIInfo::ABIKind Kind = PPC64_SVR4_ABIInfo::ELFv2;
9729 if (getTarget().getABI() == "elfv1" || getTarget().getABI() == "elfv1-qpx")
9730 Kind = PPC64_SVR4_ABIInfo::ELFv1;
9731 bool HasQPX = getTarget().getABI() == "elfv1-qpx";
9732 bool IsSoftFloat = CodeGenOpts.FloatABI == "soft";
9733
9734 return SetCGInfo(new PPC64_SVR4_TargetCodeGenInfo(Types, Kind, HasQPX,
9735 IsSoftFloat));
9736 }
9737
9738 case llvm::Triple::nvptx:
9739 case llvm::Triple::nvptx64:
9740 return SetCGInfo(new NVPTXTargetCodeGenInfo(Types));
9741
9742 case llvm::Triple::msp430:
9743 return SetCGInfo(new MSP430TargetCodeGenInfo(Types));
9744
9745 case llvm::Triple::riscv32:
9746 return SetCGInfo(new RISCVTargetCodeGenInfo(Types, 32));
9747 case llvm::Triple::riscv64:
9748 return SetCGInfo(new RISCVTargetCodeGenInfo(Types, 64));
9749
9750 case llvm::Triple::systemz: {
9751 bool HasVector = getTarget().getABI() == "vector";
9752 return SetCGInfo(new SystemZTargetCodeGenInfo(Types, HasVector));
9753 }
9754
9755 case llvm::Triple::tce:
9756 case llvm::Triple::tcele:
9757 return SetCGInfo(new TCETargetCodeGenInfo(Types));
9758
9759 case llvm::Triple::x86: {
9760 bool IsDarwinVectorABI = Triple.isOSDarwin();
9761 bool RetSmallStructInRegABI =
9762 X86_32TargetCodeGenInfo::isStructReturnInRegABI(Triple, CodeGenOpts);
9763 bool IsWin32FloatStructABI = Triple.isOSWindows() && !Triple.isOSCygMing();
9764
9765 if (Triple.getOS() == llvm::Triple::Win32) {
9766 return SetCGInfo(new WinX86_32TargetCodeGenInfo(
9767 Types, IsDarwinVectorABI, RetSmallStructInRegABI,
9768 IsWin32FloatStructABI, CodeGenOpts.NumRegisterParameters));
9769 } else {
9770 bool EnableMMX = getContext().getTargetInfo().getABI() != "no-mmx";
9771 return SetCGInfo(new X86_32TargetCodeGenInfo(
9772 Types, IsDarwinVectorABI, RetSmallStructInRegABI,
9773 IsWin32FloatStructABI, CodeGenOpts.NumRegisterParameters,
9774 CodeGenOpts.FloatABI == "soft", EnableMMX));
9775 }
9776 }
9777
9778 case llvm::Triple::x86_64: {
9779 StringRef ABI = getTarget().getABI();
9780 X86AVXABILevel AVXLevel =
9781 (ABI == "avx512"
9782 ? X86AVXABILevel::AVX512
9783 : ABI == "avx" ? X86AVXABILevel::AVX : X86AVXABILevel::None);
9784
9785 switch (Triple.getOS()) {
9786 case llvm::Triple::Win32:
9787 return SetCGInfo(new WinX86_64TargetCodeGenInfo(Types, AVXLevel));
9788 default:
9789 return SetCGInfo(new X86_64TargetCodeGenInfo(Types, AVXLevel));
9790 }
9791 }
9792 case llvm::Triple::hexagon:
9793 return SetCGInfo(new HexagonTargetCodeGenInfo(Types));
9794 case llvm::Triple::lanai:
9795 return SetCGInfo(new LanaiTargetCodeGenInfo(Types));
9796 case llvm::Triple::r600:
9797 return SetCGInfo(new AMDGPUTargetCodeGenInfo(Types));
9798 case llvm::Triple::amdgcn:
9799 return SetCGInfo(new AMDGPUTargetCodeGenInfo(Types));
9800 case llvm::Triple::sparc:
9801 return SetCGInfo(new SparcV8TargetCodeGenInfo(Types));
9802 case llvm::Triple::sparcv9:
9803 return SetCGInfo(new SparcV9TargetCodeGenInfo(Types));
9804 case llvm::Triple::xcore:
9805 return SetCGInfo(new XCoreTargetCodeGenInfo(Types));
9806 case llvm::Triple::arc:
9807 return SetCGInfo(new ARCTargetCodeGenInfo(Types));
9808 case llvm::Triple::spir:
9809 case llvm::Triple::spir64:
9810 return SetCGInfo(new SPIRTargetCodeGenInfo(Types));
9811 }
9812}
9813
9814/// Create an OpenCL kernel for an enqueued block.
9815///
9816/// The kernel has the same function type as the block invoke function. Its
9817/// name is the name of the block invoke function postfixed with "_kernel".
9818/// It simply calls the block invoke function then returns.
9819llvm::Function *
9820TargetCodeGenInfo::createEnqueuedBlockKernel(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
9821 llvm::Function *Invoke,
9822 llvm::Value *BlockLiteral) const {
9823 auto *InvokeFT = Invoke->getFunctionType();
9824 llvm::SmallVector<llvm::Type *, 2> ArgTys;
9825 for (auto &P : InvokeFT->params())
9826 ArgTys.push_back(P);
9827 auto &C = CGF.getLLVMContext();
9828 std::string Name = Invoke->getName().str() + "_kernel";
9829 auto *FT = llvm::FunctionType::get(llvm::Type::getVoidTy(C), ArgTys, false);
9830 auto *F = llvm::Function::Create(FT, llvm::GlobalValue::InternalLinkage, Name,
9831 &CGF.CGM.getModule());
9832 auto IP = CGF.Builder.saveIP();
9833 auto *BB = llvm::BasicBlock::Create(C, "entry", F);
9834 auto &Builder = CGF.Builder;
9835 Builder.SetInsertPoint(BB);
9836 llvm::SmallVector<llvm::Value *, 2> Args;
9837 for (auto &A : F->args())
9838 Args.push_back(&A);
9839 Builder.CreateCall(Invoke, Args);
9840 Builder.CreateRetVoid();
9841 Builder.restoreIP(IP);
9842 return F;
9843}
9844
9845/// Create an OpenCL kernel for an enqueued block.
9846///
9847/// The type of the first argument (the block literal) is the struct type
9848/// of the block literal instead of a pointer type. The first argument
9849/// (block literal) is passed directly by value to the kernel. The kernel
9850/// allocates the same type of struct on stack and stores the block literal
9851/// to it and passes its pointer to the block invoke function. The kernel
9852/// has "enqueued-block" function attribute and kernel argument metadata.
9853llvm::Function *AMDGPUTargetCodeGenInfo::createEnqueuedBlockKernel(
9854 CodeGenFunction &CGF, llvm::Function *Invoke,
9855 llvm::Value *BlockLiteral) const {
9856 auto &Builder = CGF.Builder;
9857 auto &C = CGF.getLLVMContext();
9858
9859 auto *BlockTy = BlockLiteral->getType()->getPointerElementType();
9860 auto *InvokeFT = Invoke->getFunctionType();
9861 llvm::SmallVector<llvm::Type *, 2> ArgTys;
9862 llvm::SmallVector<llvm::Metadata *, 8> AddressQuals;
9863 llvm::SmallVector<llvm::Metadata *, 8> AccessQuals;
9864 llvm::SmallVector<llvm::Metadata *, 8> ArgTypeNames;
9865 llvm::SmallVector<llvm::Metadata *, 8> ArgBaseTypeNames;
9866 llvm::SmallVector<llvm::Metadata *, 8> ArgTypeQuals;
9867 llvm::SmallVector<llvm::Metadata *, 8> ArgNames;
9868
9869 ArgTys.push_back(BlockTy);
9870 ArgTypeNames.push_back(llvm::MDString::get(C, "__block_literal"));
9871 AddressQuals.push_back(llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(Builder.getInt32(0)));
9872 ArgBaseTypeNames.push_back(llvm::MDString::get(C, "__block_literal"));
9873 ArgTypeQuals.push_back(llvm::MDString::get(C, ""));
9874 AccessQuals.push_back(llvm::MDString::get(C, "none"));
9875 ArgNames.push_back(llvm::MDString::get(C, "block_literal"));
9876 for (unsigned I = 1, E = InvokeFT->getNumParams(); I < E; ++I) {
9877 ArgTys.push_back(InvokeFT->getParamType(I));
9878 ArgTypeNames.push_back(llvm::MDString::get(C, "void*"));
9879 AddressQuals.push_back(llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(Builder.getInt32(3)));
9880 AccessQuals.push_back(llvm::MDString::get(C, "none"));
9881 ArgBaseTypeNames.push_back(llvm::MDString::get(C, "void*"));
9882 ArgTypeQuals.push_back(llvm::MDString::get(C, ""));
9883 ArgNames.push_back(
9884 llvm::MDString::get(C, (Twine("local_arg") + Twine(I)).str()));
9885 }
9886 std::string Name = Invoke->getName().str() + "_kernel";
9887 auto *FT = llvm::FunctionType::get(llvm::Type::getVoidTy(C), ArgTys, false);
9888 auto *F = llvm::Function::Create(FT, llvm::GlobalValue::InternalLinkage, Name,
9889 &CGF.CGM.getModule());
9890 F->addFnAttr("enqueued-block");
9891 auto IP = CGF.Builder.saveIP();
9892 auto *BB = llvm::BasicBlock::Create(C, "entry", F);
9893 Builder.SetInsertPoint(BB);
9894 unsigned BlockAlign = CGF.CGM.getDataLayout().getPrefTypeAlignment(BlockTy);
9895 auto *BlockPtr = Builder.CreateAlloca(BlockTy, nullptr);
9896 BlockPtr->setAlignment(BlockAlign);
9897 Builder.CreateAlignedStore(F->arg_begin(), BlockPtr, BlockAlign);
9898 auto *Cast = Builder.CreatePointerCast(BlockPtr, InvokeFT->getParamType(0));
9899 llvm::SmallVector<llvm::Value *, 2> Args;
9900 Args.push_back(Cast);
9901 for (auto I = F->arg_begin() + 1, E = F->arg_end(); I != E; ++I)
9902 Args.push_back(I);
9903 Builder.CreateCall(Invoke, Args);
9904 Builder.CreateRetVoid();
9905 Builder.restoreIP(IP);
9906
9907 F->setMetadata("kernel_arg_addr_space", llvm::MDNode::get(C, AddressQuals));
9908 F->setMetadata("kernel_arg_access_qual", llvm::MDNode::get(C, AccessQuals));
9909 F->setMetadata("kernel_arg_type", llvm::MDNode::get(C, ArgTypeNames));
9910 F->setMetadata("kernel_arg_base_type",
9911 llvm::MDNode::get(C, ArgBaseTypeNames));
9912 F->setMetadata("kernel_arg_type_qual", llvm::MDNode::get(C, ArgTypeQuals));
9913 if (CGF.CGM.getCodeGenOpts().EmitOpenCLArgMetadata)
9914 F->setMetadata("kernel_arg_name", llvm::MDNode::get(C, ArgNames));
9915
9916 return F;
9917}
